ithin a BTM project)"],"marine_subjects":["Coral reefs","Big marine life (sharks, whales, etc.)","Macro subjects","Marine behavior","Conservation stories"],"time_availability":"2-3 entire weeks at a time for a workshop, aproject or individual training","travel_willingness":"Depends on duration and location","budget":"Advanced budget (3,000 - 6,000 €/USD)","start_timeline":"Flexible/Not sure yet","ultimate_vision":"I would love to improve my filming skills to capture the essence of the marine life with a high quality camera and to learn how to process it to make documentary films with a goal for conservation and scientific research.","inspiration_to_apply":"Always wanted to learn how to create underwater documentaries and did a short internship years ago to introduce myself to the filming. I would love to mix my knowledge in Marine Biology with audiovisual techniques.\nA friend recommended me BTM Academy.","referral_source":["Word of mouth"],"questions_or_concerns":"Duration and process of the program, process/training approach, equipment and competences required"}'::jsonb, '{}', '[]'::jsonb, '2026-02-13T16:19:28+00:00');
INSERT INTO applications (program, status, user_id, answers, tags, admin_notes, submitted_at) VALUES ('filmmaking', 'reviewing', NULL, '{"first_name":"Sandor","last_name":"Vennink","nickname":"Sandor","email":"sandor@fewture.net","phone":"611395762","age":"45-54","gender":"Male","nationality":"Netherlands","country_of_residence":"Netherlands","languages":"English, Dutch, can understand German","current_occupation":"IT Specialist Office 365 and Azure","physical_fitness":"Excellent - Regular exercise, no health concerns","health_conditions":"No health conditions affecting diving","diving_types":["Recreational Scuba diving"],"certification_level":"Divemaster","number_of_dives":"250+","last_dive_date":"28.02.2025","diving_environments":["Tropical Reefs","Deep diving","Night diving"],"buoyancy_skill":10,"equipment_owned":["DSLR/Mirrorless with housing"],"filming_equipment":"Sony ZVE1 + 16-35f4. 2x Weefine 800lumen light. Ikelite housing. 6\" dome","planning_to_invest":"Yes, within the next years","years_experience":"3-5 years","skill_camera_settings":7,"skill_lighting":3,"skill_post_production":5,"skill_color_correction":5,"skill_storytelling":2,"skill_drone":6,"skill_over_water":6,"content_created":["Personal vacation videos","Social media content"],"btm_category":"INDEPENDENT CREATOR (Experienced hobbyist/influencer seeking improvement)","involvement_level":"I do occasional projects above water. Events with drone and camera. Underwater is pure hobby/holliday.","online_presence":"None of the above","online_links":"Videos are private. Some examples:\nhttps://youtu.be/ado2RYKNxGc\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=uSrZzG0Ureg\nhttps://youtu.be/5YLUZAaJ7pY\nhttps://youtu.be/ykf2bGTxBaY\n\nInstagram with above water photo''s (I''m also a photographer)\nhttps://www.instagram.com/unlivedsv","income_from_filming":"No, not yet.","primary_goal":"Transform hobby into professional career","secondary_goal":"Improve content creation for social media","learning_aspects":["Lighting techniques","Storytelling and content planning","Post-production and editing","Business aspects of underwater filming","Client relations and project management"],"content_to_create":["Personal/travel memories","Social media content","Documentary style films","Commercial/advertising content","Scientific/research documentation","Conservation stories"],"learning_approach":["Group workshops (within a group of approx. 10 persons)","Small group workshop (within a group of approx. 4 persons)","Mixed approach (combination of group and individual)","Project-based learning (within a BTM project)"],"marine_subjects":["Coral reefs","Big marine life (sharks, whales, etc.)","Marine behavior"],"time_availability":"2-3 entire weeks at a time for a workshop, aproject or individual training","travel_willingness":"Yes, willing to travel internationally","budget":"Professional budget (6,000 - 12,000 €/USD)","start_timeline":"Flexible/Not sure yet","ultimate_vision":"I would like to explore if I can turn this into a carreer. See if i can develop the skills for it and level up my \"Holliday skill\" to professional. I''m looking for a carreer change. But.. as you may understand..this is quite the undertaking so I''m not quitting my job just yet until I have a good understanding on how far I can take this. I''m willing to commit a lot of resources if the payoff is there. Travel is no problem, money is no problem.","inspiration_to_apply":"I''ve been following you guys for years. Absolute no1 when it comes to filmmaking if you ask me.","referral_source":["Social Media (Instagram, Facebook, etc.)"],"questions_or_concerns":"I''m looking to advance my skills, find out if I have what it takes to make a living from this. So the finance/business part is important (not looking to get rich, but don''t want to starve to death either :P ), how to find customers. Getting better at story telling and upping the quality of my video (sharpness, steadiness, colours). So the general question behind this is if I can get this from the course/workshop/internship. There''s one way to find out I guess. :)","anything_else":"A little personal info; \nMy name is Sandor Vennink. I''m from the Netherlands, 46 years old, 4 kids with my partner Marleen, living in Dordrecht, NL. Diving since I was a kid and currently a certified divemaster. Love photography and diving. I have a successful career in IT, but the passion is gone. \nI''m looking to do something I love doing every day, now that the kids are getting bigger. I love making underwater video''s on hollidays. Last year I did an internship as a Divemaster on Bonaire, as I love diving, teaching and sharing knowledge. However, the diving industry (PADI system) is not for me in that sense. Maybe underwater video and photo is more my thing. That is what I want to seriously explore and see where it takes me.\nAbove water I shoot with a Canon R6, some L glass and a DJI Air 3 drone. I shoot landscapes for fun, events as a freelancer. Underwater I shoot with a Sony ZV-E1 (although most of my video''s are made with a GoPro), only for fun/hobby at the moment. I''m a techy guy, lots of IT and engineering knowledge, I''m also a relaxed person with a good sense of humor and immense passion for the sea.\nLooking forward to hearing from you.\nKind regards,\nSandor"}'::jsonb, '{}', '[]'::jsonb, '2026-02-12T17:47:53+00:00');
