ography.com\n\nSecondary YouTube Channel (for sharing reels, rough drafts, ect…)\n\nhttps://youtube.com/@scottbauerunderwater8144?si=bedBo2_9Za30WxEx","income_from_filming":"Occasionally (few projects per year)","primary_goal":"Improve content creation for social media","secondary_goal":"Transform hobby into professional career","learning_aspects":["Lighting techniques","Marine life behavior understanding","Storytelling and content planning","Post-production and editing","Business aspects of underwater filming","Client relations and project management","Conservation documentation"],"content_to_create":["Social media content","Documentary style films","Scientific/research documentation","Conservation stories"],"learning_approach":["Small group workshop (within a group of approx. 4 persons)","One-on-one mentorship","Mixed approach (combination of group and individual)","Project-based learning (within a BTM project)"],"marine_subjects":["Coral reefs","Macro subjects","Marine behavior","Conservation stories"],"time_availability":"1 week to 10 days for a workshop, a project or individual training","travel_willingness":"Yes, willing to travel internationally","budget":"Moderate budget (1,000 - 3,000 €/USD)","start_timeline":"Within next 6 months","ultimate_vision":"I currently work a 9-5 but my dream has always been to break free from the corporate life and transition to underwater filming and story telling full time","inspiration_to_apply":"I have been inspired by the content that has been created by BTM since I started diving. When I first attempted shooting underwater, I even learned the basics about underwater lighting and color from BTM tutorials on YouTube.","referral_source":["Social Media (Instagram, Facebook, etc.)"],"anything_else":"There are some very beautiful places local to me that are under threat by politics, development projects, and datacenter construction projects.  \n\nAlthough one of my goals is to be a full time film maker.  My main priority at the moment is to use my small platform to bring awareness to some very serious issues occurring in both Texas as well as Florida that are threatening some of my favorite underwater places. \n\nLearning how to perfect story telling, conduct meaningful interviews, and plan compelling underwater shots that can capture the audience’s imagination are all things that I would excited to dive deeper into."}'::jsonb, '{}', '[]'::jsonb, '2026-02-07T17:02:30+00:00');
INSERT INTO applications (program, status, user_id, answers, tags, admin_notes, submitted_at) VALUES ('filmmaking', 'reviewing', NULL, '{"first_name":"Sean","last_name":"Davies","email":"Clearasreason@hotmail.com","phone":"780 281 1951","age":"35-44","gender":"Male","nationality":"Canada","country_of_residence":"Canada","languages":"English","current_occupation":"Self employed","physical_fitness":"Excellent - Regular exercise, no health concerns","health_conditions":"No health conditions affecting diving","diving_types":["Recreational Scuba diving"],"certification_level":"Advanced Open Water","number_of_dives":"51-250","last_dive_date":"24.01.2026","diving_environments":["Tropical Reefs","Deep diving","Night diving","Cave/Wreck diving"],"buoyancy_skill":8,"equipment_owned":["DSLR/Mirrorless with housing","Lighting equipment"],"filming_equipment":"Canon R5C, canon 24-50mm, Nauticam housing, Nauticam WACP 1B port, Keldan 8XR ambient 18,000 lumen video lights.","planning_to_invest":"No immediate plans","years_experience":"1-3 years","skill_camera_settings":8,"skill_lighting":8,"skill_post_production":5,"skill_color_correction":7,"skill_storytelling":7,"skill_drone":7,"skill_over_water":9,"content_created":["Social media content"],"btm_category":"INDEPENDENT CREATOR (Experienced hobbyist/influencer seeking improvement)","involvement_level":"Hobby only","online_presence":"Active social media","online_links":"snstravellovers (Instagram)","income_from_filming":"No, not yet.","primary_goal":"Improve content creation for social media","secondary_goal":"Transform hobby into professional career","learning_aspects":["Camera settings and techniques","Lighting techniques","Storytelling and content planning","Post-production and editing","Business aspects of underwater filming"],"content_to_create":["Social media content","Documentary style films","Commercial/advertising content"],"learning_approach":["One-on-one mentorship","Mixed approach (combination of group and individual)"],"marine_subjects":["Coral reefs","Big marine life (sharks, whales, etc.)"],"time_availability":"1 week to 10 days for a workshop, a project or individual training","travel_willingness":"Yes, willing to travel internationally","budget":"Advanced budget (3,000 - 6,000 €/USD)","start_timeline":"Flexible/Not sure yet","ultimate_vision":"I want to become really good at cinematic shots, I want to learn the best storytelling, best framing, the thought process behind it, and of course post production.  This can apply to not only underwater filming but on land filming as well.","inspiration_to_apply":"My wife and I became scuba divers 2 year ago and photography and videography has already been my passion for a long time and we’ve been documenting our trips abroad but after we became divers I wanted to now film the underwater world and show its beauty and magic. It’s totally different skills of course filming underwater and I want to learn from the best (you guys 😊) how to become better at storytelling and framing and capturing cinematic shots underwater to truly convey the feeling on the screen, what it feels like in the water, showcase it in all its beauty the best way possible.","referral_source":["Online search"]}'::jsonb, '{}', '[]'::jsonb, '2026-02-06T09:20:31+00:00');
