derstanding","Storytelling and content planning"],"content_to_create":["Personal/travel memories","Documentary style films","Commercial/advertising content","Scientific/research documentation","Conservation stories"],"learning_approach":["Small group workshop (within a group of approx. 4 persons)","One-on-one mentorship","Mixed approach (combination of group and individual)","Project-based learning (within a BTM project)"],"marine_subjects":["Coral reefs","Big marine life (sharks, whales, etc.)","Macro subjects","Marine behavior","Conservation stories"],"time_availability":"2-3 entire weeks at a time for a workshop, aproject or individual training","travel_willingness":"Depends on duration and location","budget":"Moderate budget (1,000 - 3,000 €/USD)","start_timeline":"Flexible/Not sure yet","ultimate_vision":"I''ve been working in the film industry for more than a decade. But I''ve fallen in love with filming the ocean and I would like to learn more about underwater cinematography to maybe transition into a full time job.","inspiration_to_apply":"I would like to do my part against climate change. And the only thing I know is filming. So why not show the beauty of the ocean.","referral_source":["Online search"],"questions_or_concerns":"Do I need to have my own filming equipment ?"}'::jsonb, '{}', '[]'::jsonb, '2026-02-03T07:56:08+00:00');
INSERT INTO applications (program, status, user_id, answers, tags, admin_notes, submitted_at) VALUES ('filmmaking', 'reviewing', NULL, '{"first_name":"Robin","last_name":"Strellen","email":"robinstrellen@mailbox.org","phone":"+4915208796638","age":"25-34","gender":"Male","nationality":"german","country_of_residence":"Germany","languages":"English, German","current_occupation":"Self-employed organic vegetable Farmer","physical_fitness":"Good - Moderately active, no major health concerns","health_conditions":"No health conditions affecting diving","diving_types":["Recreational Scuba diving","Freediving","Snorkeling"],"certification_level":"Rescue Diver, Certified Freediver, please specify level below:, FD Level 1 - going for Level 2 & 3 this year","number_of_dives":"51-250","last_dive_date":"20.11.2025","diving_environments":["Tropical Reefs","FD in Reefs","Open Water as well as colder Lakes"],"buoyancy_skill":9,"equipment_owned":["Action camera (GoPro, Osmo, Insta360, etc)","DSLR/Mirrorless with housing","Lighting equipment","Lighting: Single Strobe for Photography only"],"filming_equipment":"DJI Osmo Action 6 & Canon EOS R8 / Current Lenses: Canon 8-15mm F4.0 USM Fisheye & 100mm F2.8 IS USM & 24-50mm F4.5-6.3 IS STM","planning_to_invest":"Yes, within the next years","years_experience":"1-3 years","skill_camera_settings":2,"skill_lighting":1,"skill_post_production":2,"skill_color_correction":3,"skill_storytelling":3,"skill_drone":1,"skill_over_water":1,"content_created":["Personal vacation videos","Social media content","Footage that was never properly processed :/"],"btm_category":"DEDICATED ACHIEVER (Business-focused, seeking intensive mentorship)","involvement_level":"Hobby only","online_presence":"Active social media, Personal website","online_links":"www.mobulaocean.com / www.instagram.com/robinstrellen/","income_from_filming":"No, not yet.","primary_goal":"Improve content creation for social media","secondary_goal":"Enhance existing professional skills","learning_aspects":["Basic equipment setup and operation","Camera settings and techniques","Marine life behavior understanding","Storytelling and content planning","Post-production and editing"],"content_to_create":["Social media content","Documentary style films","Commercial/advertising content"],"learning_approach":["Group workshops (within a group of approx. 10 persons)","Small group workshop (within a group of approx. 4 persons)","One-on-one mentorship","Mixed approach (combination of group and individual)","Project-based learning (within a BTM project)","I can picture all of it! ;)"],"marine_subjects":["Big marine life (sharks, whales, etc.)","Marine behavior"],"time_availability":"2-3 entire weeks at a time for a workshop, aproject or individual training","travel_willingness":"Yes, willing to travel internationally","budget":"Moderate budget (1,000 - 3,000 €/USD)","start_timeline":"Flexible/Not sure yet","ultimate_vision":"I''d love to feel confident in gear setup, handling and filming techniques. Actually, I''m looking to build a whole proper workflow from A to Z. Coming from UW-Photography (self-studied), videography really is fascinating but somewhat chaotic at times :D. \n\nMy main goal is to improve my skills while Freediving and Snorkeling with ambient light, so I can create calm, honest underwater short films for social media and storytelling. \nThis would directly feed into my passion project, mobula. (www.mobulaocean.com)\nIt''s a ocean-travel-brand in its early stage. Me aside local experts guiding small groups to experience the ocean and its inhabitants in a respectful, connecting way by creating space for real encounters. Different skill levels are welcome and it''s mainly on Freediving and Snorkeling.","inspiration_to_apply":"You guys simply create the coolest underwater films out there! Recognizable style, great in storytelling and so catchy! Your videos always make me wanna go to the specific location and makes me dream for the next days!","referral_source":["First at the BOOT 2025"],"questions_or_concerns":"Wojzech and Luca told me you might go to the Azores again this year - I''m highly interested in this specific trip, since I feel a connection to the archipelago and could use the footage for planned trips to the destination in the future. Anyway, if you guys think another trip could be a better fit: let''s talk about it! I''m excited to hear back from you!","anything_else":"I can manage to travel from 1 to 3 weeks, depending on location, workshop, financial aspect and potential learnings (limited, but never out of ideas to make things happen if I really want it ;))"}'::jsonb, '{}', '[]'::jsonb, '2026-02-02T17:58:20+00:00');
INSERT INTO applications (program, status, user_id, answers, tags, admin_notes, submitted_at) VALUES ('filmmaking', 'reviewing', NULL, '{"first_name":"Christian","last_name":"Eschbach","nickname":"Eschi","email":"christian@christian-eschbach-fotografie.de","phone":"+41786760581","age":"45-54","gender":"Male","nationality":"german","country_of_residence":"Germany","languages":"English, German","current_occupation":"head of logistics","physical_fitness":"Need improvement - Limited physical activity or health concerns","health_conditions":"Prefer to discuss privately","diving_types":["Freediving"],"certification_level":"No certification yet","number_of_dives":"51-250","last_dive_date":"22.08.2025","diving_environments":["Tropical Reefs","Mallorca"],"buoyancy_skill":1,"equipment_owned":["a Sony a7siii in a Seafrogshousing","no light"],"filming_equipment":"seafrogs housing, vacuum pump, dome, port for many lenses. many lenses as well","planning_to_invest":"Yes, within the near future","years_experience":"Less than 1 year","skill_camera_settings":9,"skill_lighting":1,"skill_post_production":7,"skill_color_correction":6,"skill_storytelling":7,"skill_drone":1,"skill_over_water":7,"content_created":["Social media content","People Photography and filming. Never landscapes or wildlife only"],"btm_category":"INDEPENDENT CREATOR (Experienced hobbyist/influencer seeking improvement)","involvement_level":"just for me, because i hate \"jobs\". i just do what i like.","online_presence":"Active social media, Client base","online_links":"bio.site/christianeschbachfotografie","income_from_filming":"No, that''s not my goal.","primary_goal":"Improve content creation for social media","secondary_goal":"Document marine conservation/research","learning_aspects":["Lighting techniques","Marine life behavior understanding","Storytelling and content planning","Post-production and editing","Conservation documentation"],"content_to_create":["Social media content","Documentary style films","Conservation stories"],"learning_approach":["Mixed approach (combination of group and individual)","Project-based learning (within a BTM project)"],"marine_subjects":["Big marine life (sharks, whales, etc.)","showing people. models or bts of a project"],"time_availability":"1 week to 10 days for a workshop, a project or individual training","travel_willingness":"Yes, willing to travel internationally","budget":"Moderate budget (1,000 - 3,000 €/USD)","start_timeline":"Within next 6 months","ultimate_vision":"I love shooting underwater, whether it''s video or photos. I want to do it more and more professionally, ideally as a commission or to document a project and help move things forward.","inspiration_to_apply":"i like your style. I love your visual language, the storytelling.","referral_source":["Social Media (Instagram, Facebook, etc.)"],"anything_else":"I once weighed 198 kilograms and had surgery. I''m still a bit overweight, but I love learning new things and I love the water. I''m rediscovering myself and enjoy achieving new, previously unattainable goals."}'::jsonb, '{}', '[]'::jsonb, '2026-02-02T16:15:51+00:00');
INSERT INTO applications (program, status, user_id, answers, tags, admin_notes, submitted_at) VALUES ('filmmaking', 'reviewing', NULL, '{"first_name":"Kolin","last_name":"Hansen","email":"gettingsaltydiving@gmail.com","phone":"+16047611985","age":"35-44","gender":"Male","nationality":"Canadian","country_of_residence":"Canada","languages":"English","current_occupation":"3D Lighting Artist for Animation & Film","physical_fitness":"Good - Moderately active, no major health concerns","health_conditions":"No health conditions affecting diving","diving_types":["Recreational Scuba diving","Technical Scuba diving"],"certification_level":"Technical Diving certification","number_of_dives":"250+","last_dive_date":"31.01.2026","diving_environments":["Tropical Reefs","Cold water","Deep diving","Night diving"],"buoyancy_skill":9,"equipment_owned":["DSLR/Mirrorless with housing","Lighting equipment"],"filming_equipment":"Sony a7IV, 20mm F 1.8 G, 90mm Macro f2.8, 50mm Macro f2.8, 35mm f1.4 GM, Kraken Abyss 20,000, DJI Mavic 3 Classic, Insta 360 X5","planning_to_invest":"Yes, within the near future","years_experience":"3-5 years","skill_camera_settings":7,"skill_lighting":8,"skill_post_production":8,"skill_color_correction":9,"skill_storytelling":7,"skill_drone":7,"skill_over_water":6,"content_created":["Personal vacation videos","Social media content","Scientific/Research documentation"],"btm_category":"INDEPENDENT CREATOR (Experienced hobbyist/influencer seeking improvement)","involvement_level":"Part-time professional","online_presence":"Active social media, Personal website","online_links":"https://www.instagram.com/getting_salty_/ , https://www.youtube.com/channel/UC2MKeGOlQjRJgpK5EoimVQw , https://www.gettingsalty.ca/","income_from_filming":"No, not yet.","primary_goal":"Transform hobby into professional career","secondary_goal":"Document marine conservation/research","learning_aspects":["Marine life behavior understanding","Storytelling and content planning"],"content_to_create":["Documentary style films","Commercial/advertising content","Scientific/research documentation","Conservation stories"],"learning_approach":["Mixed approach (combination of group and individual)","Project-based learning (within a BTM project)"],"marine_subjects":["Coral reefs","Big marine life (sharks, whales, etc.)","Macro subjects","Marine behavior","Conservation stories"],"time_availability":"2-3 entire weeks at a time for a workshop, aproject or individual training","travel_willingness":"Yes, willing to travel internationally","budget":"Moderate budget (1,000 - 3,000 €/USD)","start_timeline":"Within next 3 months","ultimate_vision":"My vision for underwater filming is to create immersive, emotionally driven films that connect people with the ocean. I’m especially drawn to the weird and wonderful side of the underwater world and the creatures, behaviors, and moments that spark curiosity. Through cinematic storytelling, I hope to inspire deeper respect and care for life beneath the surface and help shift how people see and value the ocean.","inspiration_to_apply":"I was drawn to underwater filming because it offers constant discovery and a completely different way of seeing the world. Being underwater slows everything down and makes you notice details you’d normally miss, which I find incredibly compelling to film.\n\nI chose BTM Academy because Behind the Mask has been part of my journey from the very beginning. I originally learned how to shoot underwater through BTM''s YouTube tutorials and have followed their work for years. I’ve followed BTM’s film making for years, and getting to learn directly from the team that influenced how I started feels like a natural progression.","referral_source":["Social Media (Instagram, Facebook, etc.)"]}'::jsonb, '{}', '[]'::jsonb, '2026-02-02T16:14:09+00:00');
INSERT INTO applications (program, status, user_id, answers, tags, admin_notes, submitted_at) VALUES ('filmmaking', 'reviewing', NULL, '{"first_name":"Juan Camilo","last_name":"Mora","nickname":"Juan","email":"Jcmoraphotography@gmail.com","phone":"+57 315 8277133","age":"25-34","gender":"Male","nationality":"Colombia","country_of_residence":"Colombia","languages":"English, Spanish","current_occupation":"Photographer, expedition leader","physical_fitness":"Excellent - Regular exercise, no health concerns","health_conditions":"No health conditions affecting diving","diving_types":["Recreational Scuba diving","Freediving","Snorkeling"],"certification_level":"Instructor, Certified Freediver, please specify level below:, Molchanovs wave 2","number_of_dives":"250+","last_dive_date":"20.01.2026","diving_environments":["Tropical Reefs","Night diving"],"buoyancy_skill":10,"equipment_owned":["DSLR/Mirrorless with housing"],"filming_equipment":"I began with photography and slowly trying video . Currently working and developing a short film project in Colombia , been documenting whale shakes feeding on sardines for the past 2 years during the season of whaleshark in Colombia pacific coast .\nI feel I don''t know much about video and would love to learn so much more","planning_to_invest":"No immediate plans","years_experience":"1-3 years","skill_camera_settings":7,"skill_lighting":4,"skill_post_production":4,"skill_color_correction":4,"skill_storytelling":4,"skill_drone":6,"skill_over_water":6,"content_created":["Social media content","Documentary style","Scientific/Research documentation"],"btm_category":"OCEAN STEWARD (NGO/scientific focus, conservation-driven)","involvement_level":"Part-time professional","online_presence":"Active social media","online_links":"https://www.instagram.com/jcmoraphotography?igsh=NGtqZTV6bzM1OXFt","income_from_filming":"No, not yet.","primary_goal":"Document marine conservation/research","secondary_goal":"Enhance existing professional skills","learning_aspects":["Camera settings and techniques","Lighting techniques","Storytelling and content planning","Post-production and editing","Business aspects of underwater filming","Client relations and project management","Conservation documentation"],"content_to_create":["Documentary style films","Scientific/research documentation","Conservation stories"],"learning_approach":["Mixed approach (combination of group and individual)","To be honest all of them sound great"],"marine_subjects":["Coral reefs","Big marine life (sharks, whales, etc.)","Macro subjects","Marine behavior","Conservation stories","Hahaha all of them","all have stories to tell"],"time_availability":"2-3 entire weeks at a time for a workshop, aproject or individual training","travel_willingness":"Yes, willing to travel internationally","budget":"Moderate budget (1,000 - 3,000 €/USD)","start_timeline":"Flexible/Not sure yet","ultimate_vision":"Wow, the ocean has given me so much. Nature has given me so much. And since university as a Biologist I found such a powerful tool in my camera. I saw a way of speaking for those who can''t , and a bridge between nature and people , a way to connect people with nature, and that''s my goal . Show people what''s out there and raise awareness . That I feel is my goal , my purpose . I learned that some stories need more than one frame , they need that context, the time , the movement that flim provides. And I want to learn , I want to be able to keep using my camera , to reel this stories","inspiration_to_apply":"Met Peter a few years ago in Revilla as I was his guide there. Met Flo a couple of yeas ago while on trips with Latitude Encounters in Baja . And this team is simply amazing . I love your energy , your passion and the work you do is really inspiring . I want to learn from the best and you guys are some of biggest reference in UW film.","referral_source":["Social Media (Instagram, Facebook, etc.)"],"questions_or_concerns":"Guys, money is sometimes my biggest concern.Are there any grants or scholarships ... Event though believe me I want to put all my effort on doing this. So really been saving and working hard to be able to join and learn from you guys.","anything_else":"When do we start? Hahaha just kidding... Or not! Hahaha can''t wait !!! Can''t wait to learn and somehow someday be a part of this incredible team"}'::jsonb, '{}', '[]'::jsonb, '2026-02-02T13:43:24+00:00');
