s (within a group of approx. 10 persons)","Small group workshop (within a group of approx. 4 persons)","Mixed approach (combination of group and individual)"],"marine_subjects":["Big marine life (sharks, whales, etc.)","Marine behavior","Conservation stories"],"time_availability":"1 week to 10 days for a workshop, a project or individual training","travel_willingness":"Depends on duration and location","budget":"Small budget (under 1,000 €/USD)","start_timeline":"Flexible/Not sure yet","ultimate_vision":"Make videos to show my students in the classroom.","inspiration_to_apply":"To make better videos and pictures to show my students","referral_source":["Social Media (Instagram, Facebook, etc.)"]}'::jsonb, '{}', '[]'::jsonb, '2026-02-01T16:56:20+00:00');
INSERT INTO applications (program, status, user_id, answers, tags, admin_notes, submitted_at) VALUES ('filmmaking', 'reviewing', NULL, '{"first_name":"Laura","last_name":"Juanmarti","nickname":"Lau","email":"Laurajuanmarti@gmail.com","phone":"647113079","age":"35-44","gender":"Female","nationality":"Spanish","country_of_residence":"Spain","languages":"English, Spanish, Catalan","current_occupation":"Freediving instructor + underwater photographer","physical_fitness":"Excellent - Regular exercise, no health concerns","health_conditions":"No health conditions affecting diving","diving_types":["Recreational Scuba diving","Freediving","Snorkeling"],"certification_level":"Open Water, Advanced Open Water","number_of_dives":"51-250","last_dive_date":"29.01.2026","diving_environments":["Tropical Reefs","Deep diving","Night diving","Cave/Wreck diving"],"buoyancy_skill":10,"equipment_owned":["DSLR/Mirrorless with housing"],"filming_equipment":"Sony a 7IV , lens FE 16-35 F2.8, Lens FE 50 F 2.8, seafrogs underwater housing + flat port + 8” dome","planning_to_invest":"No immediate plans","years_experience":"1-3 years","skill_camera_settings":7,"skill_lighting":6,"skill_post_production":8,"skill_color_correction":8,"skill_storytelling":7,"skill_drone":5,"skill_over_water":6,"content_created":["Personal vacation videos","Social media content","Documentary style","Commercial work"],"btm_category":"ASPIRING PROFESSIONAL (Part-time professional aiming for full-time career)","involvement_level":"Part-time professional","online_presence":"Active social media, Personal website, Professional portfolio","online_links":"Web: https://www.thewatercyclexperience.com/foto\nIg: @thewatercyclexperience","income_from_filming":"Regular part-time income","primary_goal":"Transform hobby into professional career","secondary_goal":"Document marine conservation/research","learning_aspects":["Basic equipment setup and operation","Camera settings and techniques","Lighting techniques","Marine life behavior understanding","Storytelling and content planning","Post-production and editing","Business aspects of underwater filming","Client relations and project management","Conservation documentation"],"content_to_create":["Documentary style films","Commercial/advertising content","Conservation stories"],"learning_approach":["Mixed approach (combination of group and individual)","Project-based learning (within a BTM project)"],"marine_subjects":["Coral reefs","Big marine life (sharks, whales, etc.)","Conservation stories"],"time_availability":"2-3 entire weeks at a time for a workshop, aproject or individual training","travel_willingness":"Yes, willing to travel internationally","budget":"Advanced budget (3,000 - 6,000 €/USD)","start_timeline":"Flexible/Not sure yet","ultimate_vision":"My ultimate vision is to use underwater filmmaking as a powerful storytelling tool to connect people emotionally with the ocean. Coming from a freediving background, I’m especially drawn to capturing intimate, calm and human-centered underwater moments — where movement, breath, and light play a central role.\n\nIn the long term, I aim to create meaningful visual stories that combine freediving, travel and conservation, whether through documentaries, brand collaborations, or artistic projects. I want my work to inspire respect for the ocean and a deeper awareness of our relationship with it, while continuing to grow both creatively and technically as an underwater filmmaker.","inspiration_to_apply":"I have always been inspired by the ocean and by the way underwater images can communicate emotions that words often can’t. As a freediving instructor, the underwater world is already a big part of my life, and filmmaking or even modeling feels like a natural next step to express and share those experiences.\nI chose BTM Academy because of its strong focus on storytelling, professionalism, and real-world underwater filmmaking skills. The academy’s approach, mentors, and values resonate deeply with my own goals — not just learning how to film underwater, but how to tell meaningful stories responsibly and creatively.","referral_source":["Social Media (Instagram, Facebook, etc.)"],"questions_or_concerns":"I actually applied last year and was selected for the trip, but unfortunately I wasn’t able to attend because I received the confirmation at the same time I had already committed to a professional assignment. It was genuinely disappointing for me not to be able to join, especially knowing the incredible group of mentors involved, many of whom I truly admire.\n\nAs I’m currently prioritizing my underwater photography and filmmaking work, my main concern is around scheduling. I’d love to know whether there will be more than one course date available, and if dates are announced with enough advance notice, as I already have some work commitments confirmed throughout the year. I would truly love the opportunity to be able to take part this year if scheduling allows.","anything_else":"I’m very motivated to continue developing my skills in underwater filmmaking and photography, and I’m fully committed to approaching this training with professionalism, curiosity, and respect for the ocean."}'::jsonb, '{}', '[]'::jsonb, '2026-02-01T07:04:14+00:00');
