nt_to_create":["Personal/travel memories","Social media content","Conservation stories"],"learning_approach":["Small group workshop (within a group of approx. 4 persons)","One-on-one mentorship","Mixed approach (combination of group and individual)"],"marine_subjects":["Big marine life (sharks, whales, etc.)","Conservation stories"],"time_availability":"1 week to 10 days for a workshop, a project or individual training","travel_willingness":"Yes, willing to travel internationally","start_timeline":"Ready to start immediately","ultimate_vision":"Always love to capture the marine lives and share it to people, tell them how beautiful our ocean is","inspiration_to_apply":"Incredible chance to learn from the best","referral_source":["Social Media (Instagram, Facebook, etc.)"],"last_name":"Chong"}'::jsonb, '{}', '[]'::jsonb, '2025-07-29T11:32:39+00:00');
INSERT INTO applications (program, status, user_id, answers, tags, admin_notes, submitted_at) VALUES ('filmmaking', 'reviewing', NULL, '{"first_name":"Mac","nickname":"Mac, Cheese, Phil, Whatever else you can come up with to be honest","email":"macglen7@icloud.com","online_links":"https://www.instagram.com/macglen1/","age":"18-24","budget":"Moderate budget (1,000 - 3,000 €/USD)","phone":"+27636853106","gender":"Male","nationality":"South African","country_of_residence":"South Africa","languages":"English, Afrikaans","current_occupation":"Deckhand/Dive Master","physical_fitness":"Excellent - Regular exercise, no health concerns","health_conditions":"No health conditions affecting diving","diving_types":["Recreational Scuba diving","Freediving","Snorkeling"],"certification_level":"Divemaster","number_of_dives":"51-250","last_dive_date":"16.07.2025","diving_environments":["Tropical Reefs","Deep diving","Night diving","Cave/Wreck diving"],"buoyancy_skill":10,"equipment_owned":["Action camera (GoPro, Osmo, Insta360, etc)","Currently in the process lf purchasing a Mirrorless camera and housing"],"filming_equipment":"I have access to a large amount of equipment onboard the yacht I work on, from trays, arms, flashes and lights, GoPros, Insta 360s, Olympus cameras, lenses, filters, etc.","planning_to_invest":"Yes, within the near future","years_experience":"Less than 1 year","skill_camera_settings":6,"skill_lighting":4,"skill_post_production":7,"skill_color_correction":7,"skill_storytelling":5,"skill_drone":6,"skill_over_water":5,"content_created":["Personal vacation videos","Social media content"],"btm_category":"BEGINNER - Creative Explorer (Just starting, hobby-focused, seeking basic skills)","involvement_level":"Both Hobby and Conservation/Scientific Work","online_presence":"Active social media","income_from_filming":"No, not yet.","primary_goal":"Learn basics of underwater filming as a hobby","secondary_goal":"Transform hobby into professional career","learning_aspects":["Basic equipment setup and operation","Camera settings and techniques","Lighting techniques","Storytelling and content planning","Post-production and editing"],"content_to_create":["Documentary style films","Conservation stories"],"learning_approach":["One-on-one mentorship","Mixed approach (combination of group and individual)","Project-based learning (within a BTM project)"],"marine_subjects":["Coral reefs","Big marine life (sharks, whales, etc.)"],"time_availability":"now and then for online classes","travel_willingness":"Depends on duration and location","start_timeline":"Ready to start immediately","ultimate_vision":"I work onboard a Private Superyacht which has been pairing with different research groups and non-profits doing research on varying underwater environments underwater. Being the onboard DiveMaster and soon to be Instructor I am exposed to all of this work and it amazes me. \n\nBeing in this position I want to be able to not only record all of it, but share it in a way that people would be interested in it. On one hand this will boost my career and on the other it will share the amazing work that our partners are doing.","inspiration_to_apply":"BTM, along with one or two other channels, is the reason that I even began diving in the first place and has in turn put me where I am in life. I first saw the academy posted on the instagram and instantly knew that I wanted to be apart of it!","referral_source":["Social Media (Instagram, Facebook, etc.)"],"anything_else":"There is tons I''d love to share bit I will save it for any future communication!","last_name":"Glen"}'::jsonb, '{}', '[]'::jsonb, '2025-07-15T23:31:44+00:00');
INSERT INTO applications (program, status, user_id, answers, tags, admin_notes, submitted_at) VALUES ('filmmaking', 'reviewing', NULL, '{"first_name":"Ana Isabel","nickname":"Zuga","email":"besugo.a@gmail.com","online_links":"@zugabesuga, @ana_besugo_photography, www.zugadventures.com","age":"35-44","budget":"Small budget (under 1,000 €/USD)","phone":"912227323","gender":"Female","nationality":"Portuguese","country_of_residence":"Portugal","languages":"English, Spanish","current_occupation":"Marine biologist, dive guide freelancer and CEO of a ecoturism company, ZUGADVENTURES.","physical_fitness":"Excellent - Regular exercise, no health concerns","health_conditions":"No health conditions affecting diving","diving_types":["Recreational Scuba diving","Snorkeling"],"certification_level":"Divemaster","number_of_dives":"250+","last_dive_date":"31.01.2025","diving_environments":["Tropical Reefs","Cold water","Deep diving","Night diving","Cave/Wreck diving"],"buoyancy_skill":9,"equipment_owned":["Action camera (GoPro, Osmo, Insta360, etc)","Compact camera with housing"],"filming_equipment":"GoPro Hero 11 with housing; Canon G16 with housing FantaSea and flash Sea&Sea, Divevolk for Iphone 13, with light","planning_to_invest":"No immediate plans","years_experience":"5+ years","skill_camera_settings":6,"skill_lighting":5,"skill_post_production":6,"skill_color_correction":5,"skill_storytelling":7,"skill_drone":5,"skill_over_water":5,"content_created":["Personal vacation videos","Social media content","Scientific/Research documentation"],"btm_category":"INDEPENDENT CREATOR (Experienced hobbyist/influencer seeking improvement)","involvement_level":"Hobby only","online_presence":"Active social media, Personal website","income_from_filming":"Occasionally (few projects per year)","primary_goal":"Transform hobby into professional career","secondary_goal":"Improve content creation for social media","learning_aspects":["Basic equipment setup and operation","Camera settings and techniques","Lighting techniques","Marine life behavior understanding","Storytelling and content planning","Post-production and editing","Business aspects of underwater filming","Client relations and project management","Conservation documentation"],"content_to_create":["Social media content","Documentary style films","Scientific/research documentation","Conservation stories"],"learning_approach":["Small group workshop (within a group of approx. 4 persons)","Mixed approach (combination of group and individual)"],"marine_subjects":["Coral reefs","Big marine life (sharks, whales, etc.)","Macro subjects","Marine behavior","Conservation stories"],"time_availability":"1 week to 10 days for a workshop, a project or individual training","travel_willingness":"Depends on duration and location","start_timeline":"Flexible/Not sure yet","ultimate_vision":"Photography entered my life from a very early age, I think I was about 8 years old, a strong influence from my father. I have always been known among my friends as the paparazzi. :) In 2006 I took a diving course, a year after entering the University of Algarve in marine biology, and my vision of the underwater world and wildlife took on other shapes and colors, those of the seabed. With the Adavance Open Water Diver I immediately and without thinking, took up photography and video without mastering any underwater technique. As soon as I had the opportunity, I started investing money in cameras. I have been taking amateur underwater photographs since 2007/2008. But my biggest dream is to be part of something like the Behind the Mask family and make a living from photography and video.","inspiration_to_apply":"I''m a huge fan of your content and I''ve been following you since 2015 when one day I saw a video of yours on Facebook or Instagram and then I subscribed to your YouTube channel and since then I''ve been a huge follower. I love your videos and my biggest dream would be to be part of Behind the Mask, as a marine biologist and experienced diver (with more than 2000 dives) in several different countries and environments. I love any form of wildlife and I am fascinated by capturing every detail and sharing it with the world, with those who are interested and who find this type of content meaningful. You have been my inspiration for several years, and the fact that I have already worked with you a little here in the Azores makes me deeply grateful.","referral_source":["Social Media (Instagram, Facebook, etc.)"],"questions_or_concerns":"One of my biggest concerns is perhaps not being 100% fluent in English and having some difficulty understanding the content at first.  And then the other concern is that I don''t have financial stability and despite having a huge desire to have this training with the academy, I may not be able to due to financial issues. I am now starting an ecotourism project and the beginning is always challenging and a little uncertain.","anything_else":"If there were a scholarship that we could apply for and have the chance to have this training for free, it would be extraordinary. Of course, with future goals of \"paying\" for this opportunity with the knowledge acquired.","last_name":"Canelas Pinto Besugo"}'::jsonb, '{}', '[]'::jsonb, '2025-04-21T12:06:31+00:00');
INSERT INTO applications (program, status, user_id, answers, tags, admin_notes, submitted_at) VALUES ('filmmaking', 'reviewing', NULL, '{"first_name":"Natalie Lynn Lichtenbert","nickname":"Nat","email":"natalielynn.lichtenbert@gmail.com","online_links":"Instagram: @naturewithnatalielynn, Youtube: https://www.youtube.com/@GreenDolphinProject, Website: www.greendolphinproject.org","age":"45-54","budget":"All-In budget (>12,000 €/USD)","phone":"847-340-9994","gender":"Female","nationality":"Caucasian","country_of_residence":"United States","languages":"English, Spanish","current_occupation":"Sustainability","physical_fitness":"Excellent - Regular exercise, no health concerns","health_conditions":"No health conditions affecting diving","diving_types":["Recreational Scuba diving","Freediving"],"certification_level":"Rescue Diver, Certified Freediver","number_of_dives":"51-250","last_dive_date":"28.02.2025","diving_environments":["Tropical Reefs","Cold water","Deep diving","Night diving","Cenote"],"buoyancy_skill":7,"equipment_owned":["Action camera (GoPro, Osmo, Insta360, etc)","Compact camera with housing","DSLR/Mirrorless with housing"],"filming_equipment":"GoPro, Olympus TG-6, Panasonic GH-5","planning_to_invest":"Yes, within the near future","years_experience":"3-5 years","skill_camera_settings":2,"skill_lighting":2,"skill_post_production":4,"skill_color_correction":2,"skill_storytelling":1,"skill_drone":1,"skill_over_water":7,"content_created":["Personal vacation videos","Social media content","Documentary style"],"btm_category":"OCEAN STEWARD (NGO/scientific focus, conservation-driven)","involvement_level":"Would like to be professional","online_presence":"Active social media","income_from_filming":"No, not yet.","primary_goal":"Improve content creation for social media","secondary_goal":"Document marine conservation/research","learning_aspects":["Basic equipment setup and operation","Camera settings and techniques","Lighting techniques","Marine life behavior understanding","Storytelling and content planning","Post-production and editing","Business aspects of underwater filming","Client relations and project management","Conservation documentation"],"content_to_create":["Social media content","Documentary style films","Scientific/research documentation","Conservation stories"],"learning_approach":["Mixed approach (combination of group and individual)"],"marine_subjects":["Coral reefs","Big marine life (sharks, whales, etc.)","Macro subjects","Marine behavior","Conservation stories"],"time_availability":"1 week to 10 days for a workshop, a project or individual training","travel_willingness":"Yes, willing to travel internationally","start_timeline":"Within next 3 months","ultimate_vision":"Dreams and Aspirations: Beautiful storytelling that engages both nature and non-nature loving individuals while sharing the stories of the marine water life.  I want my viewers to experience a deep emotional connection to the creatures that they see, both big and small.  I would love to present the marine life from \"their\" perspective, want to make the storytelling from the animals'' POV.  Incorporating both conservation and research as well to deepen the story with real depth.  Would I love to do this work full time, absolutely!","inspiration_to_apply":"Given the fact that there is little out there in terms of training material, I have been reaching out everywhere to learn on my own.  When I saw your \"Diving Antarctica\" video clip on YouTube, it was mind blowing to me, the way that it was sequenced to music, the storytelling aspect that you could follow throughout, the way the music really set the tone of the experience, I just cannot say enough.","referral_source":["Social Media (Instagram, Facebook, etc.)"],"questions_or_concerns":"Don''t have any at the moment.","anything_else":"I have a non-profit, Green Dolphin Project Global (link provided above) which is now reaching an international level in the 2.5 years that we have been \"live\".  I can really leverage this to have great impact on wildlife conservation and it is my life''s mission."}'::jsonb, '{}', '[]'::jsonb, '2025-04-01T19:41:03+00:00');
INSERT INTO applications (program, status, user_id, answers, tags, admin_notes, submitted_at) VALUES ('filmmaking', 'reviewing', NULL, '{"first_name":"Daniel Kainz","email":"dka@danielmkainz.com","online_links":"danielmkainz.com","age":"25-34","budget":"Advanced budget (3,000 - 6,000 €/USD)","phone":"+43676845834500","gender":"Male","nationality":"Austria","country_of_residence":"Austria","languages":"English, German","current_occupation":"Freelance Focus Puller","physical_fitness":"Excellent - Regular exercise, no health concerns","health_conditions":"No health conditions affecting diving","diving_types":["Recreational Scuba diving","Freediving","Snorkeling"],"certification_level":"Advanced Open Water","number_of_dives":"51-250","last_dive_date":"05.06.2024","diving_environments":["Tropical Reefs","Cold water","Deep diving","Night diving","Cave/Wreck diving"],"buoyancy_skill":9,"equipment_owned":["Action camera (GoPro, Osmo, Insta360, etc)","DSLR/Mirrorless with housing","Lighting equipment"],"filming_equipment":"Nikon Z8 with Nautical Housing, 2x Keldan 8XR Ambient, 7\" Monitor, self made trim rails","planning_to_invest":"Yes, within the near future","years_experience":"1-3 years","skill_camera_settings":9,"skill_lighting":7,"skill_post_production":7,"skill_color_correction":7,"skill_storytelling":6,"skill_drone":7,"skill_over_water":9,"content_created":["Social media content","Commercial work"],"btm_category":"ASPIRING PROFESSIONAL (Part-time professional aiming for full-time career)","involvement_level":"Part-time professional","online_presence":"Active social media, Personal website","income_from_filming":"Occasionally (few projects per year)","primary_goal":"Transform hobby into professional career","secondary_goal":"Document marine conservation/research","learning_aspects":["Lighting techniques","Marine life behavior understanding","Storytelling and content planning","Post-production and editing","Business aspects of underwater filming","Conservation documentation"],"content_to_create":["Social media content","Documentary style films","Scientific/research documentation","Conservation stories"],"learning_approach":["Small group workshop (within a group of approx. 4 persons)","One-on-one mentorship","Mixed approach (combination of group and individual)","Project-based learning (within a BTM project)"],"marine_subjects":["Big marine life (sharks, whales, etc.)","Marine behavior","Conservation stories"],"time_availability":"2-3 entire weeks at a time for a workshop, aproject or individual training","travel_willingness":"Yes, willing to travel internationally","start_timeline":"Within next 6 months","ultimate_vision":"Actually my dream is to shoot underwater documentaries for big television studios. I want to show people the beauty of our lakes and oceans and we have to protect it, while I travel the world to see these wonders with my own eyes. Due to my background in film and television I would also like to be responsible for the underwater shots of a feature film. In Austria there is just one underwater DP and I am trying to give him some competition ;) I did some shots for commercials, short films and one tv feature film last year. I think the mixture between those two would be great. One for the money and one for the passion!","inspiration_to_apply":"That''s quite easy: You are living my dream. I want to travel, dive and shoot underwater and if I can earn money with it, even better!","referral_source":["Social Media (Instagram, Facebook, etc.)"]}'::jsonb, '{}', '[]'::jsonb, '2025-04-01T18:44:36+00:00');
INSERT INTO applications (program, status, user_id, answers, tags, admin_notes, submitted_at) VALUES ('filmmaking', 'reviewing', NULL, '{"first_name":"Jinu Braz de Araújo","nickname":"Jinu","email":"brazjinu07@gmail.com","online_links":"https://www.facebook.com/profile.php?id=100091262782317&mibextid=ZbWKwL","age":"25-34","budget":"Very limited budget. I basically have no financial means to be spent on this.","phone":"+670 74294909","gender":"Male","nationality":"Timor-Leste","country_of_residence":"Timor-Leste","languages":"English","current_occupation":"Marine Science student, Scuba Diving","physical_fitness":"Excellent - Regular exercise, no health concerns","health_conditions":"No health conditions affecting diving","diving_types":["Recreational Scuba diving","Snorkeling"],"certification_level":"Rescue Diver","number_of_dives":"51-250","last_dive_date":"11.11.2024","diving_environments":["Tropical Reefs","Deep diving","Night diving","Cave/Wreck diving"],"buoyancy_skill":8,"equipment_owned":["Action camera (GoPro, Osmo, Insta360, etc)"],"filming_equipment":"Go pro hero 12","planning_to_invest":"Yes, within the near future","years_experience":"Less than 1 year","skill_camera_settings":6,"skill_lighting":5,"skill_post_production":5,"skill_color_correction":5,"skill_storytelling":5,"skill_drone":7,"skill_over_water":5,"content_created":["Personal vacation videos","Social media content"],"btm_category":"BEGINNER - Creative Explorer (Just starting, hobby-focused, seeking basic skills)","involvement_level":"Complete beginner","online_presence":"Active social media","income_from_filming":"No, not yet.","primary_goal":"Transform hobby into professional career","secondary_goal":"Document marine conservation/research","learning_aspects":["Basic equipment setup and operation","Camera settings and techniques","Lighting techniques","Marine life behavior understanding","Storytelling and content planning","Post-production and editing","Business aspects of underwater filming","Client relations and project management","Conservation documentation"],"content_to_create":["Personal/travel memories","Social media content","Documentary style films","Scientific/research documentation","Conservation stories"],"learning_approach":["Group workshops (within a group of approx. 10 persons)","Small group workshop (within a group of approx. 4 persons)","Project-based learning (within a BTM project)"],"marine_subjects":["Coral reefs","Big marine life (sharks, whales, etc.)","Macro subjects","Marine behavior","Conservation stories"],"time_availability":"2-3 entire weeks at a time for a workshop, aproject or individual training","travel_willingness":"Depends on duration and location","start_timeline":"Within next 3 months","ultimate_vision":"Unfortunately I am certified as Rescue Diver under the Scuba Diving International (SDI) and I have a big passion in marine biodiversity conservation such as sea turtle, Whales and coral reef. I want to visualize the beauty of underwater to the world through the footage that I have taken to advocate in our personal page as a digital marketing to attract more people to visit our country moreover my goal is to become a professional videograher, marine storytelling and editing as well in the future.","inspiration_to_apply":"I am the one that a big fans o BTM I have watched BTM reels or video on YouTube or Instagram twice a day with a great storytelling and best editing ever that I have seen before, with a great editing I fall in love with BTM, as my background in marine science and certified as a diver BTM is really inspiring me like a role model for me the, the new video that BTM dropped out our the beauty of marine life and marine animal it''s make me really into it. Hope that through this course will transform me hobby into a professional career.","referral_source":["Social Media (Instagram, Facebook, etc.)"],"questions_or_concerns":"BTM is the best ever.","anything_else":"I want to learn more  the techniques how to hold and carry underwater camera, set up the equipment, editing and colour grade and storytelling."}'::jsonb, '{}', '[]'::jsonb, '2025-04-01T15:18:37+00:00');
