memories","Social media content","Documentary style films","Commercial/advertising content","Scientific/research documentation","Conservation stories"],"learning_approach":["One-on-one mentorship"],"marine_subjects":["Coral reefs","Big marine life (sharks, whales, etc.)","Marine behavior","Conservation stories"],"time_availability":"2-3 entire weeks at a time for a workshop, aproject or individual training","travel_willingness":"Yes, willing to travel internationally","start_timeline":"Ready to start immediately","ultimate_vision":"I want to know and see them all","inspiration_to_apply":"Your works","referral_source":["Social Media (Instagram, Facebook, etc.)"],"questions_or_concerns":"I have a lot of plan to go diving this year but I mostly have free times when I’m at home","anything_else":"I want to see the world and share it to others people like you I want to inspire them what beautiful world that we live in"}'::jsonb, '{}', '[]'::jsonb, '2025-03-30T12:55:29+00:00');
INSERT INTO applications (program, status, user_id, answers, tags, admin_notes, submitted_at) VALUES ('filmmaking', 'reviewing', NULL, '{"first_name":"Juan Carlos Bonilla Escotto","nickname":"Juan Bonilla","email":"juancarlosbonilla.e@gmail.com","online_links":"https://youtu.be/WYLSvH16DCk?si=fOBwtGNwjom4WPoA;  https://www.youtube.com/@OceanBlueTree","age":"35-44","budget":"Advanced budget (3,000 - 6,000 €/USD)","phone":"5529712673","gender":"Male","nationality":"mexican","country_of_residence":"mexico","languages":"English, Spanish","current_occupation":"Filmaker","physical_fitness":"Excellent - Regular exercise, no health concerns","health_conditions":"No health conditions affecting diving","diving_types":["Technical Scuba diving","Freediving","Snorkeling"],"certification_level":"Instructor","number_of_dives":"250+","last_dive_date":"25.03.2025","diving_environments":["Tropical Reefs","Cold water","Deep diving","Night diving","Cave/Wreck diving"],"buoyancy_skill":10,"equipment_owned":["Action camera (GoPro, Osmo, Insta360, etc)","DSLR/Mirrorless with housing","Professional video camera","Lighting equipment"],"filming_equipment":"Red VRaptor (nauticam housing), Canon R5C (nauticam housing), Keldan lights,","planning_to_invest":"Yes, within the near future","years_experience":"5+ years","skill_camera_settings":10,"skill_lighting":10,"skill_post_production":10,"skill_color_correction":10,"skill_storytelling":10,"skill_drone":10,"skill_over_water":10,"content_created":["Social media content","Documentary style","Commercial work","Scientific/Research documentation"],"btm_category":"OCEAN STEWARD (NGO/scientific focus, conservation-driven)","involvement_level":"Full-time professional","online_presence":"Professional portfolio, Client base","income_from_filming":"Full-time income","primary_goal":"Enhance existing professional skills","secondary_goal":"Document marine conservation/research","learning_aspects":["Business aspects of underwater filming","Client relations and project management","Conservation documentation"],"content_to_create":["Documentary style films","Scientific/research documentation","Conservation stories"],"learning_approach":["Project-based learning (within a BTM project)"],"marine_subjects":["Coral reefs","Big marine life (sharks, whales, etc.)","Macro subjects","Marine behavior","Conservation stories"],"time_availability":"2-3 entire weeks at a time for a workshop, aproject or individual training","travel_willingness":"Yes, willing to travel internationally","start_timeline":"Within next 3 months","ultimate_vision":"All my life, I have dreamed of traveling and documenting the depths of the ocean. Like many, I have learned on my own and have faced a profession that, in my country, lacks schools, academies, and specialized courses, in addition to having limited resources. Despite this, I have managed to build a career and make a living from it.\n\nHowever, I am still not where I want to be. Although I have had the opportunity to travel and work with various organizations, I have not yet made the leap to the big leagues or produced full documentaries at the level I aspire to. I feel that my passion is limited by the experience I have been able to build on my own and that I need support to unlock my full potential. I have invested in good equipment and dedicate every day to this profession, but I still haven''t been able to make the most of it.","inspiration_to_apply":"Nowadays, social media exposes us to the work of many people, and in the end, content gets lost among countless others. However, when I see BTM’s content, it stays in my mind; it stands out from the rest and doesn’t fade away. It remains as a true showcase of work and talent.\n\nThat is what I aspire to achieve: to create stories that are free, authentic, and leave a lasting impact. I want to develop the ability to convey solid ideas with rhythm and a unique style, while always surprising, one after another. I am confident that this academy will help me achieve my goals.","referral_source":["Social Media (Instagram, Facebook, etc.)"],"questions_or_concerns":"I would like to know more about the curriculum and what opportunities are available after completing your course. I’m also interested in whether there are any plans to collaborate with students in the future.","anything_else":"If you are looking for someone who is hardworking, relentless, has a growth mindset, and has proven their passion and determination up to this day, believe me, I am here—ready to learn from you and also to contribute."}'::jsonb, '{}', '[]'::jsonb, '2025-03-27T13:44:37+00:00');
INSERT INTO applications (program, status, user_id, answers, tags, admin_notes, submitted_at) VALUES ('filmmaking', 'reviewing', NULL, '{"first_name":"julian hebenstreit","email":"julian@underwaterjulian.com","online_links":"instagram.com/underwaterjulian \nWebsite: underwaterjulian.com\nAustralia Reel (Youtube Link): https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=T48PYR3lbW4&ab_channel=Julian","age":"18-24","budget":"Advanced budget (3,000 - 6,000 €/USD)","phone":"+4917646240283","gender":"Male","nationality":"German","country_of_residence":"Germany","languages":"English, Spanish, German","current_occupation":"Freelance Underwater Media Creator","physical_fitness":"Excellent - Regular exercise, no health concerns","health_conditions":"No health conditions affecting diving","diving_types":["Recreational Scuba diving","Freediving","Snorkeling"],"certification_level":"Divemaster, Certified Freediver","number_of_dives":"51-250","last_dive_date":"30.10.2024","diving_environments":["Tropical Reefs","Cold water","Deep diving","Night diving","Cave/Wreck diving"],"buoyancy_skill":8,"equipment_owned":["DSLR/Mirrorless with housing","Lighting equipment"],"filming_equipment":"sony a6400 + 16-50mm kit, Fantasea FA6400 Housing, 2x Sea&Sea YS-01 Strobes, Wide Angle Domeport","planning_to_invest":"Yes, within the near future","years_experience":"1-3 years","skill_camera_settings":8,"skill_lighting":7,"skill_post_production":9,"skill_color_correction":8,"skill_storytelling":8,"skill_drone":8,"skill_over_water":7,"content_created":["Personal vacation videos","Social media content","Commercial work"],"btm_category":"ASPIRING PROFESSIONAL (Part-time professional aiming for full-time career)","involvement_level":"Part-time professional","online_presence":"Active social media, Professional portfolio","income_from_filming":"Occasionally (few projects per year)","primary_goal":"Transform hobby into professional career","secondary_goal":"Enhance existing professional skills","learning_aspects":["Storytelling and content planning","Post-production and editing","Business aspects of underwater filming","Client relations and project management","Conservation documentation"],"content_to_create":["Social media content","Documentary style films","Commercial/advertising content","Scientific/research documentation","Conservation stories"],"learning_approach":["Mixed approach (combination of group and individual)","Project-based learning (within a BTM project)"],"marine_subjects":["Conservation stories"],"time_availability":"2-3 entire weeks at a time for a workshop, aproject or individual training","travel_willingness":"Depends on duration and location","start_timeline":"Flexible/Not sure yet","ultimate_vision":"I want to create Image films and conservation stories that carry meaning and drive people to protect our oceans. I''d like to be confident behind the scenes of it all, reaching out to clients successfully, planning content and things like that. It''s my dream to become an independent documentarian and story teller for the ocean.","inspiration_to_apply":"When I first saw one of your videos, many years ago, I felt compelled to pursue a journey where I too could one day produce films and videos that convey feelings and emotions the way that video made me feel.","referral_source":["Word of mouth"]}'::jsonb, '{}', '[]'::jsonb, '2025-03-27T09:32:20+00:00');
INSERT INTO applications (program, status, user_id, answers, tags, admin_notes, submitted_at) VALUES ('filmmaking', 'reviewing', NULL, '{"first_name":"Maximilian Scholl","nickname":"老马","email":"max@shinemaxmedia.com","online_links":"www.shinemaxmedia.com ins:schollmaximilian www.max-scholl.de  https://drive.google.com/file/d/1SZPXfJRSAb_9MwqZJr3RfYpVEaG2DRfk/view?usp=sharing","age":"45-54","budget":"Moderate budget (1,000 - 3,000 €/USD)","phone":"+8613602502024","gender":"Male","nationality":"German","country_of_residence":"China","languages":"English, German","current_occupation":"Director / Producer","physical_fitness":"Good - Moderately active, no major health concerns","health_conditions":"No health conditions affecting diving","diving_types":["Recreational Scuba diving"],"certification_level":"Open Water, Advanced Open Water, Rescue Diver","number_of_dives":"51-250","last_dive_date":"10.10.2024","diving_environments":["Tropical Reefs","Night diving"],"buoyancy_skill":6,"equipment_owned":["Action camera (GoPro, Osmo, Insta360, etc)","Compact camera with housing","DSLR/Mirrorless with housing","Lighting equipment"],"filming_equipment":"RX100IV, A7Sii, insta360 ace pro, Meikon/seafrog housing","planning_to_invest":"Yes, within the next years","years_experience":"3-5 years","skill_camera_settings":8,"skill_lighting":5,"skill_post_production":7,"skill_color_correction":6,"skill_storytelling":7,"skill_drone":6,"skill_over_water":8,"content_created":["Personal vacation videos","Social media content","Commercial work"],"btm_category":"ASPIRING PROFESSIONAL (Part-time professional aiming for full-time career)","involvement_level":"Hobby only","online_presence":"Personal website, Professional portfolio","income_from_filming":"No, not yet.","primary_goal":"Enhance existing professional skills","secondary_goal":"Transform hobby into professional career","learning_aspects":["Marine life behavior understanding","Storytelling and content planning","Business aspects of underwater filming","Conservation documentation"],"content_to_create":["Documentary style films","Commercial/advertising content","Scientific/research documentation","Conservation stories"],"learning_approach":["Project-based learning (within a BTM project)"],"marine_subjects":["Coral reefs","Marine behavior","Conservation stories"],"time_availability":"2-3 entire weeks at a time for a workshop, aproject or individual training","travel_willingness":"Yes, willing to travel internationally","start_timeline":"Ready to start immediately","ultimate_vision":"I would like to be part of something bigger, rather than just travel around and shoot myself. I am happy to contribute, learn from professionals and enjoy working in a team. After being in that industry for almost 20 years I am slowly losing the sparkle in my eyes for commercial product videos on land...so I am ready for new challenges and adventures. I am quite well connected in China, so there might also be some business opportunities in the future and I am also familiar with Chinese social media like XiaoHongShu, which might be interesting for you.","inspiration_to_apply":"Being passionate for both filming and diving I have been following your accounts for several years now and I am very impressed by the results of your work.","referral_source":["Word of mouth"],"questions_or_concerns":"I am only interested to join you on trips, not any online courses, even though I think the academy is a great idea in general. Theoretically and technically I do have a very strong background in video production. Projects like the coming one in June in Indonesia seems perfect for me as I believe I can contribute and deliver whatever you expect and in the same time learn something and experience an adventure. Also financially it sounds fair to me, happy to pay my own flights and could also bring some of my basic equipment.","anything_else":"I was actually thinking some years ago already to get in touch as I think it could be a good match and there might be some opportunities for both sides. I did a commercial project for an underwater scooter just a year after I started diving and thought there would be more opportunities here, then unfortunately Covid stopped my plans to get more into underwater shootings."}'::jsonb, '{}', '[]'::jsonb, '2025-03-27T04:49:45+00:00');
INSERT INTO applications (program, status, user_id, answers, tags, admin_notes, submitted_at) VALUES ('filmmaking', 'reviewing', NULL, '{"first_name":"Evan Possley","email":"epossley@gmail.com","online_links":"https://www.instagram.com/evanpossley/, https://www.evanpossley.com","age":"35-44","budget":"Moderate budget (1,000 - 3,000 €/USD)","phone":"+1-616-306-8296","gender":"Male","nationality":"USA","country_of_residence":"USA","languages":"English, Greek","physical_fitness":"Excellent - Regular exercise, no health concerns","health_conditions":"No health conditions affecting diving","diving_types":["Recreational Scuba diving","Freediving","Snorkeling"],"certification_level":"Instructor, Certified Freediver","number_of_dives":"250+","last_dive_date":"15.10.2024","diving_environments":["Tropical Reefs","Cold water","Night diving"],"buoyancy_skill":9,"equipment_owned":["DSLR/Mirrorless with housing","Lighting equipment"],"filming_equipment":"Sony a1, Sony a7s3, Nauticam housing, Kelvin 4X lights, SmallHD monitor with Nauticam Housing","planning_to_invest":"Yes, within the next years","years_experience":"3-5 years","skill_camera_settings":8,"skill_lighting":8,"skill_post_production":8,"skill_color_correction":8,"skill_storytelling":7,"skill_drone":9,"skill_over_water":9,"content_created":["Personal vacation videos","Social media content","Documentary style","Commercial work"],"btm_category":"ASPIRING PROFESSIONAL (Part-time professional aiming for full-time career)","involvement_level":"Part-time professional","online_presence":"Active social media, Personal website, Professional portfolio","income_from_filming":"Occasionally (few projects per year)","primary_goal":"Enhance existing professional skills","secondary_goal":"Document marine conservation/research","learning_aspects":["Lighting techniques","Storytelling and content planning","Business aspects of underwater filming","Client relations and project management"],"content_to_create":["Social media content","Documentary style films","Commercial/advertising content","Conservation stories"],"learning_approach":["Small group workshop (within a group of approx. 4 persons)","One-on-one mentorship","Project-based learning (within a BTM project)"],"marine_subjects":["Coral reefs","Big marine life (sharks, whales, etc.)","Marine behavior","Conservation stories"],"time_availability":"2-3 entire weeks at a time for a workshop, aproject or individual training","travel_willingness":"Yes, willing to travel internationally","start_timeline":"Ready to start immediately","ultimate_vision":"The dream is to make a living and support myself with underwater filmmaking. I would like to get experience diving throughout the world, eventually working on Blue-Chip level productions in the documentary and conservation spaces.","inspiration_to_apply":"I have been a fan of BTM for years. The work is extremely unique, creative, and masterful and has had a huge influence on my own projects. I''ve had some minor success in the underwater photo/video space, but in order to get to the next level I need to make connections in the industry and take guidance the professionals who are making an impact. It is clear to me that this is BTM!","referral_source":["Social Media (Instagram, Facebook, etc.)"]}'::jsonb, '{}', '[]'::jsonb, '2025-03-26T23:05:10+00:00');
INSERT INTO applications (program, status, user_id, answers, tags, admin_notes, submitted_at) VALUES ('filmmaking', 'reviewing', NULL, '{"first_name":"Marcos Alberto Contreras","nickname":"Marks","email":"cmal333@gmail.com","online_links":"Insta: @maalcouw, @maalcodephoto","age":"35-44","budget":"Moderate budget (1,000 - 3,000 €/USD)","phone":"+52 3310386813","gender":"Male","nationality":"Mexican","country_of_residence":"México","languages":"English, Spanish","current_occupation":"Diving instructor","physical_fitness":"Good - Moderately active, no major health concerns","health_conditions":"No health conditions affecting diving","diving_types":["Recreational Scuba diving","Snorkeling"],"certification_level":"Instructor","number_of_dives":"250+","last_dive_date":"25.03.2025","diving_environments":["Tropical Reefs","Deep diving","Night diving","Cave/Wreck diving"],"buoyancy_skill":10,"equipment_owned":["Action camera (GoPro, Osmo, Insta360, etc)","Compact camera with housing"],"filming_equipment":"Gopro 10 & canon G16 with Fantasea Housing + Sea&Sea strobe","planning_to_invest":"Yes, within the near future","years_experience":"1-3 years","skill_camera_settings":9,"skill_lighting":8,"skill_post_production":6,"skill_color_correction":7,"skill_storytelling":6,"skill_drone":1,"skill_over_water":7,"content_created":["Personal vacation videos","Social media content"],"btm_category":"DEDICATED ACHIEVER (Business-focused, seeking intensive mentorship)","involvement_level":"Hobby only","online_presence":"Active social media","income_from_filming":"No, not yet.","primary_goal":"Document marine conservation/research","secondary_goal":"Enhance existing professional skills","learning_aspects":["Lighting techniques","Marine life behavior understanding","Storytelling and content planning","Post-production and editing","Business aspects of underwater filming","Client relations and project management","Conservation documentation"],"content_to_create":["Documentary style films","Scientific/research documentation","Conservation stories"],"learning_approach":["One-on-one mentorship","Mixed approach (combination of group and individual)"],"marine_subjects":["Coral reefs","Big marine life (sharks, whales, etc.)","Macro subjects","Marine behavior","Conservation stories"],"time_availability":"1 week to 10 days for a workshop, a project or individual training","travel_willingness":"Yes, willing to travel internationally","start_timeline":"Within next 6 months","ultimate_vision":"I want to change peoples mind, I want to show the Beauty of the ocean and how fragile and important it is...I feel doing something amazing, breathtaking as you do...would generate a greater impact. On the other hand, the personal satisfaction of doing something I love with all the tools and knowledge I could acquire.","inspiration_to_apply":"Your love for the ocean, your stories, your videos, your talent","referral_source":["Social Media (Instagram, Facebook, etc.)"],"anything_else":"Never stop sharing your beautiful videos and your love for the ocean!"}'::jsonb, '{}', '[]'::jsonb, '2025-03-26T20:24:56+00:00');
INSERT INTO applications (program, status, user_id, answers, tags, admin_notes, submitted_at) VALUES ('filmmaking', 'reviewing', NULL, '{"first_name":"Justin Lutsky","email":"justin@submergeunderwater.com","online_links":"submergeunderwater.com, instagram.com/submergeunderwater/, https://www.instagram.com/jlutskyphoto/, youtube.com/@submergeunderwater","age":"35-44","budget":"Advanced budget (3,000 - 6,000 €/USD)","phone":"714-343-4898","gender":"Male","nationality":"USA","country_of_residence":"USA","languages":"English","current_occupation":"Software Developer, Underwater Portrait Photographer","physical_fitness":"Excellent - Regular exercise, no health concerns","health_conditions":"No health conditions affecting diving","diving_types":["Recreational Scuba diving","Technical Scuba diving","Freediving"],"certification_level":"Open Water, Advanced Open Water, Rescue Diver, Divemaster, Instructor, Technical Diving certification","number_of_dives":"250+","last_dive_date":"01.03.2025","diving_environments":["Tropical Reefs","Cold water","Deep diving","Night diving","Cave/Wreck diving","Film Productions","Public Safety Diving"],"buoyancy_skill":10,"equipment_owned":["Action camera (GoPro, Osmo, Insta360, etc)","Compact camera with housing","DSLR/Mirrorless with housing","Professional video camera","Lighting equipment"],"filming_equipment":"Sony A7Riii, SmallHD monitor, Nauticam housings, inon strobes, big blue video lights","planning_to_invest":"Yes, within the near future","years_experience":"5+ years","skill_camera_settings":9,"skill_lighting":9,"skill_post_production":9,"skill_color_correction":9,"skill_storytelling":9,"skill_drone":7,"skill_over_water":9,"content_created":["Personal vacation videos","Social media content","Documentary style","Commercial work","Scientific/Research documentation"],"btm_category":"DEDICATED ACHIEVER (Business-focused, seeking intensive mentorship)","involvement_level":"Part-time professional","online_presence":"Active social media, Personal website, Professional portfolio, Client base","income_from_filming":"Occasionally (few projects per year)","primary_goal":"Transform hobby into professional career","secondary_goal":"Enhance existing professional skills","learning_aspects":["Storytelling and content planning","Business aspects of underwater filming","Client relations and project management"],"content_to_create":["Documentary style films","Commercial/advertising content"],"learning_approach":["One-on-one mentorship","Project-based learning (within a BTM project)"],"marine_subjects":["Big marine life (sharks, whales, etc.)"],"time_availability":"2-3 entire weeks at a time for a workshop, aproject or individual training","travel_willingness":"Yes, willing to travel internationally","start_timeline":"Within next 3 months","ultimate_vision":"My ultimate vision for our underwater filming journey, with our company ‘Submerge’, is to elevate underwater visuals from a niche specialty to a sought-after, impactful storytelling medium within the commercial landscape. My name is Justin Lutsky, and alongside my creative partner and wife, Abbey Blake, we''ve built a strong foundation in crafting high-end underwater imagery, combining my expertise in underwater photography and filmmaking with her unique talent as an underwater model.\n\nWhile we''ve achieved success with personal clients, our aspiration is to break into larger-scale, high-budget commercial and film projects. We dream of collaborating with brands, businesses and creative storytellers that recognize the power of compelling underwater narratives, producing visuals that not only showcase our technical proficiency but also resonate deeply with a wider audience. We envision Submerge becoming synonymous with breathtaking, impactful underwater storytelling, driving brand engagement and inspiring viewers on a global scale.\n\nMy ultimate goal is to see our work utilized in major advertising campaigns, film productions, impactful documentaries, and innovative media partnerships, where our visuals can truly shine and make a significant impact. We want to move beyond simply capturing beautiful images to creating narratives that captivate, educate, and inspire action, whether it’s for environmental awareness, product promotion, or artistic expression.","inspiration_to_apply":"We’re driven by a passion to share the magic of the underwater world with a broader audience, and we believe our unique skillset and artistic vision can significantly contribute to the commercial space. We see this mentorship as a crucial step in bridging the gap between our creative passion and commercial success. We want to learn how to strategically position our work, attract high-caliber clients, and build a sustainable business model that allows us to pursue our vision of impactful underwater storytelling on a grander scale.","referral_source":["Social Media (Instagram, Facebook, etc.)"]}'::jsonb, '{}', '[]'::jsonb, '2025-03-26T19:07:40+00:00');
INSERT INTO applications (program, status, user_id, answers, tags, admin_notes, submitted_at) VALUES ('filmmaking', 'reviewing', NULL, '{"first_name":"Harper Langdon Altschul","nickname":"Harper","email":"harperaltschul@icloud.com","online_links":"https://www.instagram.com/harperaltschul/","age":"18-24","budget":"Advanced budget (3,000 - 6,000 €/USD)","phone":"+1 929 366 5400","gender":"Male","nationality":"American","country_of_residence":"USA","languages":"English, Spanish","current_occupation":"Videographer for Maldives Underwater Iniative","physical_fitness":"Excellent - Regular exercise, no health concerns","health_conditions":"No health conditions affecting diving","diving_types":["Recreational Scuba diving","Freediving"],"certification_level":"Divemaster","number_of_dives":"250+","last_dive_date":"25.03.2025","diving_environments":["Tropical Reefs","Cold water","Deep diving","Night diving","Cave/Wreck diving"],"buoyancy_skill":10,"equipment_owned":["Professional video camera","Lighting equipment"],"filming_equipment":"Sony A7SIII in Nauticam housing with a Nauticam Flat Port 45\nWWL 1B & CMC-1 \nTwo Backscatter Hybrid Flash Lights","planning_to_invest":"No immediate plans","years_experience":"1-3 years","skill_camera_settings":7,"skill_lighting":7,"skill_post_production":8,"skill_color_correction":7,"skill_storytelling":7,"skill_drone":7,"skill_over_water":8,"content_created":["Social media content","Documentary style","Currently I only have one documentary style video","but I am in the process of editing others."],"btm_category":"ASPIRING PROFESSIONAL (Part-time professional aiming for full-time career)","involvement_level":"Not necessarily professional - yet. But, I am in the process of working towards it","online_presence":"Active social media","income_from_filming":"Occasionally (few projects per year)","primary_goal":"Transform hobby into professional career","secondary_goal":"Enhance existing professional skills","learning_aspects":["Storytelling and content planning","Business aspects of underwater filming","Client relations and project management","Conservation documentation"],"content_to_create":["Personal/travel memories","Social media content","Documentary style films","Conservation stories"],"learning_approach":["Small group workshop (within a group of approx. 4 persons)","One-on-one mentorship","Project-based learning (within a BTM project)"],"marine_subjects":["Big marine life (sharks, whales, etc.)","Marine behavior","Conservation stories"],"time_availability":"now and then for online classes","travel_willingness":"Yes, willing to travel internationally","start_timeline":"Flexible/Not sure yet","ultimate_vision":"I want to pair my passions for underwater cinematography and storytelling to advocate for change in our oceans and inspire people to fall in love with our natural world. One day I dream of working with national geographic and or BBC earth to create stories that change the hearts and minds of people.","inspiration_to_apply":"I have seen many of the films BTM has produced and I was inspired to apply because I would love to gain experience working on a production with a film crew.","referral_source":["Diving community"],"questions_or_concerns":"n/a","anything_else":"I am 18 and dream of finding a way to create a career out of telling stories about our natural world. I have very big dreams and I want to be the very best I can be. That said, I want to be surrounded by people who are much more talented than me so I can learn from them."}'::jsonb, '{}', '[]'::jsonb, '2025-03-26T08:08:30+00:00');
INSERT INTO applications (program, status, user_id, answers, tags, admin_notes, submitted_at) VALUES ('filmmaking', 'reviewing', NULL, '{"first_name":"Daniel","nickname":"Mena","email":"danimena.a@gmail.com","online_links":"www.danimena.wordpress.com/;www.youtube.com/@slowdivebuceo9369;instagram.com/slowdivebuceo","age":"35-44","budget":"Moderate budget (1,000 - 3,000 €/USD)","phone":"0034622818118","gender":"Male","nationality":"Spanish","country_of_residence":"Spain","languages":"English, Spanish, French, Catalan","current_occupation":"Sales executive","physical_fitness":"Excellent - Regular exercise, no health concerns","health_conditions":"No health conditions affecting diving","diving_types":["Recreational Scuba diving","Freediving","Snorkeling"],"certification_level":"Instructor, Certified Freediver","number_of_dives":"250+","last_dive_date":"05.01.2025","diving_environments":["Tropical Reefs","Deep diving","Night diving","Cave/Wreck diving"],"buoyancy_skill":10,"equipment_owned":["Action camera (GoPro, Osmo, Insta360, etc)","DSLR/Mirrorless with housing"],"filming_equipment":"Gopro9, PanasonicGgh4, Dji mavic pro","planning_to_invest":"Yes, within the near future","years_experience":"5+ years","skill_camera_settings":6,"skill_lighting":6,"skill_post_production":10,"skill_color_correction":8,"skill_storytelling":10,"skill_drone":5,"skill_over_water":10,"content_created":["Personal vacation videos","Social media content","Commercial work"],"btm_category":"ASPIRING PROFESSIONAL (Part-time professional aiming for full-time career)","involvement_level":"Part-time professional","online_presence":"Personal website, Professional portfolio","income_from_filming":"Occasionally (few projects per year)","primary_goal":"Enhance existing professional skills","secondary_goal":"Document marine conservation/research","learning_aspects":["Camera settings and techniques","Lighting techniques","Marine life behavior understanding","Storytelling and content planning","Post-production and editing","Business aspects of underwater filming","Client relations and project management","Conservation documentation"],"content_to_create":["Documentary style films","Commercial/advertising content","Scientific/research documentation","Conservation stories"],"learning_approach":["Group workshops (within a group of approx. 10 persons)","Small group workshop (within a group of approx. 4 persons)","Project-based learning (within a BTM project)"],"marine_subjects":["Coral reefs","Big marine life (sharks, whales, etc.)","Marine behavior","Conservation stories"],"time_availability":"1 week to 10 days for a workshop, a project or individual training","travel_willingness":"Depends on duration and location","start_timeline":"Within next 3 months","ultimate_vision":"I would like to dedicate my life to underwater filming and to building a community of people who share my passions: storytelling through images, nature, and caring for all forms of life.","inspiration_to_apply":"My passion for filming started when I was a child. Later on, I studied cinema at ESCAC in Barcelona. After that, I began to travel and discovered scuba diving and the beauty of the underwater world. For some time now, I’ve been trying to merge both passions into one.\n\nAt one point, a friend and I tried to create our own label. But he moved 700 km away and started a family with two children. I had to take a job as a sales executive to pay the bills, and the project was left halfway—despite some great work done, valuable equipment invested, and a strong desire to keep going- \n\nWhile preparing our first project, we discovered your label BTM thanks to a fellow dive instructor, and we were blown away. Since then, you’ve been a true reference for us.","referral_source":["Social Media (Instagram, Facebook, etc.)"],"questions_or_concerns":"I’m just a bit afraid the cost might be beyond my reach, though I truly hope you’ll see something valuable in my work and experience that might inspire you to consider bringing me into your team","anything_else":"Yes, I’ll always be available for any kind of collaboration, and you’ll remain one of my most cherished references. I truly hope our paths cross soon"}'::jsonb, '{}', '[]'::jsonb, '2025-03-25T22:57:52+00:00');
INSERT INTO applications (program, status, user_id, answers, tags, admin_notes, submitted_at) VALUES ('filmmaking', 'reviewing', NULL, '{"first_name":"Dariush Tafreshinia","email":"dariush_tafreshi@yahoo.com","online_links":"@dariush_tafreshi","age":"45-54","budget":"Advanced budget (3,000 - 6,000 €/USD)","phone":"00989121786929","gender":"Male","nationality":"IRANIAN","country_of_residence":"IRAN","languages":"Persian","current_occupation":"Assistant Instructor Trainer","physical_fitness":"Excellent - Regular exercise, no health concerns","health_conditions":"No health conditions affecting diving","diving_types":["Recreational Scuba diving"],"certification_level":"Instructor","number_of_dives":"250+","last_dive_date":"25.03.2025","diving_environments":["Tropical Reefs","Cold water","Deep diving","Night diving","Cave/Wreck diving"],"buoyancy_skill":10,"equipment_owned":["Action camera (GoPro, Osmo, Insta360, etc)","Compact camera with housing","DSLR/Mirrorless with housing","Lighting equipment"],"filming_equipment":"Canon 5 D M II  / Canon 5 D M III / Canon R5","planning_to_invest":"Yes, within the next years","years_experience":"5+ years","skill_camera_settings":6,"skill_lighting":6,"skill_post_production":2,"skill_color_correction":1,"skill_storytelling":2,"skill_drone":6,"skill_over_water":4,"content_created":["Personal vacation videos","Social media content","Documentary style","Commercial work"],"btm_category":"OCEAN STEWARD (NGO/scientific focus, conservation-driven)","involvement_level":"Part-time professional","online_presence":"Active social media, Professional portfolio","income_from_filming":"Occasionally (few projects per year)","primary_goal":"Transform hobby into professional career","secondary_goal":"Document marine conservation/research","learning_aspects":["Marine life behavior understanding","Storytelling and content planning","Post-production and editing","Client relations and project management"],"content_to_create":["Social media content","Documentary style films","Commercial/advertising content","Conservation stories"],"learning_approach":["Mixed approach (combination of group and individual)","Project-based learning (within a BTM project)"],"marine_subjects":["Macro subjects","Marine behavior"],"time_availability":"1 week to 10 days for a workshop, a project or individual training","travel_willingness":"Depends on duration and location","start_timeline":"Within next 3 months","ultimate_vision":"I interested in traveling extensively as professional and expanding my experience through research and study, and sharing them with other.","inspiration_to_apply":"Because I love underwater world & BTM team are very professional.","referral_source":["Boat show dusseldorf"],"questions_or_concerns":"No","anything_else":"No"}'::jsonb, '{}', '[]'::jsonb, '2025-03-25T22:21:03+00:00');
INSERT INTO applications (program, status, user_id, answers, tags, admin_notes, submitted_at) VALUES ('filmmaking', 'reviewing', NULL, '{"first_name":"Franco Banfi","email":"photo@banfi.ch","online_links":"https://www.facebook.com/franco.banfi.37/?checkpoint_src=any\nhttps://www.instagram.com/francobanfi/?next=%2F\nhttps://www.banfi.ch","age":"54+","budget":"Moderate budget (1,000 - 3,000 €/USD)","phone":"+4192622983","gender":"Male","nationality":"Swiss","country_of_residence":"Switzerland","languages":"English, Spanish, French, German, Italian","current_occupation":"Photographer, tour leader","physical_fitness":"Good - Moderately active, no major health concerns","health_conditions":"No health conditions affecting diving","diving_types":["Recreational Scuba diving","Rebreather diving","Freediving","Snorkeling"],"certification_level":"Instructor, Technical Diving certification, Certified Freediver","number_of_dives":"250+","last_dive_date":"18.03.2025","diving_environments":["Tropical Reefs","Cold water","Deep diving","Night diving","Cave/Wreck diving"],"buoyancy_skill":8,"equipment_owned":["DSLR/Mirrorless with housing","Lighting equipment"],"filming_equipment":"Sony A1, 16-35mm, fisheye, Isotta Housing, monitor, 2 x Keldan lights","planning_to_invest":"No immediate plans","years_experience":"Less than 1 year","skill_camera_settings":7,"skill_lighting":8,"skill_post_production":4,"skill_color_correction":3,"skill_storytelling":3,"skill_drone":2,"skill_over_water":3,"content_created":["Social media content"],"btm_category":"INDEPENDENT CREATOR (Experienced hobbyist/influencer seeking improvement)","involvement_level":"Part-time professional","online_presence":"Active social media, Personal website, Professional portfolio","income_from_filming":"No, not yet.","primary_goal":"Improve content creation for social media","secondary_goal":"Transform hobby into professional career","learning_aspects":["Camera settings and techniques","Storytelling and content planning","Post-production and editing","Business aspects of underwater filming","Client relations and project management"],"content_to_create":["Social media content","Documentary style films","Commercial/advertising content"],"learning_approach":["One-on-one mentorship","Mixed approach (combination of group and individual)","Project-based learning (within a BTM project)"],"marine_subjects":["Big marine life (sharks, whales, etc.)","Marine behavior"],"time_availability":"2-3 entire weeks at a time for a workshop, aproject or individual training","travel_willingness":"Depends on duration and location","start_timeline":"Within next 3 months","ultimate_vision":"I would like to understand how and why to set the camera to film, like I understand photography! Filming what I see when I swim with whales, mantas or similar.","inspiration_to_apply":"First curiosity, second I know Florian, I like the way he film, short and active. I think could be on the same way I see and like.","referral_source":["Social Media (Instagram, Facebook, etc.)"],"questions_or_concerns":"Not really!"}'::jsonb, '{}', '[]'::jsonb, '2025-03-25T19:14:41+00:00');
INSERT INTO applications (program, status, user_id, answers, tags, admin_notes, submitted_at) VALUES ('filmmaking', 'reviewing', NULL, '{"first_name":"Joshua Turner","nickname":"Josh","email":"joshturnermedia@gmail.com","online_links":"Website- https://www.joshturnermedia.com/\nInstagram- https://www.instagram.com/jturner0\nYouTube- https://www.youtube.com/@joshuaturner\nUnderwater Footage examples-\nBelize- https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=e0Dswnxaaho\nFiji-https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=iuv7hSslQgs","age":"25-34","budget":"Moderate budget (1,000 - 3,000 €/USD)","phone":"9787299640","gender":"Male","nationality":"US and Canada","country_of_residence":"US","languages":"English","current_occupation":"Drone Cinematographer","physical_fitness":"Excellent - Regular exercise, no health concerns","health_conditions":"No health conditions affecting diving","diving_types":["Recreational Scuba diving"],"certification_level":"Advanced Open Water","number_of_dives":"51-250","last_dive_date":"05.07.2024","diving_environments":["Tropical Reefs","Night diving","Cave/Wreck diving"],"buoyancy_skill":9,"equipment_owned":["DSLR/Mirrorless with housing"],"filming_equipment":"Lumix GH5 \n7-14mm 50mm\nMeikon housing with 8\" dome port \n10,000Lumen Video Lights x2","planning_to_invest":"Yes, within the near future","years_experience":"3-5 years","skill_camera_settings":10,"skill_lighting":7,"skill_post_production":8,"skill_color_correction":9,"skill_storytelling":5,"skill_drone":10,"skill_over_water":10,"content_created":["Personal vacation videos","Social media content","Commercial work"],"btm_category":"DEDICATED ACHIEVER (Business-focused, seeking intensive mentorship)","involvement_level":"Part-time professional","online_presence":"Active social media, Personal website, Professional portfolio, Client base","income_from_filming":"Occasionally (few projects per year)","primary_goal":"Enhance existing professional skills","secondary_goal":"Transform hobby into professional career","learning_aspects":["Camera settings and techniques","Lighting techniques","Marine life behavior understanding","Storytelling and content planning","Post-production and editing","Business aspects of underwater filming","Client relations and project management"],"content_to_create":["Social media content","Documentary style films","Commercial/advertising content","Scientific/research documentation","Conservation stories"],"learning_approach":["Mixed approach (combination of group and individual)","Project-based learning (within a BTM project)"],"marine_subjects":["Coral reefs","Big marine life (sharks, whales, etc.)","Macro subjects","Marine behavior"],"time_availability":"2-3 entire weeks at a time for a workshop, aproject or individual training","travel_willingness":"Yes, willing to travel internationally","start_timeline":"Ready to start immediately","ultimate_vision":"Scuba diving and underwater filming is both a passion for me and something I would like to incorporate more into my work. My goal is to improve my underwater filmmaking skills and have the opportunity to learn from talented people. I do film work for tourism boards for example, I''ll be shooting a new film for Visit Malta where I''ll be capturing underwater scenes for one portion. Having the expertise and more experience filming underwater would be very valuable on a shoot like this. In addition I enjoy creating my own passion projects. Overall I love diving and filming and I am always looking for opportunities to get out there to film and experience incredible places.","inspiration_to_apply":"I''ve always had an obsession with coral reefs and the underwater world. From watching David Attenborough documentaries growing up to writing my biology thesis on the microbiology of coral bleaching and even keeping a reef aquarium at home. When I began scuba diving it opened up my eyes to a whole new world. In addition, filmmaking and photography have always been a passion of mine to the point where it is now what I do for work. I have had a few dive trips where I had the opportunity to film underwater and I absolutely loved it. I enjoy the technical challenge of underwater filmmaking and of course being able to experience incredible wildlife at the same time. I''ve been watching Behind The Mask videos on YouTube for years now and they always provided a great deal of inspiration and knowledge for me. After seeing the post about the BTM academy I had to reach out.","referral_source":["YouTube"]}'::jsonb, '{}', '[]'::jsonb, '2025-03-25T18:52:54+00:00');
INSERT INTO applications (program, status, user_id, answers, tags, admin_notes, submitted_at) VALUES ('filmmaking', 'reviewing', NULL, '{"first_name":"Anja Sawicki","nickname":"Anni","email":"Sawicki.Anja@gmail.com","online_links":"https://www.youtube.com/@lifeaddicted4455","age":"25-34","budget":"Small budget (under 1,000 €/USD)","phone":"+491737503188","gender":"Female","nationality":"German","country_of_residence":"Germany","languages":"English, French, German, Polish","current_occupation":"Biologist / Fitnesstrainer","physical_fitness":"Excellent - Regular exercise, no health concerns","health_conditions":"No health conditions affecting diving","diving_types":["Recreational Scuba diving","Freediving","Snorkeling"],"certification_level":"Open Water, Advanced Open Water, Certified Freediver","number_of_dives":"51-250","last_dive_date":"16.12.2024","diving_environments":["Tropical Reefs","Deep diving","Night diving","Cave/Wreck diving"],"buoyancy_skill":10,"equipment_owned":["Action camera (GoPro, Osmo, Insta360, etc)"],"filming_equipment":"GoPro Hero 8 and 13","planning_to_invest":"Yes, within the near future","years_experience":"1-3 years","skill_camera_settings":5,"skill_lighting":2,"skill_post_production":7,"skill_color_correction":7,"skill_storytelling":5,"skill_drone":2,"skill_over_water":5,"content_created":["Personal vacation videos"],"btm_category":"OCEAN STEWARD (NGO/scientific focus, conservation-driven)","involvement_level":"Next to my university degree, I tried as much as I could (in vaccations).","online_presence":"None of the above","income_from_filming":"No, not yet.","primary_goal":"Transform hobby into professional career","secondary_goal":"Improve content creation for social media","learning_aspects":["Basic equipment setup and operation","Camera settings and techniques","Lighting techniques","Storytelling and content planning","Post-production and editing","Business aspects of underwater filming","Client relations and project management","Inspire curiosity and enthusiasm for the ocean in people"],"content_to_create":["Social media content","Documentary style films","Conservation stories"],"learning_approach":["Small group workshop (within a group of approx. 4 persons)","Mixed approach (combination of group and individual)","Project-based learning (within a BTM project)"],"marine_subjects":["Big marine life (sharks, whales, etc.)","Conservation stories"],"time_availability":"2-3 entire weeks at a time for a workshop, aproject or individual training","travel_willingness":"Yes, willing to travel internationally","start_timeline":"Ready to start immediately","ultimate_vision":"I wish to inspire people with the underwater world, helping them develop a deeper awareness and take meaningful experiences from their underwater journeys: whether it''s a stronger connection to nature or a greater commitment to environmental protection. I would love to touch people''s hearts and remind them of the beauty of our planet. For this, storytelling as well as well-crafted videos that evoke emotions are of great importance. I would also love to offer marine biology excursions in the future and, ideally, one day make a living showing people the underwater world. Additionally, I would like to share what I personally experience and see underwater, preferably in very high quality. I have a sensitive talent for working with underwater animals and an instinct for finding them, which is why I’m known in my circle of friends for always spotting exciting creatures.","inspiration_to_apply":"I chose you because your videos were a great support during my challenging studies in marine biology and always reminded me why I was doing it. Your videos also touched the hearts of my friends, and I found it beautiful to see how they could develop enthusiasm for something they had never known before.\n\nI believe that this can have a great impact on people, helping them become more environmentally conscious in their daily lives. I am convinced that nature conservation starts beyond the coast, where people can''t truly grasp it because they don''t know it.\n\nI wish to share my love for the ocean and nature in this way and to start projects, such as marine biology trips.","referral_source":["Online search"],"questions_or_concerns":"Do I need to get equipment beforehand? If yes, which ones?","anything_else":"I recently completed my master''s thesis and am very flexible. I would love to learn more about your work and am also interested in working with you or at your organization. I am planning to pursue further certifications in underwater activities and would like to become an ocean ambassador. I’m just missing the know-how on how to monetize it. Still, it’s a heartfelt dream, and I feel it is my calling. My love for the ocean has always been my greatest drive. As a little fun story about me: My last name comes from a polish legend about the mermaid \"Sawa,\" on whose tale the city of Warsaw was founded. It''s in my genes! ;D"}'::jsonb, '{}', '[]'::jsonb, '2025-03-25T17:44:41+00:00');
INSERT INTO applications (program, status, user_id, answers, tags, admin_notes, submitted_at) VALUES ('filmmaking', 'reviewing', NULL, '{"first_name":"gabriele cecere","nickname":"gbrlccr","email":"ceradue@gmail.com","online_links":"https://www.instagram.com/gbrlccr?igsh=ZTVrMmozOG5sbW1l","age":"35-44","budget":"Small budget (under 1,000 €/USD)","phone":"+39 3470370843","gender":"Male","nationality":"italian","country_of_residence":"italy","languages":"English, French, italian","current_occupation":"commercial diver","physical_fitness":"Excellent - Regular exercise, no health concerns","health_conditions":"No health conditions affecting diving","diving_types":["Recreational Scuba diving","Rebreather diving","Freediving","commercial diving"],"certification_level":"Instructor, Technical Diving certification, Certified Freediver, commercial diver","number_of_dives":"250+","last_dive_date":"21.03.2025","diving_environments":["Tropical Reefs","Cold water","Deep diving","Night diving","Cave/Wreck diving","all diving"],"buoyancy_skill":10,"equipment_owned":["Action camera (GoPro, Osmo, Insta360, etc)","Lighting equipment"],"filming_equipment":"osmo dji4 two supe v3","planning_to_invest":"Yes, within the next years","years_experience":"Less than 1 year","skill_camera_settings":6,"skill_lighting":3,"skill_post_production":4,"skill_color_correction":5,"skill_storytelling":2,"skill_drone":1,"skill_over_water":2,"content_created":["None yet","excited to start"],"btm_category":"INDEPENDENT CREATOR (Experienced hobbyist/influencer seeking improvement)","involvement_level":"Complete beginner","online_presence":"None of the above","income_from_filming":"No, not yet.","primary_goal":"Transform hobby into professional career","secondary_goal":"Document marine conservation/research","learning_aspects":["Camera settings and techniques","Lighting techniques","Marine life behavior understanding","Storytelling and content planning","Post-production and editing","Business aspects of underwater filming","Client relations and project management"],"content_to_create":["Social media content","Documentary style films","Commercial/advertising content","Scientific/research documentation"],"learning_approach":["Mixed approach (combination of group and individual)","Project-based learning (within a BTM project)"],"marine_subjects":["Coral reefs","Big marine life (sharks, whales, etc.)","Macro subjects","Marine behavior","Conservation stories"],"time_availability":"2-3 entire weeks at a time for a workshop, aproject or individual training","travel_willingness":"Yes, willing to travel internationally","start_timeline":"Flexible/Not sure yet","ultimate_vision":"I''d love to create astonishing uw image, I would to develop my own style, also in filming or in post production.","inspiration_to_apply":"I follow btm crew and I like the energy and the vibes of your content, the team looks like not only people who did their best but also have fun to do it.","referral_source":["Social Media (Instagram, Facebook, etc.)"],"questions_or_concerns":"Is there the chance to be part of a project and earn money following btm accademy?","anything_else":"I''have a solid background in graphic design and lettering"}'::jsonb, '{}', '[]'::jsonb, '2025-03-25T10:30:49+00:00');
INSERT INTO applications (program, status, user_id, answers, tags, admin_notes, submitted_at) VALUES ('filmmaking', 'reviewing', NULL, '{"first_name":"Hank Kollross","nickname":"Scoobz","email":"scubahank@gmail.com","online_links":"Instagram handle is @Photoctopus - My Website is being actively being rebuilt right now (www.photoctopus.com)","age":"45-54","budget":"Advanced budget (3,000 - 6,000 €/USD)","phone":"+1 414-745-4043","gender":"Male","nationality":"USA","country_of_residence":"USA","languages":"English","current_occupation":"Adventure Travel Company Owner, and Software Sales","physical_fitness":"Good - Moderately active, no major health concerns","health_conditions":"No health conditions affecting diving","diving_types":["Recreational Scuba diving"],"certification_level":"Rescue Diver","number_of_dives":"250+","last_dive_date":"07.03.2025","diving_environments":["Tropical Reefs","Cold water","Night diving","Cave/Wreck diving"],"buoyancy_skill":9,"equipment_owned":["DSLR/Mirrorless with housing","Lighting equipment"],"filming_equipment":"Nikon Z8, Nauticam Housing, Kraken 18,000 Torches, Nauticam Wet Lens, all the standard Nikon Macro lenses. No external monitor yet (I just switched from shooting stills to shooting video)","planning_to_invest":"Yes, within the near future","years_experience":"1-3 years","skill_camera_settings":9,"skill_lighting":6,"skill_post_production":6,"skill_color_correction":5,"skill_storytelling":5,"skill_drone":4,"skill_over_water":5,"content_created":["Personal vacation videos","Social media content","Blackwater videos for trips I''ve been on featuring the subjects seen."],"btm_category":"OCEAN STEWARD (NGO/scientific focus, conservation-driven)","involvement_level":"Hobby only","online_presence":"Active social media, Personal website","income_from_filming":"No, thats not my goal.","primary_goal":"Learn basics of underwater filming as a hobby","secondary_goal":"Document marine conservation/research","learning_aspects":["Lighting techniques","Storytelling and content planning","Post-production and editing","Business aspects of underwater filming","Conservation documentation","I want to inspire people to make a difference","and show them worlds they might never see."],"content_to_create":["Social media content","Documentary style films","Conservation stories"],"learning_approach":["Small group workshop (within a group of approx. 4 persons)","One-on-one mentorship","Mixed approach (combination of group and individual)","Project-based learning (within a BTM project)"],"marine_subjects":["All of the above. Especially the techniques to capture the big stuff properly."],"time_availability":"1 week to 10 days for a workshop, a project or individual training","travel_willingness":"Yes, willing to travel internationally","start_timeline":"Ready to start immediately","ultimate_vision":"I am new to filming but have been a photographer for many years. I am interested in telling stories, driving awareness, and promoting marine conservation.  Watching people doom scroll through their phones and so easily influenced by what they see, I''d like to use that as a positive and help inform, engage, and ignite people to make a difference.  I am not interested in this vertical video trend, but rather driving people to more engaging content, short stories, and inspiring scenes.","inspiration_to_apply":"I have always admired the BTM videos (both educational, and travel/on-location stories) and jumped at the chance when I saw your advertisement.  I want to inspire others like your videos have inspired me to document these environments, creatures and share it with those who might never see it, but absolutely can help.","referral_source":["YouTube"],"questions_or_concerns":"No concerns. Interested in what you guys come up with for learning opportunities and how I might be able to get involved and learn along the way.","anything_else":"Generally speaking I have a very flexible schedule and can travel. I am hoping to find an opportunity to be part of something bigger than I have to date, learn while I am doing it, and take those skills to build on for future projects.  As you will have read earlier in my application, I own a travel company and have had the opportunity travel far and wide. That being said I am always leading groups around the planet and busy with that, rarely finding the dedicated time I need to focus on the craft, and build out a portfolio of work.  This might be that chance."}'::jsonb, '{}', '[]'::jsonb, '2025-03-25T00:31:33+00:00');
INSERT INTO applications (program, status, user_id, answers, tags, admin_notes, submitted_at) VALUES ('filmmaking', 'reviewing', NULL, '{"first_name":"Mikaela Noemi Flores Nunez","nickname":"Mika","email":"mika052001.flores@gmail.com","online_links":"https://www.instagram.com/_.sunblue666?igsh=MTNvNmI4ODZxOHFrdA==","age":"18-24","budget":"Small budget (under 1,000 €/USD)","phone":"+49 1635348378","gender":"Female","nationality":"Spanisch","country_of_residence":"Germany","languages":"English, Spanish, German, English B1","current_occupation":"Guest Experience Agent","physical_fitness":"Good - Moderately active, no major health concerns","health_conditions":"No health conditions affecting diving","diving_types":["Recreational Scuba diving"],"certification_level":"Open Water","number_of_dives":"0-50","last_dive_date":"15.10.2024","diving_environments":["Tropical Reefs"],"buoyancy_skill":3,"equipment_owned":["No equipment yet"],"filming_equipment":"None","planning_to_invest":"Yes, within the next years","years_experience":"None","skill_camera_settings":3,"skill_lighting":2,"skill_post_production":3,"skill_color_correction":3,"skill_storytelling":5,"skill_drone":1,"skill_over_water":1,"content_created":["None yet","excited to start"],"btm_category":"ASPIRING PROFESSIONAL (Part-time professional aiming for full-time career)","involvement_level":"Complete beginner","online_presence":"Active social media","income_from_filming":"No, thats not my goal.","primary_goal":"Document marine conservation/research","secondary_goal":"Transform hobby into professional career","learning_aspects":["Basic equipment setup and operation","Camera settings and techniques","Lighting techniques","Marine life behavior understanding","Storytelling and content planning","Post-production and editing","Client relations and project management","Conservation documentation"],"content_to_create":["Personal/travel memories","Documentary style films","Conservation stories"],"learning_approach":["Group workshops (within a group of approx. 10 persons)","Mixed approach (combination of group and individual)","Project-based learning (within a BTM project)"],"marine_subjects":["Coral reefs","Big marine life (sharks, whales, etc.)","Marine behavior","Conservation stories"],"time_availability":"2-3 entire weeks at a time for a workshop, aproject or individual training","travel_willingness":"Yes, willing to travel internationally","start_timeline":"Within next 3 months","ultimate_vision":"I would love to create and master the techniques for producing informative and recretional videos, especially those that convey the importance of art and nature conversation. It may sound cliché, but my dream ist to live from the art, while also giving it purpose by contributing to the protection of something as vital as nature. :)","inspiration_to_apply":"I went to the Ocean Gala in Düsseldorf and was blown away by how much a short film can make a difference and how it can really motivate you to do what moves you!","referral_source":["Conservation organisation"]}'::jsonb, '{}', '[]'::jsonb, '2025-03-24T14:38:54+00:00');
INSERT INTO applications (program, status, user_id, answers, tags, admin_notes, submitted_at) VALUES ('filmmaking', 'reviewing', NULL, '{"first_name":"Fabio Benelli","email":"info@fabiobenelli.com","online_links":"IG: https://www.instagram.com/_fabiobenelli_/ WebSite: https://fabiobenelli.com/en/ YouTube: https://www.youtube.com/@FabioBenelliFilmmaking","age":"25-34","budget":"Moderate budget (1,000 - 3,000 €/USD)","phone":"+393896444518","gender":"Male","nationality":"Italian","country_of_residence":"Italy","languages":"English, Italian","current_occupation":"Freelance Filmmaker","physical_fitness":"Excellent - Regular exercise, no health concerns","health_conditions":"No health conditions affecting diving","diving_types":["Recreational Scuba diving","Technical Scuba diving","Rebreather diving"],"certification_level":"Instructor, Technical Diving certification","number_of_dives":"250+","last_dive_date":"06.03.2025","diving_environments":["Tropical Reefs","Cold water","Deep diving","Night diving"],"buoyancy_skill":10,"equipment_owned":["DSLR/Mirrorless with housing","Lighting equipment"],"filming_equipment":"Sony a7SIII with NA-A7SIII Nauticam Housing, Atomos Shinobi monitor with NA-SHINOBI Nauticam Housing, Sony 16-35 f/2.8 GM Lens with Nauticam 230 dome Port, Sony 90mm Macro with Nauticam flat Port, +10 diopter lens,  Sony 24-70 f/2.8 GMII, 2x 8X 15.000 lumen Keldan Light with filter.","planning_to_invest":"Yes, within the near future","years_experience":"5+ years","skill_camera_settings":8,"skill_lighting":8,"skill_post_production":8,"skill_color_correction":7,"skill_storytelling":6,"skill_drone":8,"skill_over_water":8,"content_created":["Social media content","Documentary style","Commercial work","Scientific/Research documentation"],"btm_category":"ASPIRING PROFESSIONAL (Part-time professional aiming for full-time career)","involvement_level":"Part-time professional","online_presence":"Active social media, Personal website","income_from_filming":"Regular part-time income","primary_goal":"Enhance existing professional skills","secondary_goal":"Improve content creation for social media","learning_aspects":["Storytelling and content planning","Business aspects of underwater filming","Client relations and project management"],"content_to_create":["Documentary style films","Scientific/research documentation","Conservation stories"],"learning_approach":["One-on-one mentorship","Project-based learning (within a BTM project)"],"marine_subjects":["Coral reefs","Big marine life (sharks, whales, etc.)","Macro subjects","Marine behavior","Conservation stories"],"time_availability":"2-3 entire weeks at a time for a workshop, aproject or individual training","travel_willingness":"Yes, willing to travel internationally","start_timeline":"Within next 3 months","ultimate_vision":"I''m a topside and underwater filmmaker from Italy, with a background in marine biology, so my work focuses mainly on conservation story, science communication, travel and ocean. In these years I''ve worked mainly as a solo filmmaker and I haven''t had much opportunity to collaborate with other professionals in the industry, although I truly believe that collaboration, a good mentor and connection with people is the only way to grow both on a personal and professional level. That''s why in the next years I would like to step out and connect with other people in the industry and join international projects and I think that the Behind the Mask Academy could be the perfect opportunity to do that.","inspiration_to_apply":"I''ve been following Behind the Mask''s work since the beginning, and you''ve really inspired me to pursue this kind of career, so I''d love to learn the process of creating the craft that inspired me many years ago.","referral_source":["Social Media (Instagram, Facebook, etc.)"]}'::jsonb, '{}', '[]'::jsonb, '2025-03-24T11:17:10+00:00');
INSERT INTO applications (program, status, user_id, answers, tags, admin_notes, submitted_at) VALUES ('filmmaking', 'reviewing', NULL, '{"first_name":"Victor Harcourt","email":"vharcourt@me.com","online_links":"@vharcourt Instagram / facebook","age":"54+","budget":"Advanced budget (3,000 - 6,000 €/USD)","phone":"+61 0437091341","gender":"Male","nationality":"Australian","country_of_residence":"Australia","languages":"English","current_occupation":"Lawyer","physical_fitness":"Good - Moderately active, no major health concerns","health_conditions":"No health conditions affecting diving","diving_types":["Recreational Scuba diving"],"certification_level":"Divemaster","number_of_dives":"51-250","last_dive_date":"05.01.2025","diving_environments":["Tropical Reefs","Cold water","Deep diving","Night diving"],"buoyancy_skill":9,"equipment_owned":["Action camera (GoPro, Osmo, Insta360, etc)","DSLR/Mirrorless with housing","Lighting equipment"],"filming_equipment":"Canon R5 with 15 to 35mm f2.8 R lens; Nauticam housing; Keldan 8XR 20000lm lights; Sea&Sea YS D3 Mk 2Strobes","planning_to_invest":"No immediate plans","years_experience":"1-3 years","skill_camera_settings":8,"skill_lighting":6,"skill_post_production":4,"skill_color_correction":3,"skill_storytelling":3,"skill_drone":4,"skill_over_water":6,"content_created":["Personal vacation videos"],"btm_category":"BEGINNER - Creative Explorer (Just starting, hobby-focused, seeking basic skills)","involvement_level":"Hobby only","online_presence":"Active social media","income_from_filming":"No, not yet.","primary_goal":"Improve content creation for social media","secondary_goal":"Transform hobby into professional career","learning_aspects":["Marine life behavior understanding","Storytelling and content planning","Post-production and editing"],"content_to_create":["Social media content","Conservation stories"],"learning_approach":["Small group workshop (within a group of approx. 4 persons)","One-on-one mentorship","Mixed approach (combination of group and individual)"],"marine_subjects":["Big marine life (sharks, whales, etc.)","Conservation stories"],"time_availability":"1 week to 10 days for a workshop, a project or individual training","travel_willingness":"Yes, willing to travel internationally","start_timeline":"Within next 6 months","ultimate_vision":"I am a 60 year old lawyer in Melbourne Australia who discovered scuba diving and a love of the ocean post the pandemic. I am a very keen photographer (see @vharcourt Instagram) but have found learning video skills challenging. While my job is very rewarding I want to transition into exploring the ocean more and inviting other people in my age range into this world via video and photos. I want to increase my awareness and understanding of the issues facing marine life, share that with others and look for ways to inspire change.  With the last of my children having now finished high school I have the time and energy to devote to my passion.","inspiration_to_apply":"I have admired your work for some time and love the fun, humor and passion you bring without compromising the quality. I have viewed some of your YouTube content created to improve video skills and also follow your instagram account. The BTM Academy is a perfect opportunity to learn from experienced underwater videographers who are at the peak of their careers willing to mentor others. In my experience, the best mentors are those who are actively involved in their area of work.","referral_source":["Social Media (Instagram, Facebook, etc.)"],"questions_or_concerns":"Not at the moment. Once I receive more information about what is on offer I may have more questions."}'::jsonb, '{}', '[]'::jsonb, '2025-03-24T11:04:39+00:00');
INSERT INTO applications (program, status, user_id, answers, tags, admin_notes, submitted_at) VALUES ('filmmaking', 'reviewing', NULL, '{"first_name":"Zoé Labarthe","email":"zoelabarthe08@gmail.com","online_links":"https://www.instagram.com/zoe_.lbrt/","age":"18-24","budget":"Moderate budget (1,000 - 3,000 €/USD)","phone":"0782936438","gender":"Female","nationality":"French","country_of_residence":"France","languages":"English, French","current_occupation":"Master student","physical_fitness":"Excellent - Regular exercise, no health concerns","health_conditions":"No health conditions affecting diving","diving_types":["scientific diving"],"certification_level":"French certification (N2= autonomy 20m and inset 40m), currently preparing the N3 (autonomy 40m and inset 60m)","number_of_dives":"51-250","last_dive_date":"21.03.2025","diving_environments":["Tropical Reefs","Night diving","Cave/Wreck diving","Atlantic ocean but it''s not really cold water"],"buoyancy_skill":9,"equipment_owned":["DSLR/Mirrorless with housing","Lighting equipment"],"filming_equipment":"I shoot with my sony a6400","planning_to_invest":"Yes, within the next years","years_experience":"None","skill_camera_settings":7,"skill_lighting":2,"skill_post_production":2,"skill_color_correction":1,"skill_storytelling":1,"skill_drone":1,"skill_over_water":1,"content_created":["None yet","excited to start"],"btm_category":"OCEAN STEWARD (NGO/scientific focus, conservation-driven)","involvement_level":"Hobby only","online_presence":"Active social media","income_from_filming":"No, not yet.","primary_goal":"Transform hobby into professional career","secondary_goal":"Document marine conservation/research","learning_aspects":["Lighting techniques","Storytelling and content planning","Post-production and editing","Conservation documentation"],"content_to_create":["Social media content","Documentary style films","Scientific/research documentation"],"learning_approach":["Mixed approach (combination of group and individual)","Project-based learning (within a BTM project)"],"marine_subjects":["Big marine life (sharks, whales, etc.)","Macro subjects","Marine behavior"],"time_availability":"2-3 entire weeks at a time for a workshop, aproject or individual training","travel_willingness":"Depends on duration and location","start_timeline":"Within next 3 months","ultimate_vision":"What I do most at the moment is photography. My biggest goal is to be a wildlife photographer as well as a scientist, and to be able to create films that are accessible to documentary filmmakers. I love “artistic” short films like \"One Breath Around the World\" with Guillaume Néry. I''d like to be able to transpose this vibe into documentary-oriented films to raise public awareness and inspire them to protect marine life and learn more about it.","inspiration_to_apply":"I love the content you produce, you''ve been an inspiration for years. I''ve been following you since I was 15-16 (I''m going on 23 this year). \nSo learning from you and meeting the team is like realizing a mini childhood dream.","referral_source":["Social Media (Instagram, Facebook, etc.)"],"anything_else":"I said I could start within 3 months, but in reality it''s more like 4 months. I''m currently doing an internship in a laboratory in Okinawa until July to complete my master''s degree in marine ecology."}'::jsonb, '{}', '[]'::jsonb, '2025-03-24T05:17:13+00:00');
INSERT INTO applications (program, status, user_id, answers, tags, admin_notes, submitted_at) VALUES ('filmmaking', 'reviewing', NULL, '{"first_name":"Anthony Ochieng Onyango","nickname":"TonyWild","email":"tony@tonywild.co.ke","online_links":"Website https://www.anthonyochieng.com/  \nInstagram https://www.instagram.com/anthony_ochieng_onyango/","age":"35-44","budget":"Moderate budget (1,000 - 3,000 €/USD)","phone":"+254723696916","gender":"Male","nationality":"Kenyan","country_of_residence":"Kenya","languages":"English, Swahili","current_occupation":"Wildlife Ecologist, Educator, Conservation and Underwater Photographer and Filmmaker","physical_fitness":"Good - Moderately active, no major health concerns","health_conditions":"No health conditions affecting diving","diving_types":["Technical Scuba diving"],"certification_level":"Advanced Open Water","number_of_dives":"51-250","last_dive_date":"20.03.2025","diving_environments":["Tropical Reefs","Cave/Wreck diving"],"buoyancy_skill":8,"equipment_owned":["DSLR/Mirrorless with housing","Lighting equipment"],"filming_equipment":"Canon EOS R5 Mirrorless Digital Camera \nMX-R5 Housing for Canon EOS R5 Mirrorless \n230mm Optical Glass Fisheye Port II\nApollo III Strobe (x2)\nMacro port","planning_to_invest":"Yes, within the near future","years_experience":"Less than 1 year","skill_camera_settings":8,"skill_lighting":2,"skill_post_production":2,"skill_color_correction":2,"skill_storytelling":10,"skill_drone":8,"skill_over_water":9,"content_created":["Documentary style","Commercial work","Scientific/Research documentation"],"btm_category":"OCEAN STEWARD (NGO/scientific focus, conservation-driven)","involvement_level":"Conservation/Scientific work","online_presence":"Active social media, Personal website","income_from_filming":"Occasionally (few projects per year)","primary_goal":"Enhance existing professional skills","secondary_goal":"Document marine conservation/research","learning_aspects":["Basic equipment setup and operation","Camera settings and techniques","Lighting techniques","Marine life behavior understanding","Storytelling and content planning","Post-production and editing","Business aspects of underwater filming","Client relations and project management","Conservation documentation"],"content_to_create":["Social media content","Documentary style films","Scientific/research documentation","Conservation stories"],"learning_approach":["One-on-one mentorship","Mixed approach (combination of group and individual)","Project-based learning (within a BTM project)"],"marine_subjects":["Coral reefs","Big marine life (sharks, whales, etc.)","Macro subjects","Conservation stories"],"time_availability":"2-3 entire weeks at a time for a workshop, aproject or individual training","travel_willingness":"Yes, willing to travel internationally","start_timeline":"Ready to start immediately","ultimate_vision":"For me, underwater filmmaking is more than just capturing beautiful shots. It’s about telling stories that connect people to the ocean in a way that makes them care. Growing up, I was drawn to wildlife on land, but the ocean always had this magnetic pull. The first time I dived into Kenya’s marine parks, I felt something shift—I knew I had to bring these hidden worlds to the surface for others to see.\n\nMy life time commitment is using film to change how people see the ocean, especially in Africa. I want to show that it’s not just a vast, distant place but a living, breathing world that sustains us all. I want to document the people who depend on it, the species fighting to survive, and the conservation efforts that often go unnoticed. Whether it’s hammerhead sharks in Ghana, manatees in Cameroon, or the fishermen who live alongside them, I want to tell stories that move people to act.\n\nOne day, I hope my work reaches a global audience on platforms like National Geographic or Netflix but more importantly, I hope it sparks something in the hearts of young Africans. I want them to see the ocean as part of their heritage, worth protecting and fighting for.","inspiration_to_apply":"Watching your videos on YouTube the clarity of the shots, the way they’re edited it honestly left me in admiration. I kept thinking, Wow, this is the kind of storytelling I want to create. Seeing your work gave me the confidence to take the leap, invest in my own underwater gear, and start practicing with the short clips the BTM family shares online.\n\nBut beyond the incredible filmmaking, what really drew me in was the sense of family that BTM has. It’s more than just an academy it’s a community of passionate storytellers who uplift and inspire each other. That’s something rare, and it’s something I want to be part of. I kept telling myself that I needed to own one of the BTM merch to feel like I was truly part of this bigger family.\n\nSo, for me, applying to BTM Academy isn’t just about learning the craft—it’s about growing with a community that shares my love for the ocean and storytelling.","referral_source":["Social Media (Instagram, Facebook, etc.)"],"questions_or_concerns":"not at the moment","anything_else":"This is a journey for me, and I would love to see it come to life."}'::jsonb, '{}', '[]'::jsonb, '2025-03-24T04:15:23+00:00');
