telling and content planning","Post-production and editing","Business aspects of underwater filming","Client relations and project management"],"content_to_create":["Social media content","Documentary style films","Commercial/advertising content"],"learning_approach":["Small group workshop (within a group of approx. 4 persons)","Mixed approach (combination of group and individual)","Project-based learning (within a BTM project)"],"marine_subjects":["Conservation stories"],"time_availability":"1 week to 10 days for a workshop, a project or individual training","travel_willingness":"Yes, willing to travel internationally","start_timeline":"Ready to start immediately","ultimate_vision":"Documenting deep wrecks and Conservation Projekts","inspiration_to_apply":"The great work BTM I doing","referral_source":["Social Media (Instagram, Facebook, etc.)"]}'::jsonb, '{}', '[]'::jsonb, '2025-03-23T21:55:22+00:00');
INSERT INTO applications (program, status, user_id, answers, tags, admin_notes, submitted_at) VALUES ('filmmaking', 'reviewing', NULL, '{"first_name":"Serhii Shcherbak","nickname":"Serhio","email":"Serhiishcherbak23@gmail.com","online_links":"https://www.instagram.com/tell_me_23?igsh=aGlpY3Mwc3VpYjJ3&utm_source=qr","age":"35-44","budget":"Small budget (under 1,000 €/USD)","phone":"+9607652504","gender":"Male","nationality":"Ukrainian","country_of_residence":"Maldives","languages":"English, Ukrainian , Russian","current_occupation":"Diving Instructor","physical_fitness":"Excellent - Regular exercise, no health concerns","health_conditions":"No health conditions affecting diving","diving_types":["Recreational Scuba diving","Technical Scuba diving","Rebreather diving","Freediving","Snorkeling"],"certification_level":"Instructor, Technical Diving certification, Certified Freediver","number_of_dives":"250+","last_dive_date":"23.03.2025","diving_environments":["Tropical Reefs","Deep diving","Night diving","Cave/Wreck diving"],"buoyancy_skill":10,"equipment_owned":["Action camera (GoPro, Osmo, Insta360, etc)","Compact camera with housing","Lighting equipment"],"filming_equipment":"Olympus TG6/ go pro 12","planning_to_invest":"Yes, within the near future","years_experience":"3-5 years","skill_camera_settings":6,"skill_lighting":6,"skill_post_production":5,"skill_color_correction":6,"skill_storytelling":5,"skill_drone":4,"skill_over_water":6,"content_created":["Personal vacation videos","Social media content"],"btm_category":"ASPIRING PROFESSIONAL (Part-time professional aiming for full-time career)","involvement_level":"Part-time professional","online_presence":"None of the above","income_from_filming":"Occasionally (few projects per year)","primary_goal":"Transform hobby into professional career","secondary_goal":"Document marine conservation/research","learning_aspects":["Camera settings and techniques","Lighting techniques","Storytelling and content planning","Post-production and editing","Business aspects of underwater filming","Client relations and project management"],"content_to_create":["Social media content","Documentary style films","Commercial/advertising content"],"learning_approach":["Group workshops (within a group of approx. 10 persons)","Mixed approach (combination of group and individual)","Project-based learning (within a BTM project)"],"marine_subjects":["Coral reefs","Big marine life (sharks, whales, etc.)","Macro subjects","Marine behavior","Conservation stories"],"time_availability":"1 week to 10 days for a workshop, a project or individual training","travel_willingness":"Depends on duration and location","start_timeline":"Ready to start immediately","ultimate_vision":"I enjoy to spend a lot of time underwater , observing  marine life. I want to share this beauty with others. I like Mega fauna same as macro. Shark and manta rays is my favorite big animals, and Tiny Nudies and Shrimps together with a corrals  polyps as a macro creatures. Maldives show me how nice ocean is , after I did travel to Mexican senotes to see this amazing caves. After that I understand that I need to learn Filming because there is so much to learn and to record. I saw Behind the Mask Videos on YouTube , and it’s was so nice and inspiring. So When I saw the academy and there is a chance to learn from you guys I understand that maybe this is what I need to do. I hope I’ll get a good chance to learn filming underwater and outside or the water. I left my home country 5 years ago and now because of the war I can’t go back. I wish I can show with my work that all the nation is important and everybody can achieve there dreams.","inspiration_to_apply":"Yours incredible Videos that I see on YouTube. It’s looks easy going , professional but very friendly and easy. It’s Feels very friendly don’t know why 🤷‍♂️","referral_source":["Social Media (Instagram, Facebook, etc.)"],"questions_or_concerns":"Don’t have a question yet , will be later probably.","anything_else":"I have a full time job in A diving safari now, I can’t travel so much at the moment need to support a family which moves to other country. I would like to to learn online. I still don’t know what to expect from the program but I open and willing to learn. \nThank you For the opportunity"}'::jsonb, '{}', '[]'::jsonb, '2025-03-23T19:07:46+00:00');
INSERT INTO applications (program, status, user_id, answers, tags, admin_notes, submitted_at) VALUES ('filmmaking', 'reviewing', NULL, '{"first_name":"PEDRO NIADA","nickname":"PETER","email":"peterniadascuba@gmail.com","online_links":"@peterniada  www.peterniada.cl","age":"45-54","budget":"Moderate budget (1,000 - 3,000 €/USD)","phone":"+56996648438","gender":"Male","nationality":"Chilean","country_of_residence":"CHILE","languages":"English, Spanish","current_occupation":"UW CAMERAMAN","physical_fitness":"Excellent - Regular exercise, no health concerns","health_conditions":"No health conditions affecting diving","diving_types":["Recreational Scuba diving","Technical Scuba diving","Snorkeling"],"certification_level":"Instructor","number_of_dives":"250+","last_dive_date":"16.03.2025","diving_environments":["Cold water","Deep diving","Night diving","Cave/Wreck diving"],"buoyancy_skill":10,"equipment_owned":["DSLR/Mirrorless with housing","Lighting equipment"],"filming_equipment":"LUMIX S1H, 16-35mm lumix full frame, 105mm sigma full frame, Atomos NinjaV, Nauticam housings, two 16,000 lumen BigBlue lights.","planning_to_invest":"No immediate plans","years_experience":"5+ years","skill_camera_settings":9,"skill_lighting":9,"skill_post_production":9,"skill_color_correction":8,"skill_storytelling":5,"skill_drone":8,"skill_over_water":9,"content_created":["Social media content","Commercial work","Scientific/Research documentation"],"btm_category":"OCEAN STEWARD (NGO/scientific focus, conservation-driven)","involvement_level":"Part-time professional","online_presence":"Active social media, Personal website","income_from_filming":"Occasionally (few projects per year)","primary_goal":"Enhance existing professional skills","secondary_goal":"Document marine conservation/research","learning_aspects":["Camera settings and techniques","Lighting techniques","Storytelling and content planning","Post-production and editing","Business aspects of underwater filming","Client relations and project management","Conservation documentation"],"content_to_create":["Social media content","Documentary style films","Scientific/research documentation","Conservation stories"],"learning_approach":["Group workshops (within a group of approx. 10 persons)","Small group workshop (within a group of approx. 4 persons)","Project-based learning (within a BTM project)"],"marine_subjects":["Coral reefs","Big marine life (sharks, whales, etc.)","Macro subjects","Marine behavior","Conservation stories"],"time_availability":"2-3 entire weeks at a time for a workshop, aproject or individual training","travel_willingness":"Yes, willing to travel internationally","start_timeline":"Flexible/Not sure yet","ultimate_vision":"my best dive has always been my last, i would like to improve my uwcamera skills, storytelling so I can be able to share that knowledge in Chile and help conservation plans in my country.","inspiration_to_apply":"I used to do analog UW photography, I lost all my gear after the 2010 tsunami that hit Robinson Crusoe island where i had my diving center, after the tsunami i started doing UW filming in a way to rebuild my self.  I admire what BTM has done in all these years.","referral_source":["Conservation organisation"],"anything_else":"I have 30 years of diving experience, I lived 15 years in Robinson Crusoe Island Chile, Im a PADI instructor and UWfilming lover!!"}'::jsonb, '{}', '[]'::jsonb, '2025-03-23T16:50:36+00:00');
INSERT INTO applications (program, status, user_id, answers, tags, admin_notes, submitted_at) VALUES ('filmmaking', 'reviewing', NULL, '{"first_name":"Corina Ackermann","email":"info@corina.media","online_links":"https://www.corina.media/underwater.html   https://www.instagram.com/corina.media/   https://www.linkedin.com/in/corina-ackermann-3496b226a/","age":"35-44","budget":"All-In budget (>12,000 €/USD)","phone":"+49 151 23 151 626","gender":"Female","nationality":"German","country_of_residence":"Germany","languages":"English, German","current_occupation":"self-employed","physical_fitness":"Excellent - Regular exercise, no health concerns","health_conditions":"No health conditions affecting diving","diving_types":["Recreational Scuba diving"],"certification_level":"Advanced Open Water, Certified Freediver, Master Diver certified according to I.A.C","number_of_dives":"51-250","last_dive_date":"23.02.2025","diving_environments":["Tropical Reefs","Deep diving","Night diving","Diving in german lakes from spring until autumn"],"buoyancy_skill":8,"equipment_owned":["Action camera (GoPro, Osmo, Insta360, etc)","Compact camera with housing"],"filming_equipment":"Canon G7x Mark ii, DJI Osmo Action 4,","planning_to_invest":"Yes, within the near future","years_experience":"3-5 years","skill_camera_settings":8,"skill_lighting":2,"skill_post_production":6,"skill_color_correction":7,"skill_storytelling":6,"skill_drone":6,"skill_over_water":7,"content_created":["Personal vacation videos","Social media content","working for nature conversatoin organisation"],"btm_category":"ASPIRING PROFESSIONAL (Part-time professional aiming for full-time career)","involvement_level":"Hobby only","online_presence":"Personal website","income_from_filming":"No, not yet.","primary_goal":"Transform hobby into professional career","secondary_goal":"Enhance existing professional skills","learning_aspects":["Camera settings and techniques","Lighting techniques","Marine life behavior understanding","Storytelling and content planning","Post-production and editing","Business aspects of underwater filming","Client relations and project management","Conservation documentation"],"content_to_create":["Documentary style films","Scientific/research documentation","Conservation stories"],"learning_approach":["Small group workshop (within a group of approx. 4 persons)","One-on-one mentorship","Mixed approach (combination of group and individual)","Project-based learning (within a BTM project)"],"marine_subjects":["Coral reefs","Big marine life (sharks, whales, etc.)","Marine behavior","Conservation stories"],"time_availability":"2-3 entire weeks at a time for a workshop, aproject or individual training","travel_willingness":"Yes, willing to travel internationally","start_timeline":"Ready to start immediately","ultimate_vision":"My absolute dream is to spend a large part of my life making underwater films. On the one hand, I would like to become a part of the filmmaking community for animal and nature documentaries and, at the same time, bring people closer to the importance of the oceans thanks to the medium of film. I would love to be able to make a good living from this passion. \nI would love to be involved in protecting the oceans with such great shots as you have created. To achieve this goal, however, I still lack a few skills. I am applying to you to learn these skills. Filming skills in general and of course especially underwater. I would very much like to learn various filming techniques from you and in particular how I can capture such wonderful shots under water. I am also interested in how to plan film projects like yours in general. And of course one of my goals is to network with like-minded people in order to learn from each other and to be able to realise such projects together.","inspiration_to_apply":"If, like me, you are involved in underwater filming, there is of course no way around you. I''ve seen your work and I''m thrilled by it. Raising my skills to such a level would be really great. After Florian told about the BTM Academy at this year''s Ocean Gala in Düsseldorf, I called up the website while I was still sitting in the cinema - it wasn''t online at the time. Later in the conversation, Florian told me more about your project and I realised - this is my big chance to get a big step closer to my goal. That''s why I''m applying to you.","referral_source":["Word of mouth"],"questions_or_concerns":"I am most interested in how long I can be part of the Academy. \nThe question in your form about how long you can imagine participating in the Academy can be answered with a maximum of 3 weeks. I would like to emphasise that I can well imagine being part of BTM and your Academy for several months. Because I believe that I can improve my skills, especially over a longer period of time. On the one hand, of course, I would like to benefit from your knowledge for as long as possible and, on the other hand, I can very well imagine actively supporting even you in your projects in the long term.","anything_else":"I would like to add something to two of the answers I gave:\nTo your question ‘Years of experience in underwatefilming’ I chose 3-5years as it has been 5 years since I always had my compact camera with me on every trip when diving. This resulted in some films and photos. At the same time, I wouldn''t say I have 5 years of experience, as I only ever film and take photos underwater temporarily (in summer at the lake or on holiday in the oceans).\n\nRegarding your question ‘What is your planned investment level in your underwater filming skills?’ I answered this with ‘all-in-budget’, as on the one hand I know the prices of professional cameras and corresponding housings etc. and am of course prepared to invest. On the other hand, it''s also an investment that I can''t make overnight.\n\nI would like to tell you a little more about myself and my professional situation.\nIn June 2023, I turned my long-standing hobby of photography and filming into a profession and have been working independently in two different areas ever since. On the one hand, I work with various cameramen as a camera and sound assistant for classic TV programmes. In addition, I am establishing myself more and more on the market in the field of children''s photography and the production of image films for kindergartens and primary schools. \nHowever, my biggest goal, which I am continuously working towards, is to become part of the film crew for animal and nature documentaries. Of course, my greatest passion is the underwater world. And to get a big step closer to this goal, I would be very happy to become part of your BTM Academy. As I am self-employed, I have the freedom to invest as much time as possible in this opportunity and also to be part of your Academy and your network over a longer period of time. \nThank you for your time and for reading my application. I am very much looking forward to hearing from you. Best regards, Corina."}'::jsonb, '{}', '[]'::jsonb, '2025-03-23T16:13:48+00:00');
INSERT INTO applications (program, status, user_id, answers, tags, admin_notes, submitted_at) VALUES ('filmmaking', 'reviewing', NULL, '{"first_name":"Collin O''Brien","email":"collinob23@gmail.com","online_links":"https://www.instagram.com/oceanscollin/ ; https://www.youtube.com/@OceansCollin","age":"25-34","budget":"All-In budget (>12,000 €/USD)","phone":"5086319151","gender":"Male","nationality":"American","country_of_residence":"United States","languages":"English","current_occupation":"State Trooper (Underwater Recovery Diver)","physical_fitness":"Excellent - Regular exercise, no health concerns","health_conditions":"No health conditions affecting diving","diving_types":["Recreational Scuba diving","Professional Public Safety Diver & Underwater Recovery"],"certification_level":"Open Water, Advanced Open Water, Rescue Diver, Certified Public Safety Diver, Nitrox, FFM, Drysuit","number_of_dives":"250+","last_dive_date":"22.03.2025","diving_environments":["Tropical Reefs","Cold water","Deep diving","Night diving","Cave/Wreck diving","Ice Diving","Swift Water","Zero Vis","High Seas","High Hazard"],"buoyancy_skill":8,"equipment_owned":["Action camera (GoPro, Osmo, Insta360, etc)","Professional video camera","Lighting equipment"],"filming_equipment":"Sony FX3, Panasonic GH5, GoPro 12 & 11","planning_to_invest":"Yes, within the near future","years_experience":"5+ years","skill_camera_settings":6,"skill_lighting":3,"skill_post_production":6,"skill_color_correction":8,"skill_storytelling":1,"skill_drone":5,"skill_over_water":3,"content_created":["Personal vacation videos","Social media content"],"btm_category":"ASPIRING PROFESSIONAL (Part-time professional aiming for full-time career)","involvement_level":"In-between Hobby and Part Time Professional","online_presence":"Active social media","income_from_filming":"No, not yet.","primary_goal":"Transform hobby into professional career","secondary_goal":"Improve content creation for social media","learning_aspects":["Camera settings and techniques","Lighting techniques","Marine life behavior understanding","Storytelling and content planning","Post-production and editing","Business aspects of underwater filming","Client relations and project management"],"content_to_create":["Social media content","Documentary style films","Commercial/advertising content","Conservation stories"],"learning_approach":["Small group workshop (within a group of approx. 4 persons)","One-on-one mentorship","Project-based learning (within a BTM project)"],"marine_subjects":["Coral reefs","Big marine life (sharks, whales, etc.)","Macro subjects","Marine behavior","Conservation stories"],"time_availability":"1 week to 10 days for a workshop, a project or individual training","travel_willingness":"Yes, willing to travel internationally","start_timeline":"Within next 3 months","ultimate_vision":"My ultimate vision for my underwater filming is to bring a voice to voiceless beneath the surface. I would love to capture the story of individual marine species, ecosystems and human interaction to create emotionally compelling stories that inspire people to understand, connect with and grow their curiosity about the ocean. The more we dive and connect ourselves we truly forget just how foreign this world is to the average human.\n\nMy goal is to produce high-quality, cinematic underwater films that showcase rare marine behaviors around the world. I would love to develop my post processing skills to the point I can take my footage and transport the audience watching at home into the water with me, making them feel as if they are witnessing these incredible encounters first hand.\n\nEventually, I would love to take this passion full-time, working with brands, conservation organizations, media outlets, hotels, dive operations and production companies like BBC, National Geographic, PBS, Discovery. Although I know this will take a lot of practice, time and investment post time wise and financially. Finding a way to sustain the cost for gear and production would be my immediate challenge.\n\nUltimately, I hope my footage is able to educate, inspire those who care about our oceans and challenge the ideologies of those who remain distant to the thought of our oceans.","inspiration_to_apply":"Growing up with several family members living waterfront in Plymouth, Massachusetts I have always been drawn to the ocean. We used to spend most of our summers with them, playing in the waves, riding the boat to Stellwagen Bank to see whales, looking for sea glass and walking to the tide pools exploring all the marine life that would be left during low tide. \n\nThe very first time I descended beneath the waves, I knew I wanted to tell stories about the environments I was experiencing. It is an entire new world down there, one full of life, movement, collaboration fragility and mystery that most people will never experience or seek to understand on their own.\n\nI am interested in BTM Academy because for several years I have been captivated by your teams ability to take videos and put them together in incredible sequences paired with sound design and storytelling to truly captivate the audience. I’ve seen your videos go from travel film to documentary style to real professional productions that rival anything I have seen. Your ability to match video with music to evoke emotion has grown incredibly. Your ability to write and narrate to educate and challenge the minds of others is truly special. These are things I would love to be able to do even half as good as your team and I am not sure there is anyone else that would have the insight into this that you would.","referral_source":["Social Media (Instagram, Facebook, etc.)"]}'::jsonb, '{}', '[]'::jsonb, '2025-03-23T16:12:47+00:00');
