ons and project management","Conservation documentation"],"content_to_create":["Documentary style films","Commercial/advertising content","Scientific/research documentation","Conservation stories"],"learning_approach":["Mixed approach (combination of group and individual)","Project-based learning (within a BTM project)"],"marine_subjects":["Coral reefs","Big marine life (sharks, whales, etc.)","Macro subjects","Marine behavior","Conservation stories"],"time_availability":"2-3 entire weeks at a time for a workshop, aproject or individual training","travel_willingness":"Yes, willing to travel internationally","start_timeline":"Ready to start immediately","ultimate_vision":"I want to inspire people to protect and respect the oceans and its life and eventually make it a daily part of life that makes you feel good","inspiration_to_apply":"I have been following btm videos since ive started diving many many years ago and its always been WOW specially the video dive to be alive video is goosebumpy. Btm’s filiming and story telling is epic to say the least","referral_source":["Online search"],"questions_or_concerns":"Nah I feel I would come out with something cool if its like anything to do with your videos","anything_else":"The ocean holds mysteries that needs to be discovered"}'::jsonb, '{}', '[]'::jsonb, '2025-03-23T13:47:34+00:00');
INSERT INTO applications (program, status, user_id, answers, tags, admin_notes, submitted_at) VALUES ('filmmaking', 'reviewing', NULL, '{"first_name":"Nour Amr","nickname":"Nour","email":"Nouramr99@gmail.com","online_links":"wherenouris","age":"25-34","budget":"Moderate budget (1,000 - 3,000 €/USD)","phone":"01019935972","gender":"Female","nationality":"Egyptian","country_of_residence":"Egypy","languages":"English","current_occupation":"Social Media Manager","physical_fitness":"Excellent - Regular exercise, no health concerns","health_conditions":"No health conditions affecting diving","diving_types":["Recreational Scuba diving"],"certification_level":"Advanced Open Water","number_of_dives":"51-250","last_dive_date":"02.01.2025","diving_environments":["Tropical Reefs","Night diving","Cave/Wreck diving"],"buoyancy_skill":6,"equipment_owned":["Action camera (GoPro, Osmo, Insta360, etc)"],"filming_equipment":"GoPro 11","planning_to_invest":"Yes, within the near future","years_experience":"Less than 1 year","skill_camera_settings":2,"skill_lighting":1,"skill_post_production":7,"skill_color_correction":7,"skill_storytelling":8,"skill_drone":1,"skill_over_water":8,"content_created":["Personal vacation videos","Social media content"],"btm_category":"ASPIRING PROFESSIONAL (Part-time professional aiming for full-time career)","involvement_level":"Hobby only","online_presence":"Active social media","income_from_filming":"No, not yet.","primary_goal":"Transform hobby into professional career","secondary_goal":"Document marine conservation/research","learning_aspects":["Basic equipment setup and operation","Camera settings and techniques","Lighting techniques","Marine life behavior understanding","Storytelling and content planning","Post-production and editing","Business aspects of underwater filming","Client relations and project management","Conservation documentation"],"content_to_create":["Personal/travel memories","Social media content","Documentary style films","Conservation stories"],"learning_approach":["Small group workshop (within a group of approx. 4 persons)","One-on-one mentorship","Mixed approach (combination of group and individual)","Project-based learning (within a BTM project)"],"marine_subjects":["Coral reefs","Big marine life (sharks, whales, etc.)","Marine behavior"],"time_availability":"2-3 entire weeks at a time for a workshop, aproject or individual training","travel_willingness":"Yes, willing to travel internationally","start_timeline":"Ready to start immediately","ultimate_vision":"I always want to spend more time underwater than above. Spectating UW wild life is something I could do all day and I always like to document these moments. Having the right tools, expertise and guidance will make me show what I love the most to the whole world!","inspiration_to_apply":"The absolute brilliance that Behind The Mask create of every trip they go on.","referral_source":["Flo"],"questions_or_concerns":"none"}'::jsonb, '{}', '[]'::jsonb, '2025-03-23T13:19:39+00:00');
INSERT INTO applications (program, status, user_id, answers, tags, admin_notes, submitted_at) VALUES ('filmmaking', 'reviewing', NULL, '{"first_name":"Henrique dos Santos Pedroso","nickname":"Henry","email":"Henrique.dspedroso@gmail.com","online_links":"Soultywater","age":"35-44","budget":"Moderate budget (1,000 - 3,000 €/USD)","phone":"+351 911972071","gender":"Male","nationality":"Brazilian","country_of_residence":"Portugal","languages":"English, Spanish, Portuguese","current_occupation":"Sales Consultant - Uw photo gear","physical_fitness":"Excellent - Regular exercise, no health concerns","health_conditions":"No health conditions affecting diving","diving_types":["Recreational Scuba diving","Freediving"],"certification_level":"Instructor","number_of_dives":"250+","last_dive_date":"01.02.2025","diving_environments":["Tropical Reefs","Cold water","Deep diving","Night diving","Cave/Wreck diving"],"buoyancy_skill":10,"equipment_owned":["DSLR/Mirrorless with housing"],"filming_equipment":"Canon R5, Ikelite housing, canon 8-15 and RF 100mm","planning_to_invest":"Yes, within the near future","years_experience":"Less than 1 year","skill_camera_settings":8,"skill_lighting":8,"skill_post_production":10,"skill_color_correction":8,"skill_storytelling":9,"skill_drone":10,"skill_over_water":8,"content_created":["Personal vacation videos","Social media content","Commercial work"],"btm_category":"DEDICATED ACHIEVER (Business-focused, seeking intensive mentorship)","involvement_level":"Full-time professional","online_presence":"Active social media, Personal website, Client base","income_from_filming":"Occasionally (few projects per year)","primary_goal":"Enhance existing professional skills","secondary_goal":"Document marine conservation/research","learning_aspects":["Post-production and editing","Business aspects of underwater filming","Client relations and project management"],"content_to_create":["Personal/travel memories","Social media content","Documentary style films","Commercial/advertising content","Scientific/research documentation","Conservation stories"],"learning_approach":["Group workshops (within a group of approx. 10 persons)","Small group workshop (within a group of approx. 4 persons)","One-on-one mentorship","Mixed approach (combination of group and individual)","Project-based learning (within a BTM project)"],"marine_subjects":["Coral reefs","Big marine life (sharks, whales, etc.)","Macro subjects","Marine behavior","Conservation stories"],"time_availability":"2-3 entire weeks at a time for a workshop, aproject or individual training","travel_willingness":"Yes, willing to travel internationally","start_timeline":"Ready to start immediately","ultimate_vision":"My ultimate vision for my underwater filming journey is to capture and share the raw beauty, mystery, and emotion of the underwater world in a way that inspires connection, conservation, and curiosity. I started as a UW photographer for scuba activities and then went to surfing and now I aspire to tell powerful visual stories that would help merge adventure, nature, and human interaction beneath and above the surface—filming marine wildlife in their natural habitat, documenting freediving and scuba diving cultures, or blending surf, action sports and dive lifestyles into immersive narratives.\n\nLong-term, I want to create documentaries, collaborate with marine conservation organizations, and develop a cinematic style that brings underwater experiences to global audiences through films, online platforms, and educational content. The dream is to not only shoot visually stunning footage, but to evoke feeling, provoke thought, and move people to care about the ocean as deeply as I do :)","inspiration_to_apply":"The sense of peace and connection I felt the first time I dove beneath the surface. The ocean is a world full of movement and life that often goes unseen—and I want to be the storyteller who brings that hidden beauty to light, the graceful dance of a manta ray or the silence of a freediver descending into the blue, there’s a magic in these moments.\n\nI chose BTM Academy because it aligns perfectly with my vision and values. The academy’s emphasis on storytelling, creativity, and professional development in real underwater conditions made it stand out from other programs. Also the action style videos, the way that I like. I’m excited to learn from experienced mentors who are not only technically skilled, but also passionate about crafting beautiful narratives with images underwater. BTM feels like the place to grow as both a filmmaker and an ocean advocate","referral_source":["Social Media (Instagram, Facebook, etc.)"],"questions_or_concerns":"Are you based in Portugal? That is superb","anything_else":"Thanks for this!"}'::jsonb, '{}', '[]'::jsonb, '2025-03-23T13:09:52+00:00');
INSERT INTO applications (program, status, user_id, answers, tags, admin_notes, submitted_at) VALUES ('filmmaking', 'reviewing', NULL, '{"first_name":"CAILEAN DUNKEL","nickname":"Cailean","email":"caileanskye7@gmail.com","online_links":"https://youtube.com/@cailean_underwater?si=C3ayEro3W7yx7iVF","age":"18-24","budget":"Moderate budget (1,000 - 3,000 €/USD)","phone":"07860111297","gender":"Male","nationality":"Scottish","country_of_residence":"United Kingdom","languages":"English","current_occupation":"Currently finishing school, but in May I will become a full time boat skipper","physical_fitness":"Excellent - Regular exercise, no health concerns","health_conditions":"No health conditions affecting diving","diving_types":["Recreational Scuba diving","Freediving","Snorkeling"],"certification_level":"Advanced Open Water","number_of_dives":"0-50","last_dive_date":"16.03.2025","diving_environments":["Tropical Reefs","Cold water","Night diving"],"buoyancy_skill":7,"equipment_owned":["Action camera (GoPro, Osmo, Insta360, etc)","DSLR/Mirrorless with housing"],"filming_equipment":"Sony a6400\nSigma 16mm f1.4\nSeafrogs saltedline housing","planning_to_invest":"Yes, within the near future","years_experience":"Less than 1 year","skill_camera_settings":6,"skill_lighting":3,"skill_post_production":8,"skill_color_correction":8,"skill_storytelling":5,"skill_drone":3,"skill_over_water":4,"content_created":["Personal vacation videos"],"btm_category":"BEGINNER - Creative Explorer (Just starting, hobby-focused, seeking basic skills)","involvement_level":"Hobby only","online_presence":"None of the above","income_from_filming":"No, not yet.","primary_goal":"Transform hobby into professional career","secondary_goal":"Improve content creation for social media","learning_aspects":["Lighting techniques","Storytelling and content planning","Business aspects of underwater filming","Client relations and project management"],"content_to_create":["Social media content","Documentary style films","Conservation stories"],"learning_approach":["Mixed approach (combination of group and individual)","Project-based learning (within a BTM project)"],"marine_subjects":["Big marine life (sharks, whales, etc.)","Conservation stories"],"time_availability":"2-3 entire weeks at a time for a workshop, aproject or individual training","travel_willingness":"Yes, willing to travel internationally","start_timeline":"Ready to start immediately","ultimate_vision":"One day I hope u underwater filmmaking will be my full time career but I still have a very long way to go, at the moment I’m focusing on the basics of mainly photography but video is my true goal I have made a few videos in the past and understand they are not the best. In the summer when working on the boat I will be working on I am planning to make a small film on the struggles of puffins where I live, luckily I have almost unlimited access to them so I hope I can make a good film to build my portfolio, and when the puffins start moving away I am planning to make another short film about underwater life around the Isle of Skye this will hopefully include dolphins, many types of whales and basking sharks. \n\nThankyou very much for this opportunity to be apart of your academy!!","inspiration_to_apply":"I have been watching your channel for about 2 years now and always dreamed to do exactly what BTM do so as soon as this opportunity arised I had to give it a shot","referral_source":["Social Media (Instagram, Facebook, etc.)"]}'::jsonb, '{}', '[]'::jsonb, '2025-03-23T12:37:02+00:00');
INSERT INTO applications (program, status, user_id, answers, tags, admin_notes, submitted_at) VALUES ('filmmaking', 'reviewing', NULL, '{"first_name":"Arnau Argemi Gonzalez","nickname":"Arnau","email":"arnauargon@gmail.com","online_links":"Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/arnauargon/, Website: https://arnauargon.com/, LinkedIn: https://www.linkedin.com/in/arnau-argemi-gonzalez/","age":"25-34","budget":"Professional budget (6,000 - 12,000 €/USD)","phone":"+34 638855747","gender":"Male","nationality":"Spanish","country_of_residence":"Spain","languages":"English, Spanish","current_occupation":"Underwater Cinematographer","physical_fitness":"Excellent - Regular exercise, no health concerns","health_conditions":"No health conditions affecting diving","diving_types":["Recreational Scuba diving","Technical Scuba diving","Rebreather diving","Freediving"],"certification_level":"Divemaster, Technical Diving certification, Certified Freediver","number_of_dives":"250+","last_dive_date":"23.03.2025","diving_environments":["Tropical Reefs","Cold water","Deep diving","Night diving","Cave/Wreck diving"],"buoyancy_skill":10,"equipment_owned":["Action camera (GoPro, Osmo, Insta360, etc)","DSLR/Mirrorless with housing","Professional video camera","Lighting equipment"],"filming_equipment":"RED Raptor X, Nauticam RED Raptor Housing, Nauticam Monitor, Canon 15-35mm f/2.8, Canon 24-70mm f/2.8, Canon 28-70mm f/3.5-4.5 + Nauticam WACP-1B, 2x Sony A7SIII, Nauticam Sony A7SIII, Sony 28-60mm f/4-5.6 + Nauticam WWL-1B, Nikonos 15mm f/2.8, Ninja V Monitor, Nauticam Ninja V Housing Housing, GoPro 10, Insta360 X3, 2x Scubalamp V7K Pro, DJI Mavic 3 Pro","planning_to_invest":"Yes, within the near future","years_experience":"3-5 years","skill_camera_settings":9,"skill_lighting":8,"skill_post_production":9,"skill_color_correction":9,"skill_storytelling":7,"skill_drone":8,"skill_over_water":9,"content_created":["Social media content","Documentary style","Commercial work","Scientific/Research documentation"],"btm_category":"DEDICATED ACHIEVER (Business-focused, seeking intensive mentorship)","involvement_level":"Full-time professional","online_presence":"Active social media, Personal website, Professional portfolio, Client base","income_from_filming":"Full-time income","primary_goal":"Enhance existing professional skills","secondary_goal":"Document marine conservation/research","learning_aspects":["Lighting techniques","Marine life behavior understanding","Storytelling and content planning","Post-production and editing","Business aspects of underwater filming","Client relations and project management","Conservation documentation"],"content_to_create":["Social media content","Documentary style films","Commercial/advertising content","Conservation stories"],"learning_approach":["One-on-one mentorship","Project-based learning (within a BTM project)"],"marine_subjects":["Coral reefs","Big marine life (sharks, whales, etc.)","Marine behavior","Conservation stories"],"time_availability":"2-3 entire weeks at a time for a workshop, aproject or individual training","travel_willingness":"Yes, willing to travel internationally","start_timeline":"Ready to start immediately","ultimate_vision":"My ultimate vision for my underwater filming journey is to become a Director of Photography for both wildlife documentaries and high-end commercial productions, with a strong focus on stories that connect people to the ocean. I want to combine creative cinematography with meaningful narratives that raise awareness and appreciation for the underwater world and its conservation. Whether capturing unique behaviors of marine wildlife, documenting conservation efforts, or shooting commercial content that reflects a brand’s relationship with the sea, I aim to bring a cinematic, story-driven approach to every project. I see underwater filmmaking as my lifelong career and a way to contribute to ocean conservation through compelling, industry-leading visual storytelling.","inspiration_to_apply":"I discovered Behind the Mask through your YouTube channel years ago, and what stood out to me immediately was the way your films feel intimate and intentional. Your ability to blend cinematography with personal, honest narratives like with \"Jo In the Blue\" really resonated with me. Watching your work made me reflect on my own approach to storytelling and pushed me to think deeper about how I connect stories to visuals. That inspiration is what led me to apply to this BTM Academy program. I want to learn from a team that not only values technical skill, but also has a clear voice and emotional depth in their storytelling.","referral_source":["Social Media (Instagram, Facebook, etc.)"],"questions_or_concerns":"I would love to know more about how participants are supported after the program ends. Will there be any future opportunities with Behind the Mask after the program?","anything_else":"Yes! This year I’m working on two upcoming productions that are part of the continuation of a project called Waves of Tomorrow, which I began last year in collaboration with Bluewave Alliance. These episodes will continue to explore success stories of marine protected areas in the Mediterranean Sea, building on the visual and narrative style we developed in the first episode. I’m excited to keep pushing the boundaries of my storytelling, both technically and emotionally. I believe that being part of the BTM Academy would be the perfect way to enhance my skills further and bring even more creativity into these kinds of projects."}'::jsonb, '{}', '[]'::jsonb, '2025-03-23T12:21:55+00:00');
INSERT INTO applications (program, status, user_id, answers, tags, admin_notes, submitted_at) VALUES ('filmmaking', 'reviewing', NULL, '{"first_name":"Remy Allemann","email":"remyallemann@msn.com","online_links":"https://wendyholdener-my.sharepoint.com/:f:/g/personal/info_wendyholdener_ch/EkDF8_2vutpGu4nSeWLcdC8B9svB6jq5jHJ1iQM9lgAmXA?e=cVQNG8","age":"25-34","budget":"Advanced budget (3,000 - 6,000 €/USD)","phone":"+41799571747","gender":"Male","nationality":"Swiss","country_of_residence":"Switzerland","languages":"English, French, German, Italian","current_occupation":"Sportsmanagement / Agent","physical_fitness":"Excellent - Regular exercise, no health concerns","health_conditions":"No health conditions affecting diving","diving_types":["Recreational Scuba diving","Freediving","Snorkeling"],"certification_level":"Divemaster","number_of_dives":"250+","last_dive_date":"24.01.2025","diving_environments":["Tropical Reefs","Night diving","Cave/Wreck diving"],"buoyancy_skill":10,"equipment_owned":["Professional video camera"],"filming_equipment":"Sony FX30 with Nauticam FX3 housing and Dome port.","planning_to_invest":"Yes, within the next years","years_experience":"1-3 years","skill_camera_settings":4,"skill_lighting":1,"skill_post_production":4,"skill_color_correction":1,"skill_storytelling":5,"skill_drone":1,"skill_over_water":3,"content_created":["Personal vacation videos"],"btm_category":"DEDICATED ACHIEVER (Business-focused, seeking intensive mentorship)","involvement_level":"Have worked on professional productions but only as safety diver and helping hand on boats.","online_presence":"None of the above","income_from_filming":"No, not yet.","primary_goal":"Transform hobby into professional career","secondary_goal":"Document marine conservation/research","learning_aspects":["Camera settings and techniques","Lighting techniques","Marine life behavior understanding","Post-production and editing"],"content_to_create":["Social media content","Documentary style films","Conservation stories"],"learning_approach":["One-on-one mentorship","Project-based learning (within a BTM project)"],"marine_subjects":["Big marine life (sharks, whales, etc.)","Marine behavior"],"time_availability":"2-3 entire weeks at a time for a workshop, aproject or individual training","travel_willingness":"Yes, willing to travel internationally","start_timeline":"Ready to start immediately","ultimate_vision":"My dream is to get back into diving a lot more again. I used to work as a dive guide but then got sucked into corporate life here in Europe. I have quit my job in January this year and have now a 60% job with a very flexible work schedule. My dream is to be able to go dove the rest of my time, learn from and about the ocean as well as film the breathtaking things I see underwater in order to share, so more people care about conserving our beautiful and crucial underwater eco systems.","inspiration_to_apply":"Your Youtube video \"Cocos - island of sharks\" played a big role in my latest changes in life and I''ve watched a lot of your \"how to\" videos about filming. When the BTM academy was announced, I immediatly wanted to apply.","referral_source":["Social Media (Instagram, Facebook, etc.)"],"questions_or_concerns":"Not at this moment.","anything_else":"Can''t wait to get in touch."}'::jsonb, '{}', '[]'::jsonb, '2025-03-23T12:03:42+00:00');
INSERT INTO applications (program, status, user_id, answers, tags, admin_notes, submitted_at) VALUES ('filmmaking', 'reviewing', NULL, '{"first_name":"Molly Knox","email":"mindfuldiving.co@gmail.com","online_links":"https://mindfuldiving.com/\nhttps://www.instagram.com/mindful_diving/\nhttps://www.tiktok.com/@mindful.diving\nhttps://www.pinterest.com/mindful_diving/","age":"25-34","budget":"Small budget (under 1,000 €/USD)","phone":"+17178179774","gender":"Female","nationality":"USA","country_of_residence":"USA","languages":"English, Spanish","current_occupation":"Freelance paid social specialist","physical_fitness":"Excellent - Regular exercise, no health concerns","health_conditions":"No health conditions affecting diving","diving_types":["Recreational Scuba diving"],"certification_level":"Open Water, Advanced Open Water, Rescue Diver","number_of_dives":"51-250","last_dive_date":"31.12.2024","diving_environments":["Tropical Reefs","Cold water","Deep diving","Night diving"],"buoyancy_skill":8,"equipment_owned":["Action camera (GoPro, Osmo, Insta360, etc)"],"filming_equipment":"GoPro Hero 8 with housing and filters... that''s all","planning_to_invest":"Yes, within the next years","years_experience":"Less than 1 year","skill_camera_settings":5,"skill_lighting":3,"skill_post_production":4,"skill_color_correction":3,"skill_storytelling":5,"skill_drone":1,"skill_over_water":1,"content_created":["Personal vacation videos","Social media content"],"btm_category":"BEGINNER - Creative Explorer (Just starting, hobby-focused, seeking basic skills)","involvement_level":"Hobby only","online_presence":"Active social media, Personal website","income_from_filming":"No, not yet.","primary_goal":"Improve content creation for social media","secondary_goal":"Transform hobby into professional career","learning_aspects":["Basic equipment setup and operation","Camera settings and techniques","Lighting techniques","Storytelling and content planning","Post-production and editing","Conservation documentation"],"content_to_create":["Personal/travel memories","Social media content","Conservation stories"],"learning_approach":["Mixed approach (combination of group and individual)","Project-based learning (within a BTM project)"],"marine_subjects":["Coral reefs","Marine behavior","Conservation stories"],"time_availability":"1 week to 10 days for a workshop, a project or individual training","travel_willingness":"Depends on duration and location","start_timeline":"Flexible/Not sure yet","ultimate_vision":"I''m just starting to take my underwater filming seriously. I''ve only been scuba diving since 2022 and since then, I feel like I''ve come a long way from filming every single second to only capturing simple moments. What I want to share are the peaceful underwater moments that invoke introspection and show the beauty of the underwater world. Additionally, I also want to share conservation stories and help build awareness of marine conservation efforts. I''m starting my divemaster training with a marine conservation specialty, and here''s where I''m hoping to learn more and be able to share more educational content. My goal with Mindful Diving is to share mindful diving tips and techniques and help divers to be more present underwater because I feel like a lot of divers these days are only underwater to get a video of macro life. And while I also love a good shark, whale, manta ray sighting, there''s so much more to the ocean and more to appreciate about it. Lastly, I''m hoping to boost my skills to help with marketing efforts and work for a dive shop and/or marine conservation organization.","inspiration_to_apply":"Honestly, seeing that Florian was not only a filmmaker, but also an advertiser. I also worked in advertising and one of the reasons why I wanted to transition my career out of it is because I had pivotal moment while traveling that I realized I wasn''t advertising \"for good.\" One of the things that bothers me about US and western culture is the consumerism and materialism, and, as an advertiser for consumer product goods, I realized I was contributing to that problem. So I loved seeing someone with a similar background who is using for good, to spread awareness, and share unique stories. Ultimately, I hope to do the same.","referral_source":["Social Media (Instagram, Facebook, etc.)"],"questions_or_concerns":"I think my biggest concern will be financial. I''m open to traveling anywhere really, depending on time and location, and am flexible with starting after 5/21 (that''s when my divemaster ends) but please note, I have to be budget conscious at the moment.","anything_else":"Not at the moment (:"}'::jsonb, '{}', '[]'::jsonb, '2025-03-23T12:01:38+00:00');
INSERT INTO applications (program, status, user_id, answers, tags, admin_notes, submitted_at) VALUES ('filmmaking', 'reviewing', NULL, '{"first_name":"Weining Wang","nickname":"Chelsea","email":"wangchelsea948@gmail.com","online_links":"https://www.instagram.com/chelsea__scuba?igsh=bjUwdDVwa2p6aXQz&utm_source=qr","age":"25-34","budget":"Small budget (under 1,000 €/USD)","phone":"+886985108184","gender":"Female","nationality":"Taiwan","country_of_residence":"Thailand (at the moment)","languages":"English, Mandarin","current_occupation":"Diving Instructor","physical_fitness":"Excellent - Regular exercise, no health concerns","health_conditions":"No health conditions affecting diving","diving_types":["Recreational Scuba diving"],"certification_level":"Instructor","number_of_dives":"250+","last_dive_date":"23.03.2025","diving_environments":["Tropical Reefs","Deep diving","Night diving","Cave/Wreck diving"],"buoyancy_skill":10,"equipment_owned":["Action camera (GoPro, Osmo, Insta360, etc)","DSLR/Mirrorless with housing","Lighting equipment"],"filming_equipment":"Sony a6300 with sea frog housing, AOI wide angle dome lens, a weefine 07 ring strobe. Planning on getting an orca torch D910V video light soon","planning_to_invest":"Yes, within the near future","years_experience":"Less than 1 year","skill_camera_settings":3,"skill_lighting":3,"skill_post_production":3,"skill_color_correction":3,"skill_storytelling":4,"skill_drone":1,"skill_over_water":4,"content_created":["Personal vacation videos","Social media content"],"btm_category":"BEGINNER - Creative Explorer (Just starting, hobby-focused, seeking basic skills)","involvement_level":"Hobby only","online_presence":"Active social media","income_from_filming":"No, thats not my goal.","primary_goal":"Transform hobby into professional career","secondary_goal":"Document marine conservation/research","learning_aspects":["Basic equipment setup and operation","Camera settings and techniques","Lighting techniques","Marine life behavior understanding","Storytelling and content planning","Post-production and editing","Conservation documentation"],"content_to_create":["Personal/travel memories","Social media content","Documentary style films","Scientific/research documentation","Conservation stories"],"learning_approach":["Small group workshop (within a group of approx. 4 persons)","One-on-one mentorship","Mixed approach (combination of group and individual)","Project-based learning (within a BTM project)"],"marine_subjects":["Coral reefs","Big marine life (sharks, whales, etc.)","Marine behavior","Conservation stories"],"time_availability":"2-3 entire weeks at a time for a workshop, aproject or individual training","travel_willingness":"Depends on duration and location","start_timeline":"Within next 3 months","ultimate_vision":"Wow umm ok so eventually I’d like to be a professional videographer but not only that I’d like to learn how to create cinematic style videos to tell stories either about a project or marine conservation works. I wanna be able to travel around and film these marine animals and their behaviors and be able to influence the public through compelling storytelling to raise awareness for ocean conservation.\n\nPrevious pages on the survey it asked me to choose what category fits me the most, and I’m a beginner but aiming to become professional and perhaps more!!\n\nI bought my second hand camera housing from my friend last year, took it to the Maldives and played around with it when diving with the tiger sharks. And on the same trip I also met a few professional photographers and videographers. Right then and there I was immediately hooked and couldn’t stop thinking about becoming one myself.\n\nAfter that I started slowly investing in equipment as being a diving instructor in Thailand doesn’t necessarily make banks, so this is where I struggle. I’m trying to work as much as I can to save money but then I don’t have time to practice photography videography or take classes and apply them practically. And if I spent a huge amount of money on equipment then I don’t have money to take courses or travel to do workshops.\n\nI feel stuck. I was feeling so frustrated cause this is what I really wanna do. Become a professional videographer and be able to travel to places and film these fantastic marine life and there behaviors. Then I watched ALIVE when it came out and it literally brought me to tears!!\n\nAll I know was I wanna be able to do THAT. Create films that move, and influence people and potentially give them hope or inspirations.","inspiration_to_apply":"Your content is top notch!! Sorry I think i kinda answered this question in my previous answer. Apologies. I love watching all your videos I found you guys through YouTube when I first started diving professionally. And I just thought it’d be a dream to learn from people like these guys and then there I saw you guys posted the academy program thing and I immediately applied for it!","referral_source":["Social Media (Instagram, Facebook, etc.)"],"questions_or_concerns":"For me it’s all just money really I’m so willing to commit. I’m just strying to save as I continue this very expensive but fulfilling journey","anything_else":"I’m so nervous! To learn from guys like you all!! And so afraid I don’t make it or not gonna cut it but if I never try I never know so here goes. Thanks for reading. Cheers!"}'::jsonb, '{}', '[]'::jsonb, '2025-03-23T10:44:07+00:00');
INSERT INTO applications (program, status, user_id, answers, tags, admin_notes, submitted_at) VALUES ('filmmaking', 'reviewing', NULL, '{"first_name":"LENA Pierre-Dominique","email":"pierdomlena@yahoo.fr","online_links":"@pierredopido","age":"35-44","budget":"All-In budget (>12,000 €/USD)","phone":"+33664706069","gender":"Male","nationality":"FRENCH","country_of_residence":"FRANCE","languages":"English, French","current_occupation":"cameraman","physical_fitness":"Good - Moderately active, no major health concerns","health_conditions":"No health conditions affecting diving","diving_types":["Recreational Scuba diving","Technical Scuba diving","Rebreather diving","Snorkeling","commercial diving"],"certification_level":"CMAS 3 stars / rebreather / commercial diving CAH 2B  ( French certification )","number_of_dives":"51-250","last_dive_date":"15.01.2025","diving_environments":["Tropical Reefs","Cold water","Deep diving","Night diving","13°C water / 60 meters deep"],"buoyancy_skill":8,"equipment_owned":["Action camera (GoPro, Osmo, Insta360, etc)","DSLR/Mirrorless with housing","Professional video camera","Lighting equipment"],"filming_equipment":"Sony AS3 and Nauticam Housing, 16-35/24-70/90 macro Lens // 2 *10000 lumens light","planning_to_invest":"Yes, within the near future","years_experience":"1-3 years","skill_camera_settings":6,"skill_lighting":4,"skill_post_production":4,"skill_color_correction":6,"skill_storytelling":3,"skill_drone":10,"skill_over_water":10,"content_created":["Personal vacation videos","Social media content","Commercial work"],"btm_category":"ASPIRING PROFESSIONAL (Part-time professional aiming for full-time career)","involvement_level":"Part-time professional","online_presence":"Active social media","income_from_filming":"Occasionally (few projects per year)","primary_goal":"Enhance existing professional skills","secondary_goal":"Document marine conservation/research","learning_aspects":["Lighting techniques","Marine life behavior understanding","Storytelling and content planning","Post-production and editing","Business aspects of underwater filming","Client relations and project management","Conservation documentation"],"content_to_create":["Documentary style films","Commercial/advertising content","Scientific/research documentation","Conservation stories"],"learning_approach":["One-on-one mentorship","Mixed approach (combination of group and individual)","Project-based learning (within a BTM project)"],"marine_subjects":["Marine behavior","Conservation stories"],"time_availability":"2-3 entire weeks at a time for a workshop, aproject or individual training","travel_willingness":"Depends on duration and location","start_timeline":"Ready to start immediately","ultimate_vision":"learn professional tips, filming and lighting underwater, work on a pro documentary","inspiration_to_apply":"let try","referral_source":["Social Media (Instagram, Facebook, etc.)"]}'::jsonb, '{}', '[]'::jsonb, '2025-03-23T10:35:40+00:00');
INSERT INTO applications (program, status, user_id, answers, tags, admin_notes, submitted_at) VALUES ('photography', 'reviewing', NULL, '{"first_name":"Devin","last_name":"Lucas","email":"lucasdevin856@gmail.com","online_links":"Instagram @devinclucas","age":"18-24","budget":"Advanced budget (3,000 - 6,000 €/USD)","phone":"6509466314","gender":"Male","nationality":"USA","country_of_residence":"USA","languages":"English","current_occupation":"Student (software engineer)","physical_fitness":"Excellent - Regular exercise, no health concerns","health_conditions":"No health conditions affecting diving","diving_types":["Recreational Scuba diving","Technical Scuba diving","Freediving","Snorkeling"],"certification_level":"Open Water, Advanced Open Water, Rescue Diver","number_of_dives":"250+","last_dive_date":"06.01.2026","diving_environments":["Tropical Reefs","Cold water","Deep diving","Night diving","Cave/Wreck diving"],"buoyancy_skill":10,"equipment_owned":["Action camera (GoPro, Osmo, Insta360, etc)"],"photography_equipment":"Insta360 X4 w/ dive case (Dad has a Nikon with submersion case + lighting I have used before)","planning_to_invest":"Yes, within the near future","years_experience":"3-5 years","skill_camera_settings":6,"skill_lighting":4,"skill_post_production":8,"skill_color_correction":6,"skill_composition":4,"skill_drone":4,"skill_over_water":5,"content_created":["Personal vacation photography","Social media content"],"btm_category":"ASPIRING PROFESSIONAL (Part-time professional aiming for full-time career)","involvement_level":"Hobby only","online_presence":"Active social media","income_from_photography":"No, not yet.","primary_goal":"Transform hobby into professional career","secondary_goal":"Improve content creation for social media","learning_aspects":["Camera settings and techniques","Lighting techniques"],"content_to_create":["Personal/travel memories","Social media content","Documentary style photo series","Commercial/advertising content","Scientific/research documentation","Conservation stories","Any and all types of content."],"learning_approach":["Group workshops (within a group of approx. 10 persons)","Small group workshop (within a group of approx. 4 persons)","One-on-one mentorship","Mixed approach (combination of group and individual)","Project-based learning (within a BTM project)"],"marine_subjects":["Big marine life (sharks, whales, etc.)","Macro subjects"],"time_availability":"2-3 entire weeks at a time for a workshop, aproject or individual training","travel_willingness":"Yes, willing to travel internationally","start_timeline":"Flexible/Not sure yet","ultimate_vision":"I just want to convey my experiences to the best of my ability to convince as many people as possible to get into the ocean/protect it.","inspiration_to_apply":"I have been diving since I was 10, taking photos/videos since I was ~14. You have a sick instagram ad. I just came back from diving in Ishigaki and now I’m sitting around 300 total dives. I need more!","referral_source":["Social Media (Instagram, Facebook, etc.)"],"questions_or_concerns":"I’m looking to make a camera + housing + UW lighting purchase soon. What would your recommendations be for someone transitioning from an action cam to a more traditional setup?","anything_else":"You’re gonna get people with more experience/money with/for UW photo/video, but not more passion."}'::jsonb, '{}', '[]'::jsonb, '2026-01-29T23:34:56+00:00');
INSERT INTO applications (program, status, user_id, answers, tags, admin_notes, submitted_at) VALUES ('photography', 'reviewing', NULL, '{"first_name":"Patryk","last_name":"Romańczuk","email":"patryk.romanczuk@gmail.com","online_links":"https://www.instagram.com/patryk_romanczuk/\nhttps://www.youtube.com/@PatrykRomanczuk\nhttps://instagram.com/romanczuk.waterart\nhttp://romanczuk.art/","age":"25-34","budget":"Advanced budget (3,000 - 6,000 €/USD)","phone":"+48511714983","gender":"Male","nationality":"Poland","country_of_residence":"Poland","languages":"English","physical_fitness":"Excellent - Regular exercise, no health concerns","health_conditions":"No health conditions affecting diving","diving_types":["Recreational Scuba diving","Freediving","Snorkeling"],"certification_level":"Open Water, Advanced Open Water, Certified Freediver, please specify level below:, SSI Free 20","number_of_dives":"51-250","last_dive_date":"05.12.2025","diving_environments":["Tropical Reefs","Night diving","Cave/Wreck diving"],"buoyancy_skill":8,"equipment_owned":["DSLR/Mirrorless with housing"],"photography_equipment":"Sony A7III in Seafrogs Housing with 6\" Dome. Mostly shooting with Tamron 17-28 f2.8 lens. But I''m regularly changing my lens lineup","planning_to_invest":"Yes, within the near future","years_experience":"1-3 years","skill_camera_settings":10,"skill_lighting":8,"skill_post_production":9,"skill_color_correction":8,"skill_composition":10,"skill_drone":7,"skill_over_water":10,"content_created":["Social media content","I mostly created photoshoot with models on cruises organised by me. Mostly model posing","a bit of fashion."],"btm_category":"INDEPENDENT CREATOR (Experienced hobbyist/influencer seeking improvement)","involvement_level":"Hobby only","online_presence":"Active social media, Personal website, Professional portfolio","income_from_photography":"Occasionally (few projects per year)","primary_goal":"Improve content creation for social media","secondary_goal":"Enhance existing professional skills","learning_aspects":["Camera settings and techniques","Lighting techniques","Marine life behavior understanding","Composition and content planning","Post-production and editing","Business aspects of underwater photography"],"content_to_create":["Social media content","Freediving models with marine life would be absolute dream. But everything artistic underwater is a catch for me."],"learning_approach":["Small group workshop (within a group of approx. 4 persons)","One-on-one mentorship","Mixed approach (combination of group and individual)","Project-based learning (within a BTM project)"],"marine_subjects":["Big marine life (sharks, whales, etc.)","Marine behavior"],"time_availability":"2-3 entire weeks at a time for a workshop, aproject or individual training","travel_willingness":"Yes, willing to travel internationally","start_timeline":"Flexible/Not sure yet","ultimate_vision":"I feel like I''ve done a lot above water. I''ve been working with models for years. Underwater photography is my two worlds collapsing into one. I love water - it has been a part of my life fromy my early years as a child. I love exploring, swimming, diving, sailing - anything around the water. \n\nI would like to share with the world the beauty of the oceans through artistic vision while sailing from place to place to witness the wonders of the nature. I''m constantly stunned with new things I learn about marine life which would be a dream of mine to incorporate into my artistic work. If any of it will bring preservation awarness or just more atention to sea-life - that''s even better for me.","inspiration_to_apply":"I learned quite a lot from Your YT. And I really feel connected to the works that You are presenting as They closely match what I would like to see coming from me as well.","referral_source":["Social Media (Instagram, Facebook, etc.)"],"anything_else":"Yes! My wife is also applying to Freediving performance program :) We are both creators, she''s my no.1 underwater model. \n\nWe are currently organising photo trips on our own where we charter catamaran and invite mostly non-underwater photographers and models to at least try a bit of this world with us."}'::jsonb, '{}', '[]'::jsonb, '2026-02-02T13:57:24+00:00');
INSERT INTO applications (program, status, user_id, answers, tags, admin_notes, submitted_at) VALUES ('photography', 'reviewing', NULL, '{"first_name":"Miguel","last_name":"Valladares","email":"valladaresmiguel@gmail.com","online_links":"@miguelvalladares_","age":"35-44","budget":"All-In budget (>12,000 €/USD)","nickname":"Mike","phone":"524448290331","gender":"Male","nationality":"Mexico/Spain","country_of_residence":"Mexico","languages":"English, Spanish","physical_fitness":"Good - Moderately active, no major health concerns","health_conditions":"No health conditions affecting diving","diving_types":["Recreational Scuba diving","Snorkeling"],"certification_level":"Divemaster","number_of_dives":"250+","last_dive_date":"22.12.2025","diving_environments":["Tropical Reefs","Deep diving","Night diving","Cave/Wreck diving","Photography"],"buoyancy_skill":10,"equipment_owned":["Action camera (GoPro, Osmo, Insta360, etc)","DSLR/Mirrorless with housing","Professional photo/video camera","Lighting equipment"],"photography_equipment":"Nikon D850, Nauticam Housing, Inon z330 strobes, macro and wide angle ports, gopro, subaqua and fix neo lights.","planning_to_invest":"Yes, within the near future","years_experience":"5+ years","skill_camera_settings":8,"skill_lighting":8,"skill_post_production":6,"skill_color_correction":7,"skill_composition":8,"skill_drone":5,"skill_over_water":7,"content_created":["Social media content"],"btm_category":"INDEPENDENT CREATOR (Experienced hobbyist/influencer seeking improvement)","involvement_level":"Part-time professional","online_presence":"Active social media","income_from_photography":"No, not yet.","primary_goal":"Transform hobby into professional career","secondary_goal":"Document marine conservation/research","learning_aspects":["Lighting techniques","Marine life behavior understanding","Composition and content planning","Post-production and editing","Business aspects of underwater photography","Client relations and project management","Conservation documentation"],"content_to_create":["Documentary style photo series","Commercial/advertising content","Scientific/research documentation"],"learning_approach":["Group workshops (within a group of approx. 10 persons)","Small group workshop (within a group of approx. 4 persons)","One-on-one mentorship","Mixed approach (combination of group and individual)","Project-based learning (within a BTM project)"],"marine_subjects":["Coral reefs","Big marine life (sharks, whales, etc.)","Macro subjects","Marine behavior","Conservation stories"],"time_availability":"1 week to 10 days for a workshop, a project or individual training","travel_willingness":"Depends on duration and location","start_timeline":"Flexible/Not sure yet","ultimate_vision":"my ultimate vision is to evolve into a highly skilled respected underwater photographer and videographer, capable of telling powerful visual stories about the ocean and its wildlife. i have always been deeply passionate about diving, the sea, and marine animals, and my goal is to translate that passion into technically strong, compelling imagery.","inspiration_to_apply":"I was inspired by your social media and youtube videos, your strong reputation for combining technical mastering, real-world experience, and mentorship learning. I am highly motivated to improve every aspect of my underwater photography and filmmaking, and I believe BTM offers the structured environment and high standards needed to accelerate that growth.","referral_source":["Social Media (Instagram, Facebook, etc.)"],"questions_or_concerns":"Is it mostly freediving or scuba diving as well? do you have equipment available to try for different kinds of shooting or Ill be using only what I own? will there be any zoom or virtual 1-1 clases?"}'::jsonb, '{}', '[]'::jsonb, '2026-01-21T16:50:45+00:00');
INSERT INTO applications (program, status, user_id, answers, tags, admin_notes, submitted_at) VALUES ('photography', 'reviewing', NULL, '{"first_name":"Sergey","last_name":"Dolgopolov","email":"dolgopolovsergey@gmail.com","age":"54+","budget":"All-In budget (>12,000 €/USD)","phone":"+38269109001","gender":"Male","nationality":"Montenegrin, Russian","country_of_residence":"Montenegro","languages":"English","current_occupation":"Manager","physical_fitness":"Excellent - Regular exercise, no health concerns","health_conditions":"No health conditions affecting diving","diving_types":["Recreational Scuba diving"],"certification_level":"Advanced Open Water","number_of_dives":"51-250","last_dive_date":"13.12.2025","diving_environments":["Tropical Reefs","Deep diving","Night diving"],"buoyancy_skill":8,"equipment_owned":["DSLR/Mirrorless with housing"],"photography_equipment":"Canon R5 with housing, RF 16-35, RF 100 macro","planning_to_invest":"Yes, within the near future","years_experience":"Less than 1 year","skill_camera_settings":7,"skill_lighting":5,"skill_post_production":8,"skill_color_correction":7,"skill_composition":6,"skill_drone":1,"skill_over_water":8,"content_created":["Personal vacation photography"],"btm_category":"BEGINNER - Creative Explorer (Just starting, hobby-focused, seeking basic skills)","involvement_level":"Hobby only","online_presence":"None of the above","income_from_photography":"No, thats not my goal.","primary_goal":"Learn basics of underwater photography as a hobby","secondary_goal":"Learn basics of underwater photography as a hobby","learning_aspects":["Lighting techniques","Marine life behavior understanding","Composition and content planning","Post-production and editing"],"content_to_create":["Personal/travel memories","Documentary style photo series"],"learning_approach":["Small group workshop (within a group of approx. 4 persons)","One-on-one mentorship","Mixed approach (combination of group and individual)"],"marine_subjects":["Coral reefs","Big marine life (sharks, whales, etc.)","Macro subjects"],"time_availability":"1 week to 10 days for a workshop, a project or individual training","travel_willingness":"Yes, willing to travel internationally","start_timeline":"Within next 6 months","ultimate_vision":"Photografy and water is my hobby from my childhood. Recently I have started diving (Egypt, Maldives) and opened for myself new world. It just captivares me. I would like  to achieve a professional level of photography, but as a hobby. Well...., and perhaps to participate in exhibitions.","inspiration_to_apply":"Florian''s Fisher performance at Dusseldorf Boat Show exhibition","referral_source":["Dusseldorf Boat show"]}'::jsonb, '{}', '[]'::jsonb, '2026-01-24T18:38:48+00:00');
INSERT INTO applications (program, status, user_id, answers, tags, admin_notes, submitted_at) VALUES ('photography', 'reviewing', NULL, '{"first_name":"NICOLA","last_name":"MARGIESON","email":"nschellander@hotmail.com","online_links":"https://www.instagram.com/nicky_freediver/","age":"45-54","budget":"Moderate budget (1,000 - 3,000 €/USD)","nickname":"NICKY","phone":"07828422029","gender":"Female","nationality":"BRITISH","country_of_residence":"UK","languages":"English, French","current_occupation":"ARTIST, DESIGNER AND HORSE TRAINER","physical_fitness":"VERY ACTIVE AND REGULAR EXERCISE.REMISSION FROM CANCER.","health_conditions":"Yes, but cleared by doctor for diving","diving_types":["Recreational Scuba diving","Freediving","Snorkeling"],"certification_level":"Open Water, Advanced Open Water, Certified Freediver, please specify level below:, SSI LEVEL 2","number_of_dives":"250+","last_dive_date":"14.10.2025","diving_environments":["Tropical Reefs","Cold water","Deep diving","Night diving","Cave/Wreck diving"],"buoyancy_skill":10,"equipment_owned":["Action camera (GoPro, Osmo, Insta360, etc)"],"photography_equipment":"GOPRO 11","planning_to_invest":"Yes, within the near future","years_experience":"Less than 1 year","skill_camera_settings":7,"skill_lighting":2,"skill_post_production":8,"skill_color_correction":8,"skill_composition":5,"skill_drone":1,"skill_over_water":5,"content_created":["Personal vacation photography","Social media content"],"btm_category":"OCEAN STEWARD (NGO/scientific focus, conservation-driven)","involvement_level":"Hobby only","online_presence":"Active social media","income_from_photography":"No, not yet.","primary_goal":"Transform hobby into professional career","secondary_goal":"Document marine conservation/research","learning_aspects":["Basic equipment setup and operation","Camera settings and techniques","Lighting techniques","Marine life behavior understanding","Composition and content planning","Post-production and editing","Business aspects of underwater photography","Client relations and project management","Conservation documentation"],"content_to_create":["Personal/travel memories","Social media content","Documentary style photo series","Commercial/advertising content","Scientific/research documentation","Conservation stories"],"learning_approach":["Group workshops (within a group of approx. 10 persons)","Small group workshop (within a group of approx. 4 persons)","One-on-one mentorship","Mixed approach (combination of group and individual)"],"marine_subjects":["Big marine life (sharks, whales, etc.)","Marine behavior","Conservation stories"],"time_availability":"1 week to 10 days for a workshop, a project or individual training","travel_willingness":"Yes, willing to travel internationally","start_timeline":"Ready to start immediately","ultimate_vision":"I would love to be able to capture moments of freedivers, in training and in competition. And also offer marine-based services visually in some way. I am also passionate about hopefully assisting/helping organisations such as Seashepherd, providing key visuals and information and research as visual images.","inspiration_to_apply":"It looks very interesting and is hopefully the way I start out on a new venture.","referral_source":["Diving community"],"questions_or_concerns":"-","anything_else":"I have quite a bit of time on my hands to dedicate to this and am flexible in terms of lifestyle and travel."}'::jsonb, '{}', '[]'::jsonb, '2026-01-27T14:10:01+00:00');
INSERT INTO applications (program, status, user_id, answers, tags, admin_notes, submitted_at) VALUES ('photography', 'reviewing', NULL, '{"first_name":"Mahsa","last_name":"Mirza","email":"m.mirzamo@gmail.com","online_links":"Instagram.com/mahsamim","age":"35-44","budget":"Moderate budget (1,000 - 3,000 €/USD)","phone":"4088320033","gender":"Female","nationality":"Iranian American","country_of_residence":"USA","languages":"English, Persian","current_occupation":"Software engineer","physical_fitness":"Excellent - Regular exercise, no health concerns","health_conditions":"No health conditions affecting diving","diving_types":["Recreational Scuba diving","Snorkeling"],"certification_level":"Advanced Open Water","number_of_dives":"51-250","last_dive_date":"06.01.2026","diving_environments":["Tropical Reefs","Deep diving","Night diving"],"buoyancy_skill":8,"equipment_owned":["Action camera (GoPro, Osmo, Insta360, etc)","DSLR/Mirrorless with housing"],"photography_equipment":"Gopro hero13, Sony a7riii with seafrogs housing, Sony 16-35 f5 lens, drone","planning_to_invest":"Yes, within the near future","years_experience":"None","skill_camera_settings":7,"skill_lighting":1,"skill_post_production":7,"skill_color_correction":6,"skill_composition":7,"skill_drone":1,"skill_over_water":6,"content_created":["Personal vacation photography"],"btm_category":"OCEAN STEWARD (NGO/scientific focus, conservation-driven)","involvement_level":"Complete beginner","online_presence":"None of the above","income_from_photography":"No, not yet.","primary_goal":"Transform hobby into professional career","secondary_goal":"Document marine conservation/research","learning_aspects":["Camera settings and techniques","Lighting techniques","Marine life behavior understanding","Business aspects of underwater photography","Client relations and project management","Conservation documentation"],"content_to_create":["Documentary style photo series","Scientific/research documentation","Conservation stories"],"learning_approach":["Mixed approach (combination of group and individual)","Project-based learning (within a BTM project)"],"marine_subjects":["Big marine life (sharks, whales, etc.)","Marine behavior","Conservation stories"],"time_availability":"2-3 entire weeks at a time for a workshop, aproject or individual training","travel_willingness":"Yes, willing to travel internationally","start_timeline":"Within next 6 months","ultimate_vision":"tell honest, purposeful stories about marine ecosystems, especially in remote and lesser-documented places. I want my work to go beyond aesthetics and support conservation and research through strong storytelling and collaboration. Ultimately, my goal is to contribute to exploration-driven projects that combine fieldwork, impact, and meaningful visual narratives.","inspiration_to_apply":"I chose BTM because of its strong emphasis on real-world skills and storytelling — exactly what I need as I transition from a technical career into a professional, impact-driven path in underwater photography.","referral_source":["Social Media (Instagram, Facebook, etc.)"],"anything_else":"I’m exploring a career transition and want to turn my passion for diving and photography into a sustainable career. I’m still learning the business side of underwater photography and filmmaking, and I’m eager to learn how to build a professional path in this field."}'::jsonb, '{}', '[]'::jsonb, '2026-02-03T01:09:03+00:00');
INSERT INTO applications (program, status, user_id, answers, tags, admin_notes, submitted_at) VALUES ('photography', 'reviewing', NULL, '{"first_name":"Amit","last_name":"Cohen","email":"amitcohen355@gmail.com","age":"25-34","budget":"Moderate budget (1,000 - 3,000 €/USD)","phone":"+972587001700","gender":"Male","nationality":"Israeli","country_of_residence":"Israel","languages":"English, Hebrew","current_occupation":"Freedive center worker","physical_fitness":"Excellent - Regular exercise, no health concerns","health_conditions":"No health conditions affecting diving","diving_types":["Recreational Scuba diving","Freediving","Snorkeling"],"certification_level":"Advanced Open Water, Certified Freediver, please specify level below:, Stage B freediver- Apnea International, about to complete stage C","number_of_dives":"51-250","last_dive_date":"19.12.2025","diving_environments":["Tropical Reefs","Night diving","Cave/Wreck diving","Drift diving"],"buoyancy_skill":8,"equipment_owned":["Action camera (GoPro, Osmo, Insta360, etc)","DSLR/Mirrorless with housing"],"photography_equipment":"Canon R8 \nIkelite 200DLM/D Housing\nGoPro 11","planning_to_invest":"No immediate plans","years_experience":"None","skill_camera_settings":5,"skill_lighting":2,"skill_post_production":4,"skill_color_correction":3,"skill_composition":3,"skill_drone":5,"skill_over_water":8,"content_created":["None yet","excited to start"],"btm_category":"BEGINNER - Creative Explorer (Just starting, hobby-focused, seeking basic skills)","involvement_level":"Hobby only","online_presence":"None of the above","income_from_photography":"No, not yet.","primary_goal":"Improve content creation for social media","secondary_goal":"Transform hobby into professional career","learning_aspects":["Basic equipment setup and operation","Camera settings and techniques","Lighting techniques","Marine life behavior understanding","Composition and content planning","Post-production and editing"],"content_to_create":["Personal/travel memories","Social media content","Documentary style photo series"],"learning_approach":["Group workshops (within a group of approx. 10 persons)","Small group workshop (within a group of approx. 4 persons)","Mixed approach (combination of group and individual)"],"marine_subjects":["Coral reefs","Big marine life (sharks, whales, etc.)"],"time_availability":"2-3 entire weeks at a time for a workshop, aproject or individual training","travel_willingness":"Yes, willing to travel internationally","start_timeline":"Within next 3 months","ultimate_vision":"My desire is to create content about marine life from around the globe, based more on still images and later also video.\nI want to share a story, a passion through my content.\nFor the future, I would love to work with dive centers, liveaboards and more. \nMy first step will be focusing on taking my UW photography to the next level.","inspiration_to_apply":"First of all, I’ve got into the UW photography from a pure love to the ocean and the marine life. \nI’ve been scuba diving for the last 4 years and in 2024 I got into freediving and for the past year I’ve been training on it more.\nDuring my scuba trips, I have been documenting with an Action camera and was a bit disappointed with the results. I knew I can document underwater life in a better way.\nI’m using Canon camera for a long time outside the water, so I was sure sometime I’ll start to take UW photography more seriously.\nThis morning I watched your video on the BTM Academy, and thought how spectacular it will be to work with this team and learn from them. Your YouTube channel have been my favorite marine life content for a while.","referral_source":["Social Media (Instagram, Facebook, etc.)"],"questions_or_concerns":"Just would like to get more information on the program (Where it would take place, pricing, schedule).","anything_else":"I got my new Ikelite gear just a few days ago. \nStill haven’t got into the water with it. \nI have a big desire to the ocean and specifically for marine life. My big goal is to document marine life around the world in the most natural and professional way possible. \nI want to share it all on social media but I haven’t started yet."}'::jsonb, '{}', '[]'::jsonb, '2026-02-03T07:58:26+00:00');
INSERT INTO applications (program, status, user_id, answers, tags, admin_notes, submitted_at) VALUES ('photography', 'reviewing', NULL, '{"first_name":"Morgan","last_name":"Rodriguez","email":"ramaarae@gmail.com","online_links":"www.instagram.com/morganrodriguez_photo/","age":"25-34","budget":"Moderate budget (1,000 - 3,000 €/USD)","phone":"1-7204132877","gender":"Female","nationality":"American","country_of_residence":"United States","languages":"English, Spanish","current_occupation":"Self Employed","physical_fitness":"Excellent - Regular exercise, no health concerns","health_conditions":"No health conditions affecting diving","diving_types":["Neither","but interested in learning"],"certification_level":"No certification yet","number_of_dives":"0-50","last_dive_date":"25.02.2026","diving_environments":["I''m a beginner"],"buoyancy_skill":1,"equipment_owned":["DSLR/Mirrorless with housing"],"photography_equipment":"None. I own a Canon 5D Mark ii","planning_to_invest":"Yes, within the next years","years_experience":"None","skill_camera_settings":8,"skill_lighting":6,"skill_post_production":7,"skill_color_correction":8,"skill_composition":8,"skill_drone":1,"skill_over_water":1,"content_created":["None yet","excited to start"],"btm_category":"INDEPENDENT CREATOR (Experienced hobbyist/influencer seeking improvement)","involvement_level":"Complete beginner","online_presence":"Active social media, Personal website, Professional portfolio, Client base","income_from_photography":"No, not yet.","primary_goal":"Enhance existing professional skills","secondary_goal":"Document marine conservation/research","learning_aspects":["Basic equipment setup and operation","Camera settings and techniques","Lighting techniques","Marine life behavior understanding","Conservation documentation"],"content_to_create":["Documentary style photo series","Scientific/research documentation","Conservation stories"],"learning_approach":["One-on-one mentorship","Mixed approach (combination of group and individual)"],"marine_subjects":["Coral reefs","Big marine life (sharks, whales, etc.)","Macro subjects","Conservation stories"],"time_availability":"2-3 entire weeks at a time for a workshop, aproject or individual training","travel_willingness":"Yes, willing to travel internationally","start_timeline":"Within next 6 months","ultimate_vision":"I am an experienced portrait photographer with a background in intimate photography that focuses on the relationship between women and the land they live on. I have Indigenous Mexican roots, so land relationship, and seeing our land, oceans, and ecosystems as living relatives is very important for my culture.\n\nThe ocean is an environment that both terrifies me and magnetizes me, and I want to learn more about being a more responsible artist, diver, and witness to its power. I am interested in using underwater photography as a way to platform the beauty, fragility, and conservation reality of our oceans, while continuing to explore the relationship between people and the environments that shape them.\n\nBuilding the skillset of underwater photography feels like a daunting task to take on alone, and I cherish being able to work in small groups and with trusted teachers to build both this skill and this relationship with the ocean.","inspiration_to_apply":"I live in the Rocky Mountains in Colorado USA, and connection to nature is an extremely important part of my life. My home has no central heat or many common modern amenities, so tracking the patterns of the forest around me has become essential. Noticing the shifts of seasons, incoming storms, animal and bird behaviors, predators in the area (so I can button up my chickens), and subtle environmental changes are all things I''m routinely in touch with.\n\nI feel deeply connected to my ecosystem and want to use my work and platform to advocate for the importance of relationship between people and the earth.\n\nI was born in coastal California and absolutely love returning to the ocean whenever I can travel. As a birth worker, Indigenous healer, and photographer, documenting the relationship between people and land is a core value in my work. I am always paying attention to how bodies exist within environment. How they are shaped by it, how they move through it, and how they are supported by it.\n\nUnderwater photography feels like one of the next natural steps in my path. It allows me to deepen my craft while exploring and revering a new environment that I have always felt intrinsically tied to.","referral_source":["Social Media (Instagram, Facebook, etc.)"],"questions_or_concerns":"I do not yet have diving experience or my own housing gear. I understand this work can take many years to hone, and I am committed to approaching it with patience and respect. I would value guidance on \"where to start.\"","anything_else":"Not at this moment, thank you for your time."}'::jsonb, '{}', '[]'::jsonb, '2026-02-26T03:13:34+00:00');
INSERT INTO applications (program, status, user_id, answers, tags, admin_notes, submitted_at) VALUES ('photography', 'reviewing', NULL, '{"first_name":"Tia","last_name":"Krum","email":"Tmegardner92@gmail.com","online_links":"Instagram : seaktheseaphotos for portraits, seaktheseaadventures for personal/wildlife/underwater adventure photos","age":"25-34","budget":"Moderate budget (1,000 - 3,000 €/USD)","phone":"2405772902","gender":"Female","nationality":"American","country_of_residence":"USA","languages":"English, Learning Spanish but not fluent","current_occupation":"Administrative as well as portrait (human) photographer","physical_fitness":"Average - Some physical activity, manageable health conditions","health_conditions":"Yes, but cleared by doctor for diving","diving_types":["Freediving","Snorkeling","Started scuba cert"],"certification_level":"No certification yet, Have taken freediving courses ; just need to do certification dives - live in an area where freediving is not a thing.","number_of_dives":"0-50","last_dive_date":"25.08.2025","diving_environments":["Tropical Reefs","Ocean freediving"],"buoyancy_skill":5,"equipment_owned":["Action camera (GoPro, Osmo, Insta360, etc)","DSLR/Mirrorless with housing"],"photography_equipment":"Sony A7IV  with 17-75mm lens & aquatech housing with insta360 attachment","planning_to_invest":"No immediate plans","years_experience":"1-3 years","skill_camera_settings":8,"skill_lighting":5,"skill_post_production":6,"skill_color_correction":6,"skill_composition":6,"skill_drone":1,"skill_over_water":9,"content_created":["Personal vacation photography","I have photographed sharks and various marine life","but not heavily."],"btm_category":"DEDICATED ACHIEVER (Business-focused, seeking intensive mentorship)","involvement_level":"I am a beginner in underwater photography but desperately want to create images that capture emotions/story to aid in conservation and connecting people with the ocean who may not get the opportunity to connect","online_presence":"Active social media, Client base","income_from_photography":"No, not yet.","primary_goal":"Document marine conservation/research","secondary_goal":"Transform hobby into professional career","learning_aspects":["Camera settings and techniques","Lighting techniques","Marine life behavior understanding","Composition and content planning","Post-production and editing","Business aspects of underwater photography","Conservation documentation"],"content_to_create":["Personal/travel memories","Documentary style photo series","Scientific/research documentation","Conservation stories"],"learning_approach":["Small group workshop (within a group of approx. 4 persons)","One-on-one mentorship","Mixed approach (combination of group and individual)","Project-based learning (within a BTM project)"],"marine_subjects":["Coral reefs","Big marine life (sharks, whales, etc.)","Marine behavior","Conservation stories"],"time_availability":"1 week to 10 days for a workshop, a project or individual training","travel_willingness":"Depends on duration and location","start_timeline":"Flexible/Not sure yet","ultimate_vision":"Honestly I just want to make an impact. I don’t care about making money persay…and I only care about followers for awareness reasons not for popularity. The ocean is my heart and I can feel every vibration of energy. I can feel how misunderstood she is, and I know I have this gift for a reason. I want to use photos to connect the average person to what us ocean people see, and feel, and change minds. So much of our ocean is misunderstood which causes fear and disconnection. But, I don’t really know how to do that at times. I get overwhelmed sticking to a style or a theme. Or my photos don’t portray exactly what I hope for them too and I’m not sure what parts I’m missing. Maybe it’s an editing thing? Maybe it’s an angle or lighting thing? I’d love for my work to additionally benefit social behaviors, marine life tracking/identification and aid in conservation.","inspiration_to_apply":"Underwater photography speaks to my heart. Being able to capture moments in time face to face with other living creatures that most of the world will never fully experience is a gift. I feel it can create change, compassion, connection, and even legacy when used to its full potential. I chose BTM because I feel the professionals ive followed produce similar artwork that I hope to and have a deep understanding of the best ways to guide me to a higher level of knowledge than I can gain elsewhere.","referral_source":["Social Media (Instagram, Facebook, etc.)"],"questions_or_concerns":"Admittedly, I’m not super skilled in the water yet as far as actual freediving depth skills go. I have knowledge. I have training. But I don’t live in an area where I can practice depth frequently. I am comfortable in the water, and I am working on them as much as I can (pool, travel trips for freediving etc). I also just started a new job so at this exact second I have no leave."}'::jsonb, '{}', '[]'::jsonb, '2026-03-26T17:39:15+00:00');
INSERT INTO applications (program, status, user_id, answers, tags, admin_notes, submitted_at) VALUES ('photography', 'reviewing', NULL, '{"first_name":"Kate","last_name":"Müller-Czarnek","email":"katczarnek@gmail.com","online_links":"wedding photography website: https://mullerkate.com/en/home\n\nprivate/hobby:\nhttps://www.instagram.com/unsimple.kejti?igsh=a2NjY2JwM21zbG5r&utm_source=qr","age":"25-34","budget":"Moderate budget (1,000 - 3,000 €/USD)","nickname":"just Kate","phone":"+48 504163583","gender":"Female","nationality":"polish","country_of_residence":"Polska","languages":"English, polish","current_occupation":"wedding photojournalist","physical_fitness":"Good - Moderately active, no major health concerns","health_conditions":"No health conditions affecting diving","diving_types":["Recreational Scuba diving","Freediving"],"certification_level":"Advanced Open Water","number_of_dives":"0-50","last_dive_date":"22.08.2025","diving_environments":["Tropical Reefs","deepspot Poland"],"buoyancy_skill":7,"equipment_owned":["Action camera (GoPro, Osmo, Insta360, etc)","DSLR/Mirrorless with housing"],"photography_equipment":"Sony AIV tamron 17-28mm 2.8","planning_to_invest":"Yes, within the next years","years_experience":"1-3 years","skill_camera_settings":9,"skill_lighting":6,"skill_post_production":7,"skill_color_correction":7,"skill_composition":7,"skill_drone":1,"skill_over_water":6,"content_created":["underwater portraits with one or two models"],"btm_category":"INDEPENDENT CREATOR (Experienced hobbyist/influencer seeking improvement)","involvement_level":"Hobby only","online_presence":"Active social media, Personal website","income_from_photography":"No, not yet.","primary_goal":"Improve content creation for social media","secondary_goal":"Transform hobby into professional career","learning_aspects":["Camera settings and techniques","Composition and content planning","Post-production and editing","Business aspects of underwater photography","Client relations and project management"],"content_to_create":["Personal/travel memories","Social media content","Commercial/advertising content"],"learning_approach":["Mixed approach (combination of group and individual)"],"marine_subjects":["Coral reefs","Big marine life (sharks, whales, etc.)","Marine behavior"],"time_availability":"now and then for online classes","travel_willingness":"Depends on duration and location","start_timeline":"Flexible/Not sure yet","ultimate_vision":"I’d like to somehow transfer the stories about love I tell in my wedding journalism to underwater tales. To show the dependency between human and nature and how we are small in comparison to the the underwater realm.","inspiration_to_apply":"I am drew to the water and enchanted by how it shapes the light. I loved your “Alive” youtube video, it lit the urge to try more and be brave. I live in the centre of Europe with no easy access to open water so I am surely lacking experience but also confidence as nobody in my area is not doing anything like it.","referral_source":["I did my freediving course with Wojtek Dopierala and saw that he was working with you."],"questions_or_concerns":"What are the next steps in this application process?","anything_else":"Since it’s still a hobby and I am freelance working mom with really hard logistics for free time this year I really hope I can pull this off, despite that right now it seems like impossible."}'::jsonb, '{}', '[]'::jsonb, '2026-03-26T18:21:34+00:00');
INSERT INTO applications (program, status, user_id, answers, tags, admin_notes, submitted_at) VALUES ('photography', 'reviewing', NULL, '{"first_name":"Lucia","last_name":"Tuzinska","email":"tuzenska@gmail.com","online_links":"www.lutu.photos, @tuzenska","age":"35-44","budget":"Moderate budget (1,000 - 3,000 €/USD)","nickname":"Lusea","phone":"00421918396626","gender":"Female","nationality":"Slovak","country_of_residence":"Slovakia","languages":"English, Spanish","current_occupation":"Freelance photographer","physical_fitness":"Good - Moderately active, no major health concerns","health_conditions":"No health conditions affecting diving","diving_types":["Recreational Scuba diving","Freediving","Snorkeling"],"certification_level":"Open Water, Advanced Open Water, Certified Freediver, please specify level below:, AIDA II, Tenerife","number_of_dives":"51-250","last_dive_date":"23.04.2024","diving_environments":["Tropical Reefs","Deep diving","Night diving","Cave/Wreck diving"],"buoyancy_skill":9,"equipment_owned":["Action camera (GoPro, Osmo, Insta360, etc)","DSLR/Mirrorless with housing","Professional photo/video camera"],"photography_equipment":"Not having one yet, just gopro and previously dome","planning_to_invest":"Yes, within the near future","years_experience":"Less than 1 year","skill_camera_settings":10,"skill_lighting":5,"skill_post_production":10,"skill_color_correction":10,"skill_composition":10,"skill_drone":6,"skill_over_water":10,"content_created":["artistic","hopefully later on something to support ocean"],"btm_category":"OCEAN STEWARD (NGO/scientific focus, conservation-driven)","involvement_level":"Hobby only","online_presence":"Active social media, Personal website, Professional portfolio, Client base","income_from_photography":"No, not yet.","primary_goal":"Enhance existing professional skills","secondary_goal":"Document marine conservation/research","learning_aspects":["Basic equipment setup and operation","Camera settings and techniques","Lighting techniques","Marine life behavior understanding","Post-production and editing","Business aspects of underwater photography","Conservation documentation","artistic approach"],"content_to_create":["Documentary style photo series","Commercial/advertising content","Conservation stories","visual asseys"],"learning_approach":["Mixed approach (combination of group and individual)","Project-based learning (within a BTM project)"],"marine_subjects":["Coral reefs","Big marine life (sharks, whales, etc.)","Marine behavior","Conservation stories"],"time_availability":"1 week to 10 days for a workshop, a project or individual training","travel_willingness":"Yes, willing to travel internationally","start_timeline":"Flexible/Not sure yet","ultimate_vision":"I would love to keep exploring aliveness but finally getting more comfortable underwater.  My ultimate vision is to create images that where bodies, breath, and the ocean itself become one. I’m drawn to freediving and artistic expression, to capture the fluidity, emotion, and impermanence of underwater life. I love interesting compositions, split shots, and immersive wide-angle imagery that invite viewers to feel, not just see. My goal is to push beyond technical photography and into creating experience-driven art that celebrates human and oceanic blend.","inspiration_to_apply":"I found you thriugh Zoe, and was instantly inspired by the name you chose, that is why I clicked :) then further more by the way you guys communicate online and the meaning around your vision. I love spaces where there is a vision to bridge meaningful with skillfull. It represents an opportunity to learn from experienced professionals, gain structured guidance, and refine my artistic voice while in the water. I’m eager to merge technical skills with my own creative, expressive approach and this program feels like the perfect space to grow my skills while being fully immersed in the oceanic environment I love. I even created reel from the music you had on your profile, because it just touched something real in me, and that is I find is social media for.","referral_source":["Zoe account"],"questions_or_concerns":"I feel like I will wait for what you will bring about and then the questions will arise for sure :)","anything_else":"Thanks for being and doing meaningful and deep stuff."}'::jsonb, '{}', '[]'::jsonb, '2026-03-31T11:28:15+00:00');
